title: butterball cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large mixer bowl.
Mix at low speed until dough forms and becomes lighter in color.
Shape into balls, using a rounded teaspoonful for each.
Place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 18 minutes.
Do not brown. Roll warm cookies in confectioners sugar.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt in top of double boiler.
Add milk; when slightly thickened, add a little to beaten egg yolks. Return egg yolks back to the mixture and cook until it's the right thickness.
Remove from heat and add vanilla, butter and coconut. Let cool and put in precooked pie crust.
Add meringue; top with coconut and brown in oven.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Roll out crescents on cookie sheet putting edges together. Bake according to directions.

title: heavenly spinach
directions: Cook spinach and drain.
Saute mushrooms in butter.
Combine sour cream, mayo and cheese.
Stir in spinach and mushrooms. Season with salt and pepper.
Pour in a 9 x 13-inch greased dish. Slice tomatoes 1/2 inch and place on top.
Saute bread crumbs in butter and put on top of tomatoes.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes. Serves 10 to 12.

title: spinach dip
directions: Stir in package of spinach and chestnuts to first 4 ingredients.
Chill.
Makes 3 cups.

title: *moussaka 1
directions: Slice eggplant crosswise, 1/2-inch thick.
To remove bitter taste, salt both sides of slices and place in a colander. Top with a heavy object to drain. Pat dry with paper towels.
Place slices on foil lined baking sheet.
Brush both sides with oil and brown under broiler.
Line bottom of baking pan with eggplant slices.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix Jell-O with boiling water. Add cranberry sauce, drained pineapple (save juice) and pecans. Mix well and pour 1/2 into 9 x 13 x 2-inch dish. Chill until firm. Cream cheese 1/4 to 1/3 cup pineapple juice and mayonnaise together and pour over mixture. Cover with remaining Jell-O mixture and chill. May use 1/2 of 8 ounce tub of Cool Whip with cream cheese, pineapple juice and mayonnaise.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Cool and debone.
Keep the broth to use later.
In a saucepan, prepare stuffing and use broth instead of water.
Warm the cream of chicken soup with 1/2 cup of the broth.
Mix until creamy.
Heat the mixed vegetables and set aside. Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam and alternate layers of chicken, vegetables, stuffing and soup.
When finished, cover with foil and bake in a 375° oven and cook until bubbly.
Remove foil; sprinkle on parsley or cheese and broil until brown.
Let set 1/2 hour before serving.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve the yeast in the warm water.
Mix the next 5 ingredients together.
Add yeast mixture to the second mixture. Add approximately 3 cups of bread flour, a little at a time, until mixture is "workable."
Knead until well mixed.
Place in well-greased bowl and flip dough to grease the top.
Cover with a cloth; let double in size.
Punch down; roll out dough and shape into rolls.
Butter tops; cover and let double.
(You can prepare these ahead of time and refrigerate dough before the second rising.)
Bake at 450° for about 6 minutes.
Yields 36.

title: zesty green beans
directions: Warm beans and pour off liquid.
In separate pan, mix next 6 ingredients.
Cook slightly.
Pour over beans in buttered casserole.
Mix melted butter and corn flakes.
Sprinkle over beans.
Top with cheese.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: texas potatoes
directions: Mix together in large bowl the frozen hash browns, with all ingredients except corn flake crumbs which go on top.
Bake in large Pyrex casserole dish at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Scald milk.
Mix sugar, flour and salt and add to well beaten eggs.
Pour into scalded milk and add chocolate and vanilla; cook until thick.
Pour into baked pie shell and serve with whipped cream.

title: chicken, rice and peas au gratin
directions: Melt 3 tablespoons butter in saucepan over medium heat.
Blend in flour and tarragon and cook 1 minute without browning. Gradually stir in broth and milk until thickened and smooth.
Fold in chicken and add salt and pepper; set aside.
Spread rice in greased 6-cup shallow baking dish; sprinkle with peas and pour on creamed chicken.
Dot with remaining 1 tablespoon butter, then sprinkle with Parmesan and bread crumbs.
Bake in preheated 400° oven until bubbly, about 20 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: swedish apple crumble
directions: Empty 1 can apple into a shallow 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Combine 1/4 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle half this mixture over apples.
Add other can of apples and sprinkle rest of the mixture over them.
Combine flour and 1/2 cup of sugar.
Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse cornmeal.
Spread over top of apples.
Bake in preheated 425° oven for 15 minutes or until top is browned.
Serve warm or cold.

title: string bean casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Garnish with bread crumbs or crushed crackers.
Bake at 300° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: orange sherbet salad
directions: Prepare whipped cream or Dream Whip.
Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add orange sherbet and other ingredients.
Fold in whipped cream.
Chill.
Serves 12.

title: barbecue ribs
directions: Broil or brown spareribs.
Combine catsup, brown sugar, paprika, vinegar, salt, Worcestershire sauce, water and onion flakes (or diced onions) to make a sauce.
Place spareribs in baking dish.
Cover with sauce.
Bake covered for 2 to 3 hours at 350°.
Baste often.

title: sally lunn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease tube pan.
Heat milk, shortening and 1/4 cup of water until very warm.
Blend 1 1/3 cups flour with sugar, salt and yeast in large mixing bowl.
Blend warm liquids into the flour mixture.
Beat with mixer on medium about 2 minutes.
Gradually add about 2/3 cup of flour and eggs.
Beat at high speed about 2 minutes.
Add remaining flour (2 cups).
Batter will be thick, but not stiff.
Cover and let dough rise in a warm draft-free place until doubled in size, approximately 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Beat dough down with spatula.

title: deviled eggs
directions: When boiling eggs, if a teaspoon of vinegar is added, the eggs are easier to peel and less likely to crack.
Cut eggs lengthwise in half.
Slip out egg yolks and mash with fork.
Mix in all other ingredients, then fill egg whites with egg yolk mixture. Cover and refrigerate until served.
Makes 24.

title: christmas salad
directions: Cut broccoli in small florets.
Chop onion and mix raisins in a bowl.
Brown bacon and let cool.
Crunch up and add to mixture. Mix the mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar together.
Pour over broccoli, onion, raisins and bacon.
Place in the refrigerator a few hours before serving.

title: zucchini cake
directions: In large bowl, mix together.
Bake in 2 greased loaf pans at 325° for 1 hour.

title: eclair cake
directions: Line bottom of 9 x 13-inch cake pan with graham crackers; this is the first layer of the cake.

title: snowballs
directions: Cook butter, sugar and dates in heavy pan for 6 minutes on slow heat.
Stir constantly.
Cool a few minutes.
Add pecans and Rice Krispies.
Form mixture into small balls and roll in coconut.

title: patsy's hot mustard barbecue sauce
directions: Place ketchup and both types of mustards (yellow and Dijon) in a medium saucepan.
Add salt, black pepper and sugar; mix well. Add liquid smoke and stir again.
Blend the horseradish and the jalapeno peppers in a blender with the vinegar.
Blend for 1 minute until all ingredients are liquefied, then add to sauce. Squeeze the lemon juice directly into the pan, then add whole lemon to mixture.
Blend well with other ingredients.

title: noodle-rice casserole
directions: Melt margarine in large skillet; add angel hair that is broken into 1 1/2-inch pieces.
Cook until golden brown; stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Pour into lightly greased 8-inch square baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes, stirring once.
Yields 6 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken until done.
Remove from pot and cook noodles in broth until tender.
Cut chicken in small pieces and mix noodles, chicken soup and sour cream.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Pour into large casserole dish.
Mix melted margarine and bread crumbs and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: pinto bean casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Combine tomato sauce, catsup and Worcestershire sauce then mix with beef and onion. Place pinto beans in ungreased casserole dish.
Pour beef mixture over beans.
Prepare corn muffin mix as directed.
Spread over beef mixture.
Bake as directed on corn muffin mix box.

title: homemade caramel corn
directions: Remove any unpopped kernels of corn from popcorn.
Add peanuts; set aside.

title: fruit salad
directions: Combine fruit, miniature marshmallows and sour cream.
Mix together lightly and chill in refrigerator.

title: jello cake
directions: Mix orange jello with 3/4 cup boiling water and 3/4 cup cold water.
Let stand.
Make 1 box orange supreme cake mix and pour cooled jello over it.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except chocolate chips until well beaten, about 2 minutes. Stir in chocolate chips. Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes. Yield: 14 to 16 servings.

title: granny anderson's doughnuts
directions: Measure 1 1/2 cups of flour first.
Mix all dry ingredients and set aside remaining flour.
Add wet ingredients to dry ingredients, then slowly add more flour to the dough mix.
Turn out onto well-floured surface and roll and cut doughnuts.
Fry 2 to 3 minutes.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve sugared or plain. Yields 2 dozen.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
In large bowl, combine flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt (if desired).
Using a fork, mix well.
Using pastry blender, cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Add buttermilk.
Using fork mix just until mixture forms soft dough and leaves sides of bowl (it may be a bit sticky).

title: boxman's cherry torte
directions: Beat egg and add sugar.
After sugar dissolves, fold in drained cherries.
Sift dry ingredients together and fold into cherry mixture.
Add butter and extract.

title: egg & sausage casserole
directions: Fry sausage.
Drain.
Beat eggs, add soup and mix well.
Add cheese and sausage.
Blend in well.
Pour in large casserole sprayed with Pam.
Bake 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush cookies.
Cream butter, cream cheese and powdered sugar; set aside.
Mix pudding and milk, add Cool Whip.
Alternate layers of cookies and pudding mixture, begin and end with cookies.
Use 8-inch plastic flower pot and add silk flowers or use 9 x 11-inch Pyrex dish.

title: norwegian cabbage
directions: Shred
cabbage.
Melt
butter.	Add cabbage and brown a bit, stirring often. Add chicken broth or chicken bouillon and water and brown sugar. Cover and steam until tender.

title: homemade spaghetti
directions: Cook ground beef, onion, pepper and garlic until onion is tender and meat is brown.
Drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Simmer for 1 1/2 hours in slow cooker, stirring occasionally.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Prepare pie shell.
Beat eggs slightly in a medium size bowl. Blend in sugar, flour, butter and vanilla.
Stir in pecans and chocolate pieces.
Pour into prepared pastry shell.
Bake in a slow oven (325°) for 50 minutes or until lightly golden and firm on top.
Cool on wire rack.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix as listed.
Mixture will be coarse.
Bake in tube or Bundt pan for 1 hour and 20 minutes at 350°.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pudding and Cool Whip.
Add other ingredients; refrigerate.

title: jellied cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve raspberry jello in 1 cup hot water.
Add 1 cup cold water.
Chill until partially set.
Fold in the orange, pineapple, cranberries and nuts.
Chill until firm.
Cut in squares and "tie" with cream cheese.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Top with crushed corn flakes or potato chips.
Dot with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: sausage breakfast casserole
directions: Cook sausage until done.
Crumble and drain.
Spread each slice of bread with margarine.
Cut into squares.
Place in 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Sprinkle with sausage.
Top with cheese. Combine remaining ingredients and pour over sausage and cheese. Let sit 8 hours or overnight.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: pork chops and apple stuffing
directions: Place chops in ungreased casserole.
Saute celery and onion in margarine in saucepan over medium heat until onion is tender, about 5 minutes.
Toss celery mixture, croutons, nuts and apples in bowl. Stir in juice to desired moisture.
Spoon mixture evenly over chops.
Cover and cook in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Uncover and cook until stuffing is dry on top, 15 to 20 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: "fasties, but goodies"(cheezy muffins)
directions: Mix well all ingredients.
Spoon into 3 miniature muffin pans. Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: brownies
directions: Cream sugar and butter well.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add flour and chocolate syrup, alternately, ending with flour.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: canned peppers and cabbage
directions: Wash and clean insides of peppers.
Cover peppers with hot water 15 minutes.
Bring water, vinegar and sugar to boil.
Drain peppers and pack with shredded cabbage in hot jars.
Put 1 teaspoon salad oil and 1/2 teaspoon salt to each pint.
Pour hot solution over peppers and seal.

title: corn meal muffins
directions: Beat egg.
Add buttermilk and soda.
Blend in approximately 1 cup of meal.
Do not have mixture thick.
Put into greased muffin tins (12).
Bake in oven at about 375° until tops brown.
Let stand a few minutes before getting out of tins.
"Takes practice."

title: chipped beef dip
directions: Cut up chipped beef and the green part of the onions.
Mix all ingredients together.
Serve with pretzels, chips or crackers.

title: tamale pie
directions: Cut tamales into 1/2-inch slices and arrange in bottom of deep casserole (about 4-quart size).
Layer with half the cooked ground beef.
Sprinkle a layer of half the green chilies, half the corn, 1/2 the olives and 1/2 the onions.
Repeat with tamale slices and so on.
Top with shredded cheese and then an even covering of tomato sauce or salsa.
Bake in a 350° oven, uncovered, for about an hour.
Amounts of ingredients can be adjusted.
Can be frozen and/or microwaved.

title: clam dip
directions: Beat all ingredients well with an electric mixer.

title: nutty apple dip
directions: Mix ingredients together in small bowl, saving a few teaspoons of nuts to sprinkle on top.
Chill.
Dip apple slices into nutty dip.
Tastes like caramel apples.
(Apple slices can be kept in a bowl of cold water to prevent them from turning brown.)
The kids love it!!

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients until well blended.
Bake in tube cake pan for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: bud's gooey butter cake(serves 10)
directions: Mix butter, 2 eggs and yellow cake mix. Put in greased 13 x 9 pan. Mix powdered sugar, cream cheese and 2 beaten eggs. Pour over top of cake. Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°. Prep: 1:00. Cook: 35. Total: 1:35.

title: spanish treasure casserole
directions: Sift flour and baking powder in bowl.
Add shortening and 1/2 cup grated cheese.
Cut in with pastry blender or two knives.
Add 1/2 cup milk all at once.
Stir just until moistened.
Spread in 8 x 12-inch casserole dish.
Melt bacon drippings in frying pan. Add sliced onions and cook over medium heat until limp and light brown.
Stir in ham.
Spoon onion-ham mixture over batter in casserole.
Top with remaining cheese.
Beat together egg, remaining milk and mustard.
Pour over onion mixture.
Bake 10 minutes at 450°.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 20 minutes longer. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Marinate vegetables in Italian dressing for 24 hours and serve.
(Other fresh vegetables may be substituted according to personal preference.)

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients. Bring to a boil and boil rapidly for 30 seconds. Remove from heat. Stir in peanut butter, oatmeal and vanilla. Mix well. Drop by a teaspoon on waxed paper and cool.

title: stromboli(italian bread loaf with meat and cheese)
directions: Place risen dough on floured board.
Flatten and stretch into approximately 12 x 15-inches.
Spread ingredients over surface of dough in following order:
tomatoes, onions, pastrami, oregano, garlic powder, salt and pepper.
Roll dough lengthwise in jellyroll fashion.
Pinch edges to secure ingredients.
Roll will resemble roll of French bread.
Carefully place on nonstick cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes until golden brown.
Cool well.
Cut into 3/4-inch slices just before serving.

title: southwest hot green chili chicken soup
directions: Chop onion and peppers; saute in butter.
Blend in flour and other ingredients.
Add chicken and chicken stock; bring to a boil.
Simmer until smooth.
Add cream or milk.
Heat, then add sour cream.
(I add a few pieces of cut red, dry, chili peppers.)

title: low-fat pecan oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream sugars and margarine. Add egg whites, mixing well. Add raisin water, applesauce and vanilla. Sift together flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg. Add oatmeal to dry ingredients and fold all into creamed mixture. Blend well. Fold in raisins and nuts. Spoon dough onto cookie sheet sprayed with vegetable cooking spray. Bake at 375° for 9 to 10 minutes depending on individual ovens. These are very moist cookies.

title: roast turkey
directions: Rinse
turkey inside and out.
Remove neck and giblets. Mix spices in a bowl and rub mixture inside and on the outside of the turkey.
Cut
celery and onion in large pieces.
Place along with garlic inside of turkey.
Put bacon strips over the breast.
Add enough
water
to
steam the bird in moist heat. Maintain water level by checking.	Start with 14 coals on top and 14
coals on the bottom for 20 minutes.	Then reduce to 12 coals on top	and 10	on the bottom for 1 1/2 hours or longer until done.
Replenish coals as needed.

title: something good
directions: Line cookie sheet with foil, then line with graham crackers.

title: monkey bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Cut biscuits into 1/4-inch balls and roll in sugar mixture and drop into pan.
Sprinkle remaining sugar mixture over biscuits and pour melted butter over biscuits.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: easy ripe olive jambalaya
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; add onion, green pepper and garlic. Saute until tender.
Blend in flour, salt, pepper, paprika and Worcestershire.
Cut olives in halves; add to sauteed mixture. Stir in tomatoes.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened. Arrange rice and shrimp in buttered casserole.
Pour vegetable mixture over shrimp and rice and mix.
Bake for about 20 minutes and heated through in a 350° oven.

title: taco pizza dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and onion dip until smooth.
Spread on round tray.
Brown beef and drain.
Mix in taco seasoning.
Spread beef on cheese mixture.
Top with green peppers, onions and then cheese.
Refrigerate.
Serve with Fritos.

title: cheese dreams
directions: Bring cheese and margarine to room temperature.
Combine all ingredients well.
Roll into small balls (the size of a marble). Place on an ungreased cookie sheet 1 inch apart and press slightly with a fork.
Bake at 325° for approximately 20 minutes.
Cool and store in an airtight container.

title: no-fat yogurt herbed "cream cheese"
directions: In a bowl, whip together the yogurt, dried milk and herbs. Place Mr. Coffee filter into a sieve or colander.
Spoon the yogurt mixture into the filter.
Suspend the filter above a bowl (cover the exposed surface with waxed paper).
Place into the refrigerator for 24 hours.
The whey will separate from the cheese and drop into the bowl.
The longer the cheese is left in the refrigerator, the firmer the cheese.
Remove the cheese and serve with crackers. Store in closed container.

title: church beans
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: renee's chicken
directions: Place the chicken breasts in a baking pan. Mix first 4 ingredients together and spread on top of chicken and bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: broken glass torte
directions: Dissolve the 3 packages of flavored gelatin dessert in 1 1/2 cups hot water and chill in separate cake pans until firm 1 day before.
Cut into cubes 1 1/2-inches wide.
Soften the plain gelatin in cold water and dissolve in hot pineapple juice.
Cool and fold into sweetened whipped cream.
Fold the colored Jell-O carefully into whipped cream mixture.
Turn into spring-form pan which has been lined with the ladyfingers.
Chill at least 6 hours before serving.

title: low-fat chocolate cloud cake
directions: Sift together flour, cocoa, sugar, baking soda, baking powder and salt into mixing bowl.
Stir until blended.
Add prunes, vanilla, eggs and milk and stir just until blended.
Combine Espresso and boiling water and stir until dissolved.
Stir into batter until blended.
Pour batter into 2 (9-inch) round baking pans sprayed with nonstick vegetable spray.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, or until center tests done with wood pick.
Let cakes cool in pans for 10 minutes.
Invert onto wire rack to cool. Spread top of 1 cake with Seven Minute Frosting.
Place remaining cake on top and frost both layers.

title: baked ham and macaroni
directions: Cook and drain macaroni.
Combine with ham, soup, water and onion.
Arrange in greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle top with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Combine flour, salt, baking powder, pepper, flour, eggs, onion and parsley. Add potatoes to mixture
and beat throughly with a spoon.
Cook over medium heat until golden brown and crisp on one side.
Turn carefully and brown on other side.
Serve with applesauce.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Wash broccoli and chop fine.
Mix all other ingredients together. Salt and pepper to taste.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours.

title: broccoli in sour cream
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Mix with other ingredients and spoon into small casserole dish.
Sprinkle with additional cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
(Cheddar cheese can be used.)

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together shortening, brown sugar and eggs until light and fluffy.
Stir in sweet milk.
Sift together dry ingredients; stir into creamed mixture.
Stir in rolled oats, nuts and raisins. Drop from tablespoon 2-inches apart on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 400° for about 8 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Remove from sheet.

title: chili
directions: In a large saucepan, cook ground beef, onion, green pepper and garlic until meat is brown.
Drain fat and stir in tomatoes, kidney beans, tomato sauce, chili powder, salt and pepper.
Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat and cover; simmer for 20 minutes.

title: asparagus soup
directions: Steam asparagus in broth until tender (do not discard liquid). In blender, puree asparagus and broth.
Add yogurt and cheeses. Blend well.
Season to taste.
May be served warmed or chilled. Serves 4.

title: homemade soap
directions: Melt grease and strain through cloth, then add equal amount of water and let stand for a day or two until the grease hardens on top of the water, that takes out the salt, etc.
When the grease has hardened, skim off of the water and put it into an enamel pail. In a bowl, take 1 quart of cold water plus 2/3 cup cold water, Purex and Borax.
Take outside and add lye to the mixture in the bowl, being careful not to inhale the fumes.
The lye will cause the water to almost boil.

Stir occasionally until lukewarm, then add slowly to the grease which should be the same temperature. Stir about 15 minutes or until about the consistency of honey. Pour into milk cartons or glass dishes.
Allow to stand for 2 days or until it can be cut.
Let harden a few weeks before using. 1.2 ounces of cotronella gives it a scent which is nice.
Good luck.

title: beef casserole
directions: Place hamburger in a 9 x 12-inch dish. Sprinkle a little Worcestershire sauce on hamburger. Cover meat with the onion soup. Cover with 1/2 can mushroom soup. Add vegetables and cover with remaining mushroom soup.
Cover top with Tater Tots.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or cream of chicken soup

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter, margarine, sugar and powdered sugar until creamy.
Add soda, cream of tartar, salt and vanilla; add beaten egg and flour.
Shape dough into balls size of a small walnut. Dip glass into additional sugar; press on cookie.
Bake 10 minutes at 375°.
Yields 4 dozen cookies.

title: artichoke crostini
directions: Slice Baguette into 36 slices (1/4 to 1/2-inch); place, cut side down, on aluminum foil-lined baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 5 minutes or until crisp.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Mix in order given; drop by spoonfuls on a greased or Teflon cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: zucchini appetizer
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch metal pan. Bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: sunshine salad
directions: Mix jello and Cool Whip.
Drain pineapple and mandarin oranges.
Add to jello mixture and mix well.
Add marshmallows and fold well.
Refrigerate overnight before serving.

title: easy trifle
directions: Drain raspberries, (save 1 c. of juice). Combine juice and cornstarch. Cook until clear, thickened. Chill. Mix milk and water. Stir into pudding. Mix. Beat to blend. chill 5 minutes. Whip cream, fold into pudding. Cut cake into bite sized pieces. (Could use sponge cake.) Put cubes into large bowl, sprinkle with orange
juice. Add a layer of raspberries, 1/2 of syrup juice, 1/2 pudding. Repeat layers. Chill 1 hour before serving. Sprinkle nuts over top.

title: hobo dinner
directions: Mix in large bowl, ground beef, ketchup, salt and pepper to taste. Shape into 3 to 4 patties about 1/2 inch thick. Place on individual sheets of foil; sprinkle with equal amounts of carrots, potatoes and onions on top of meat. Wrap securely with foil. Place on large baking sheet. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until carrots are done.

title: green beans with fresh tomato sauce
directions: Saute green pepper and onion in butter until soft, about 5 minutes.
Add tomato, oregano and salt.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Add cooked beans.
Stir and cook just enough to heat thoroughly. Serves 4.

title: oyster crackers snacks
directions: Combine oil, garlic powder, dill weed and lemon pepper; mix well.
Pour over crackers in large enough container to mix well. Add Ranch dressing and stir until well coated.
Sprinkle with Parmesan, if desired.
Store in airtight container.
Keeps well.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix flour and salt, cut in shortening.
Add sour cream and mix well (1 tablespoon shortening may be substituted for the sour cream).
Add enough water to mix well.

title: grandma o'neill's rolls
directions: Heat first 4 ingredients in pan until scalded; do not boil. Cool until warm.
With mixer and large bowl, beat eggs.
Mix water, sugar and yeast until dissolved in small bowl; set aside to let rise.
Slowly add warm liquid to eggs; alternate with flour and add yeast mixture.
Mix well.
Remove mixer; cover dough and let rise 2 hours.
Dump dough on floured surface and form into buns or crescent rolls.
Place in greased cookie sheet.
Cover and let rise 2 hours.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown. Spread melted butter on tops and enjoy.

title: chocolate delight bites
directions: Heat chocolate in large microwavable bowl at High for 2 minutes.
Stir until completely melted.
Or heat in heavy saucepan over very low heat.
Beat in cream cheese and vanilla.
Cool to room temperature.
Gently stir in whipped topping.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Shape quickly into 1-inch balls.
Roll in nuts, coconut or chocolate.
Store, covered, in refrigerator.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: impossible pizza
directions: Cook and stir sausage until brown; drain.
Sprinkle sausage, Parmesan cheese, onion, tomatoes, green pepper, basil, oregano and garlic salt in greased 10-inch pie plate.
Combine eggs, milk and flour and mix until smooth.
Pour into pie plate.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes or until done.
Cool 5 minutes before cutting.

title: chili mac
directions: Saute chopped onion and green pepper in small amount of margarine in pan.
Add ground beef.
Cook until browned.
Add tomato soup.
Season with chili powder to taste (approximately 2 tablespoons).
Cook elbow macaroni in water as directed on package.
Drain.
Mix the cooked macaroni together with the other ingredients.
Serve.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, salt and cocoa together.
Add milk, egg yolks and vanilla.
Boil until thick in double boiler.
Pour into cooled, baked pastry shell.
Beat egg whites for meringue.
Makes 1 pie.

title: roma meat roll
directions: Combine meat, egg, saltines, oregano and 2/3 cup tomato sauce. Mix well.
Pat meat into rectangle (on wax paper) approximately 12-inches long, 8-inches wide and 1/4-inch thick.
Sprinkle grated cheese over entire surface of meat to within 1/2-inch of edges. Beginning with long edge of meat, roll into roll as a jelly roll, keeping the ends of the roll closed as you roll.
Use the wax paper to assist you in forming the roll and transferring to cookie sheet for baking.
Bake 30 minutes at 375°, then pour remaining 1/3 cup tomato sauce over top.
Return to oven for 15 more minutes.

title: p~b mallow drops
directions: In a large bowl, mix nuts, mallows and Rice Krispies.

title: old kentucky nut cake
directions: Cream
together shortening, butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Then add flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir in milk, vanilla and walnuts.
Bake at 350°.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until light and fluffy.
Add sugar, oil and vanilla. Blend well.
Stir in zucchini.
Add all dry ingredients, then fold in the nuts.
Bake in greased and floured loaf pans for 50 to 60 minutes in 350° oven.
(I use a couple spoons of orange peel.)

title: warm tomato taco dip
directions: Reserve 2 tbsp tomatoes for garnish. Add remaining tomatoes and taco seasoning to skillet of drained beef. Cook for 5 minutes. Spoon into 1 1/2 quart shallow baking dish. Top with cheese. Garnish with reserved tomatoes and sliced green onions and sour cream, if desired. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: glazed fresh strawberry pie
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and boil until clear; add dry jello, lemon juice and food coloring.
Cool and pour over strawberries that have been placed in a baked pie shell.
Chill. May garnish with whipped topping, if desired.

title: bourbon balls
directions: Crush wafers and add powdered sugar, cocoa and nuts.
Mix thoroughly; add the corn syrup and bourbon and mix again.
Roll into balls the size of small walnuts and roll balls in powdered sugar.
Store in airtight container and refrigerate.

title: fast fixing chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour oil into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Tilt pan to cover bottom with oil.
Put remaining ingredients into pan; stir with fork until blended.
Scrape sides and spread batter evenly. Bake for 35 to 40 minutes, until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cooled cake may be sprinkled with powdered sugar, if desired.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown beef and onion in saucepan. Add onion, soup, salt, sugar, garlic and oregano leaves.
Simmer for 30 minutes.

title: my special meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 375° until done, approximately 1 hour.

title: orange cereal muffins
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. Add cereal.
Combine eggs, orange juice, margarine and rind. Add to flour mixture and mix only enough to dampen flour.
Spoon into greased muffin pans, filling 2/3 full. Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chicken mexican casserole
directions: Place chicken in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Season with salt and pepper.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours.
Remove chicken and let cool.
Leave juices in pan.
Shred cooked chicken into bite-sized pieces.
Break tortillas into small pieces and mix 1/2 with chicken juices in pan.
Mix soups, picante sauce, milk and onion together.

title: chili beans
directions: Put all ingredients in pot.
Cook slowly on top of stove until beans are soft.

title: deelishus dip-in-bread
directions: Cut top crust off about 1/4 of the way down the loaf.
Mix balance of ingredients together with mixer.
Put mixture in the bread; put the top on; wrap well in foil.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Honestly, this doesn't burn or dry out.
It's amazing!

title: julie's potato salad
directions: Wash and cut potatoes leaving skin on them. Cook just until tender.
Drain well, let cool. Add eggs and pickles, mustard and mayonnaise. Mix well. Pour into glass bowl.
Decorate with sliced green olives and chives.

title: chicken noodle casserole
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients with a sauce made of the remaining ingredients. Melt oleo. Add flour. Stir until dissolved. Add other ingredients. Cook until thickened. Mix with chicken mixture and put in casserole dish to reheat later or serve as is. Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Add dry jello to cream cheese and mix. Thaw and mash strawberries; drain juice and if necessary, add water to make one cup liquid.
(Set aside mashed strawberries.)
Bring juice to a full boil.
Add cream cheese and jello mixture, stirring until it is dissolved good.
Add mashed strawberries, pecans and marshmallows.
Mix well and then gently fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into tube pan.
Refrigerate for 2 hours or until firm.

title: chocolate peanut butter no bake cookies
directions: On stove top in large saucepan, add sugar, milk, butter and cocoa.
Bring to boil.
Boil for 1 minute.
Take off burner, then add peanut butter and oatmeal.
Drop onto wax paper by tablespoon; let cool.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: caramel dip
directions: Mix with electric mixer.
Use as a dip for apple or pear halves.

title: no sugar bars
directions: Boil dates, raisins and prunes in together in water for 5 minutes.
Add butter or oleo; set aside.
In a bowl, mix eggs, soda, vanilla, salt, flour and chopped nuts.
Add fruit mixture to batter.
Add cinnamon, nutmeg or cloves, if desired.
Bake in a 7 x 11-inch pan at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool and cut.

title: chocabutter pies
directions: Heat milk; add egg yolks (beaten).
Combine flour with sugar and cocoa.
Cook until thick.
Cool.
Add vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shells.
Cool until okay to spread melted peanut butter over.
Melt some good quality semi-sweet chocolate pieces with margarine and spread over peanut butter.

title: chili con carne
directions: Melt the butter in a 2-quart glass casserole dish.
Add ground beef and onion.
Cook with microwave 4 to 5 minutes, stirring several times.
Cook until all pink has left the meat and chopped onion is limp.
Add flour and stir well to combine.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook for 25 minutes, stirring occasionally. Recipe yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: cranberry pie
directions: Mix all up together.
Put half on the bottom of a 9 x 10-inch baking dish.
Pour a can of cranberries over the mixture and spread.
Put other half of mixture over cranberries.
Cook until brown at 350°.

title: pumpkin dessert
directions: This is great and believe it or not, the very best flavor is butterscotch.

title: barbecued pork chops
directions: Brown chops and place in a casserole.
Mix together water, ketchup, onions, vinegar, Worcestershire sauce, brown sugar and seasoning and pour over chops.
Bake in oven at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: apple brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Mix flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon in a large bowl.
Whisk oil and eggs in another large bowl.
Stir in sugar and vanilla.
Stir in flour mixture.
Then add apples, nuts and raisins.
Mixture will be very stiff.
Spread into pan.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes until top is golden and a toothpick inserted comes out clean.
Cool completely on wire rack.
Cut into 40 squares.

title: country casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in a large roaster.
Cover ingredients with water.
Lay a few bacon strips across the top. Cook at 325° for 1 hour or until done.

title: kahlua dip
directions: Mix together above ingredients.
Serve with fresh pineapple chunks, fresh strawberries, apple slices (sliced thin) and pear slices (sliced thin).

title: david's favorite cookies
directions: Cream oleo
and sugar.	Add eggs.
Mix.
Add dry ingredients and
milk.	Drop
by
teaspoonfuls	on
greased
cookie sheet. Bake 10 minutes at 325° to 350° until lightly browned. You can add walnuts and pecan pieces or even ice cookies after baking and cooled.

title: cheese straws
directions: Mix thoroughly and put through cookie press.
Bake at 375° until done.

title: wagon wheel cookies
directions: Melt together butter or margarine and unsweetened chocolate. Blend sugar into eggs.
Add dry ingredients to egg, sugar and vanilla mixture.
Pour in melted butter and chocolate.
Mix all together and add chopped walnuts or pecans at this time.
May need to add more flour if mixture is too runny.
Want it somewhat stiff, but too much flour will make cookies dry.
Chill overnight, covered.
Roll in balls and roll in powdered sugar before baking.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
(I usually double this recipe when I make it.)

title: low-fat chili
directions: Brown meat with chopped onion, breaking up the meat as it browns.
Pour off any grease.
Add chili mix.
Add tomatoes and tomato puree.
Simmer on low heat about 1 hour.
You can add beans or serve over spaghetti.

title: raisin filled cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add beaten eggs, vanilla, salt, milk and flour, sifted with baking powder.
Knead dough.

title: double good yeast rolls
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients with the flour; mix in a bowl. Mix 2 minutes on low speed of electric mixer; set aside.
Combine flour mixture with the remaining ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Mix 3 minutes with a heavy-duty electric mixer at medium speed.
Mix 3 minutes at medium speed.
Cover; let rise in a warm place (85°), free from drafts, about 3 hours, or until the dough has doubled in bulk.
Punch dough down.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Melt first 4 ingredients.
Bring to a boil for 3 minutes. Remove from heat.
Add last 2 ingredients.
Spoon on wax paper. Let stand and refrigerate.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Saute onion, celery and carrot in margarine.
Cook until soft. Add broccoli and cook 15 minutes.
Stir in flour.
Add chicken broth and seasonings.
Mix together.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Add milk and heat to serving temperature.

title: partridge in cheese sauce
directions: Roll breast in flour seasoned with salt and pepper.
Brown in frying pan with bacon grease.
Put browned breasts in casserole dish.
Mix soup and milk; pour over meat and crumble bacon over it.
Bake covered at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Uncover and bake until cheese browns.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix with electric blender until smooth.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour (test for doneness).

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Salt and pepper chicken and cook in crock-pot all day on low. Bone out chicken and pour broth in saucepan.
Mix soup with broth. Cut up tortillas and cook in broth mixture until done.
Add chicken.

title: pepper steak
directions: Boil steak 3 to 4 hours or until tender enough to easily break apart.
Shred and place meat in skillet or crock-pot.
Add salt, pepper, onion, green pepper, sugar and Worcestershire sauce to taste.
Stir in tomato sauce (approximately 16 ounces per 2 pounds of shredded meat).
Simmer for approximately 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Serve with rice.

title: quick biscuits
directions: Mix together all ingredients and drop by spoonfuls onto a cookie sheet. Or, extra flour may be worked into the dough, rolled out and cut. Bake at 450°f 230°c. gas mark 8 until golden brown.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Sift together 3 cups flour and salt.
Add shortening and mix until crumbly.
Add egg, water and vinegar.
Stir well.
Form 3 balls.
Chill or may use immediately.
The food processor is great for mixing.

title: sour cream substitute
directions: Combine all ingredients; beat in blender until smooth.
Chill for at least 4 hours.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Cut in Crisco and add yeast and buttermilk.
Mix well.
Turn out on floured board, roll to 1/4-inch thickness, let raise.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: fried chicken
directions: Mix eggs and Italian dressing in medium bowl.
Mix flour, sage, garlic, salt and pepper in large bowl.
Skin chicken; dip in medium bowl, then dip in large bowl.
Place in heated oil over medium heat; brown on both sides to desired crispiness.
Place in baking pan; bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: beefy cheese pie
directions: Brown chuck; drain.
Add onion, next 4 ingredients and pepper; set aside.
Unroll 1 package rolls.
Place the 4 sections of dough together, forming a 12 x 6-inch rectangle.
Seal edges and perforations together.
Roll to 12-inch square.
Fit into a 9-inch pie plate; trim.
Separate one of the eggs; set yolk aside.
Beat egg white with 2 remaining eggs.
Spread half over dough.
Spoon meat mixture into shell and arrange cheese slices atop; spread remaining egg mixture over cheese.
Mix reserved yolk and 1 tablespoon water; brush lightly on edge of pastry.
Reserve remaining egg mixture.
Roll second package of rolls to 12-inch square as before, placing atop filling.
Trim, seal and flute edge; cut slits for escape of steam.
Brush top with remaining egg yolk mixture.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
If pastry gets too brown, cover with foil.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving. Serves 6.

title: spaghetti
directions: Brown ground beef.
Pour off grease.
Place beef and remaining ingredients in a large stock pot.
Simmer 2 to 3 hours or until onion becomes tender. Serve over spaghetti noodles with garlic bread.

title: no peek casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 2 qt. casserole dish.
Cover and bake at 300° for 3 hours.
Don't peek!
Serve over wheat noodles, low-carb noodles or brown rice.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: corn 'n cabbage
directions: Fry bacon until crisp and brown; remove bacon.
Add water and sugar to bacon drippings.
Bring to boil; add cabbage and corn and cover.
Cook until just tender, about 7 minutes.
Spoon into serving dish; sprinkle with paprika.
Garnish with crisp bacon.

title: coke salad
directions: Boil first four ingredients.
Add next three ingredients.
Mix well.
Place in refrigerator until set.

title: hamburg tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in skillet; drain fat.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add beans, tomatoes and tomato sauce.
Pour into 2-quart casserole or 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Slice cheese and layer on top.
Layer Tater Tots on top of cheese slices.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: ann's muffins
directions: READ RECIPE BEFORE MAKING.
Mix glaze:
Lemons, oranges, and powdered sugar and put in refrigerator overnight.
Next day make muffins according to box directions.
Cook in small muffin pans. Dip muffins in glaze while hot.
Place on dish.
Get a cup of coffee, sit down, and enjoy them.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Spray pan with Pam after you have placed wax paper on bottom of pan. Mix pecans and coconut together and place in bottom of pan. Mix German chocolate cake mix according to directions and pour over pecan mixture. Cream together margarine, cream cheese and powdered sugar. Spoon over cake mix. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until firm. Cool completely before turning out.

title: sweet and sour hot dogs
directions: Put all in crock-pot and let cook on low for about 6 hours.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix together first 7 ingredients.
Pour into a 10 x 10-inch pan.
Add stuffing and butter.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: grits-n-cheese bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour boiling water over grits.
Stir until blended.
Fold in Cheddar and Parmesan cheeses.
Add beaten eggs and chives.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake 40 minute or until knife inserted into center comes out clean.

title: lazy cook tamales(an original recipe)
directions: Stew the chicken until tender.
Remove meat from bones; cut into bite size pieces and set aside.
(You will need a quart and half of chicken broth.)

Pour the fat with broth into a 2-cup measure and reserve (this should be about half or less fat). Simmer together for 20 minutes or more 2 cups chicken broth, the tomato puree, 1 1/2 cups broth or juice and the seasonings.
After simmering period, mix together the flour with enough broth to make a smooth paste.
Stir into sauce, stirring constantly, until sauce is smooth and slightly thick.
Remove from heat.

title: tortilla wraps
directions: Blend cream cheese and chiles.
Spread evenly over tortillas. Spread layer of salsa evenly over cream cheese mixture.
Sprinkle cheese over all.
Roll tortilla up like a jelly roll.
Refrigerate a few hours to overnight.
Slice into 1/2-inch pieces and serve.

title: corn-rice casserole
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in butter until tender.
Combine with cooked rice, jalapeno pepper, corn, cheese and sugar.
Spoon in lightly greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: currant biscuits(english tea biscuits)
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drop by tablespoon on cookie sheet; flatten with bottom of a glass.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and water in 3-quart pan.
Cook and stir to 230°.
Add margarine.
Stir frequently.
When temperature reaches 280°, add nuts.
Stir constantly to 305°.
Remove from heat.
Stir in soda quickly and pour on greased cookie sheet. Cool and crack.

title: nacho dip
directions: Heat all until well blended and hot.
Serve hot.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Dissolve sugar in hot water.
Add remaining ingredients, except ginger ale.
Cover and refrigerate until ready to serve. To serve, pour mixture over ice into a punch bowl and add 2 quarts of ginger ale.
Serves 40.

title: chicken-bacon egg rolls
directions: Cook bacon until almost done.
Drain off fat.
Add pecans to wok or skillet; continue cooking bacon and pecans until bacon is crisp and pecans are toasted. Drain and cook slightly.
Chop bacon and pecans. In bowl combine chicken, celery, bacon and pecans. Add sour cream and salt; mix
well.
Fill egg roll skins with tablespoon of filling.
Fold and roll.
Heat in at least 2 inches of oil for 2 to 3 minutes until golden brown.
Drain on paper towel and serve warm.

title: calico pickles
directions: Combine vegetables in a large bowl.
Dissolve salt in water and pour over vegetables.
Soak for 15 to 18 hours in cool place. Drain.
In a large kettle, mix sugar, spices and vinegar.
Bring to a boil and boil for 3 to 4 minutes.
Add vegetables and simmer 5 to 7 minutes.
Pack hot into 8 hot pint jars, leaving 1/4-inch headspace.
Remove air bubbles.
Adjust caps; process 15 minutes in boiling water bath.
Yield:
8 pints.
Very good and pretty to give as gifts.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil chicken; take off bone.
Reserve 1 cup broth; mix with flour for dumplings.
Roll out; cut dumplings.
Add to chicken; cook for about 10 minutes.
Turn off heat; let stand for another 10 minutes.

title: antipasto
directions: Rinse frozen veggies under cold water and drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Store in refrigerator 24 hours. Serve with good bread and fresh ground pepper.
Easy and delicious.
Can add or delete any ingredient, except marinades and sauce.

title: weight watchers mandarin orange salad
directions: Mix dry jello into Cool Whip.
Add cottage cheese and drained oranges (do not use juice).
Chill until set.
Use as salad or dessert.
I always doubled recipe as my family loves it.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls flat on baking sheet.
Bake according to directions on package.
Cool completely.
Mix together softened cream cheese and Ranch dressing.
Spread mixture over cooled pastry.
Sprinkle with chopped vegetables.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Cook 2 to 3 hours; remove meat, potatoes and celery and press out all juices into stock.

title: cucumber relish
directions: Soak the cucumbers and onions overnight in the salt and cold water. Drain.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Boil the chicken until done; debone. Crush Doritos and place in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Pour 1 cup chicken broth over chips. Shred chicken; cover chips. Shred cheese.
Layer half over the chicken.
Put remaining ingredients into blender. Blend until it makes a smooth sauce.
Pour over layer of cheese.
Put remaining cheese on top.
Place in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: smoked turkey grab 'n go
directions: Place tortillas on plate and microwave on High for 10 to 15 seconds or wrap tortillas in aluminum foil and warm for 10 to 15 minutes in 350° oven.

title: strawberry-spinach salad
directions: Rinse spinach leaves thoroughly; tear into bite size pieces. Drain on paper towels.
Hull and rinse strawberries.
Cut in half or leave whole, depending on size.
Drain on paper towels.
In container of electric blender, combine onion, vinegar, oil, honey and Worcestershire sauce; blend until smooth.
Stir in sesame seed and poppy seed.
In a large salad bowl, combine spinach and strawberries.
Toss with dressing.
Serve immediately (the salad will wilt after a few hours in the refrigerator.)
Yield:
10 servings.

title: apple pie
directions: Combine all dry ingredients and gently mix with the apples to which the orange juice has been added.
Line a pie plate with crust.
Add the apples and dot with butter.
Adjust top crust, fluting the edge.
Sprinkle the top with sugar.

title: duchess potatoes
directions: Beat potatoes and butter with electric mixer until smooth. Using large spoon, form mounds and place on greased cookie sheet or ovenproof flat plate.
Drizzle with melted butter and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake in preheated 450° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: saltine supremes
directions: Line cookie sheet with aluminum foil.
Cover with saltines. Combine sugar and butter in saucepan.
Bring to boil and boil for 2 minutes.
Pour over crackers.
Bake at 400° for 4 minutes. Remove from oven and sprinkle chocolate chips over all.
As chips melt, spread evenly.
Sprinkle Bits 'O Brickle over chocolate. Refrigerate 1 hour.
Cut into squares.

title: pie shells
directions: Add 3 to 4 tablespoons of cold milk or just enough to stick dough together for rolling out consistency.
Roll out on floured waxed paper until crust is about 1/2 to 3/4 inch larger than pie pan.
Turn pan over crust; flip over.
Peel off paper.
Turn under edge to be even with pie pan.
Fill in any holes.
Flute with fingers.

title: brown fig pie
directions: Slice figs into crust. Mix sugar and gelatin and pour over figs. Place pats of butter around top of pie and sprinkle vanilla over top. Mix the 3 tablespoons of butter and flour together to make a crumbly mixture, sprinkle on top. Bake in a 350° oven until golden brown.

title: pepper jelly (hot)
directions: Bring sugar and vinegar to
a boil.
Add peppers; cook 2 minutes.
Add Certo and put in prepared jars.

title: mayonnaise biscuits
directions: Combine and mix ingredients.
Drop into greased muffin pan. Bake at approximately 325° or 350° until brown.

title: curry dip
directions: Mix either by hand or in blender.
Serve with zucchini squash slices, cucumber, celery, carrots or crackers.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar thoroughly; add eggs, pumpkin and water.
Sift together flour, baking powder, soda, salt and spices; add to pumpkin mixture.
Stir in nuts, raisins and dates.
Pour into two 2-quart loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Three (1 pound) coffee cans may be used for baking.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cut peppers in halves lengthwise; seed, wash and drain. Combine remaining ingredients; use to stuff pepper cases.
Place in shallow greased pan and add water to depth of 1 inch.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 1 hour.

title: great american meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients in a shallow baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Let stand for 5 minutes before cutting.

title: japanese fruit cake
directions: Dust raisins and nuts with flour.
Bake in 3 cake pans at 300° until cake leaves side of pans.

title: lemon chicken
directions: In skillet, cook chicken, onion, carrot and garlic in butter until chicken is lightly browned, about 5 minutes.
In a bowl, combine cornstarch and chicken broth; stir in lemon juice, peel, salt and rice.
Add to skillet and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; add broccoli.
Cover and simmer 5 to 10 minutes or until rice is tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: quick-to-make no bake lemonade pie
directions: Blend Cool Whip, lemonade, milk and juice.
Spoon into pie crust.
Chill.
Keeps up to 1 week in refrigerator.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream margarine.
Gradually add sugar, beating until mixture is fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Sift flour, soda and salt and mix well.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with sour cream, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Stir in coconut and flavoring.

title: homemade biscuits
directions: Mix well.
Place in baking pan with large spoon.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: brandied fruit starter
directions: To make starter:
Drain and slice 2 cups canned peaches.
Add 2 cups sugar; stir well.
Place in a glass container that does not have a tight fitting lid (an apothecary jar is ideal).
Stir this mixture once every day for two weeks.
It will begin to froth or work.
Now you have a starter and can begin to add additional fruits:
peaches, pineapple and maraschino cherries.
(Do not use pears or bananas.)
Add to your mixture every two weeks one cup drained, sliced canned fruit and one cup sugar each time.
After the new fruit and sugar, marinate a couple of days.
The mixture is ready again.
Never let the mixture get lower than one cup in quantity or you will need to start over.
The mixture should never be refrigerated.
It will stop the "brandying" process.
You can go a month or two before adding more fruit.
It may be more potent, but the mixture never spoils.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Boil broccoli 5 minutes; drain.
Mix broccoli and remaining ingredients.
Top with crushed Ritz crackers.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: okra gumbo
directions: In heavy skillet, place oil, okra, onions, salt and pepper; lightly brown.
Add tomatoes with juice, tomato sauce, bay leaf and Cajun seasoning.
Cover and simmer about 35 minutes.
Add water as needed.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Serve over hot rice.

title: chicken breasts in sour cream with mushrooms
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish, arrange dried beef slices on bottom.
Put one piece of chicken breast on each slice and top with half strip of bacon.

title: crab cheese buns
directions: Heat cheese and margarine until melted in microwave; stir until mixed.
Mix in crab meat and add dash of garlic (if desired) and dash of salt.
Spread mixture on muffin and place under broiler.
Broil 4 to 5 minutes until brown and bubbly.
Serve as light snack or as a meal with a tossed salad or cole slaw and fresh fruit!

title: apple crisp
directions: Peel, core and slice apples.
Place in an ungreased pan. Cover with 1 cup water.
Combine cake mix, brown sugar and cinnamon.
It will be crumbly.
Cover apples with crumb mixture and bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Mix margarine, oil and eggs well.
Add to dry ingredients. Add zucchini.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle chips over all.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 to 3/4 hour, or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: three layer cookies
directions: Blend and press mixture into a 10 x 15 inch pan.

title: vanilla wafers cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs and beat well.
Add wafers, coconut and nuts.
Bake in tube pan for 1 1/2 hours in 300° oven.

title: colonial pumpkin pie
directions: Combine pumpkin, sugar, salt, spices and molasses; mix.
Add eggs and milk; mix thoroughly.
Pour mixture onto unbaked pie shell.
Bake in hot oven (425°) 45 minutes to 1 hour or until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: peppers ole
directions: Microwave Directions:
Place peppers and water in ungreased 9 x 13-inch microwave-safe dish (or divide peppers and water between two 8-inch microwave-safe dishes).
Cover; microwave on High for 2 minutes and drain.
In medium bowl, combine rice, cheese, sour cream, beans and corn mixture.
Spoon heaping 1/2 cup of filling into each pepper half.
Cover and microwave in 9 x 13-inch dish on High for 15 to 16 minutes or until peppers are tender.
(Microwave each 8-inch dish for 6 to 8 minutes.)
Top each pepper with a tablespoon of salsa, a tortilla chip and cilantro.
Makes 8 servings.

title: mom's pancakes
directions: Blend egg yolks, buttermilk and flour with a fork.
Then add baking soda, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Melt margarine; add to mixture.
Whip egg whites until stiff; fold into mixture. Serves 8.

title: beet jelly
directions: Boil beets and water until soft; drain.
Keep 3 1/2 cups of juice.
Boil all ingredients; add sugar.
Boil for 2 minutes until jellied.
Put into jelly jars.
Seal.

title: karo nut pie
directions: Beat eggs well.
Gradually add sugar and beat remaining ingredients.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes and reduce heat to 325° for 25 minutes.

title: quick turtles
directions: Arrange pecans in clusters 2-inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Top each cluster with one caramel, slightly flattened. Bake at 300° for 7 minutes or until caramel softens.
Remove to wax paper.
Flatten caramel with spatula.
Top each with 1 chocolate Kiss while still warm.
Spread when melted.
Refrigerate until chocolate hardens.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease 9-inch pie pan.
Combine all ingredients and beat for 2 minutes with mixer.
Pour into pie pan and bake for 50 minutes or until center is puffed up.
Serves 8; contains 112 calories per slice.

title: sue's devil's food yummy
directions: Bake cake by directions on box in oblong baking pan.
Cool and split lengthwise.
Place 1/2 of cake in serving dish.

title: apple-carrot salad
directions: Mix all together in large serving dish.
Use just enough mayonnaise to lightly coat the ingredients.

title: nut meat balls
directions: Cook millet 4 parts water to 1 part millet.
Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Roll into small balls.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake on cookie sheet for 30 minutes at 325°.
Serve with tomato sauce.

title: chocolate mousse
directions: Crust:
Cut together flour, chopped walnuts and oleo.
Press into 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients, except nuts and dried beef, together.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix and form in small balls and set aside for a few hours to become firm.
Melt chocolate and paraffin in double boiler; keep over low heat while dipping balls, otherwise mixture will harden too much.
A very good Christmas cookie.

title: sweet and sour dressing
directions: Mix together until thick, about 10 minutes. Keeps well in refrigerator.

title: sourdough pancakes
directions: Mix the night before first 3 ingredients.
In the morning take out 1 cup of starter from the mixture and replace in refrigerator. Then add next 5 ingredients.
Lastly, boil water and add baking soda to boiling water.
Add that mixture to pancake batter. Guaranteed the best ever!

title: broiled crab english muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients and spread over toasted English muffins. Cut muffins in fourths and broil low for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: banana split
directions: I use a 10 x 13-inch glass baking dish.

title: sugar shapes
directions: Beat together all ingredients, except flour.
Add flour.
Mix and wrap in wax paper.
Chill for 2 hours.
Roll to 1/4-inch and cut with cookie cutter.
Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: golden layer cake
directions: Cream together sugar, oil and vanilla.
Add eggs 1 at a time. Beat after each.
Add flour alternately with milk.
Bake at 350° approximately 20 minutes.

title: kahlua
directions: Mix well the sugar, instant coffee and boiling water.
Let cool.
Add vodka and vanilla bean.
Ferment at least 2 weeks. Makes 2 liters.

title: blueberry delight
directions: In 9 x 13-inch pan, dump blueberry filling.
Then pour on the pineapple.
Top with dry cake mix and make furrows in the mix. Melt margarine and pour into furrows.
Bake at 375° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: delicious potato casserole
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until thoroughly heated. May sprinkle with paprika, if desired.

title: munch cookies
directions: Heat Karo and brown sugar on stove.
Stir to dissolve sugar, but do not let it bubble.
Remove from stove and add peanut butter, stirring to mix well.
Pour over Special K cereal and mix well. Butter a 9 x 12-inch pan.
With hands buttered also, pat mixture into pan.

title: sinfully delicious pink fluff
directions: Mix cream cheese and sugar until creamy. Beat in 1 tub Cool Whip. Pour over cooled crust and smooth evenly. Drain 1 package thawed frozen strawberries and put on top of mixture. Smooth another 8-ounce container of Cool Whip over top.

title: marinated tomatoes
directions: At least 4 hours before serving, arrange tomatoes and cheese in a dish.
With a wire whisk, whisk the other ingredients and spoon over.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: salt and pepper steak
directions: Cut steak into thin strips; roll in flour.
In a skillet, heat oil and fry meat, onion, green pepper, salt and pepper until brown.
Add water and soy sauce.
Cover and simmer until tender. Serve over cooked rice.

title: dilly bread
directions: Soften yeast in water.
Add the rest of the ingredients down to flour.
Mix slightly.
Add flour to form a soft dough, beating well after each addition using low speed on mixer.
Scrape mixer beaters with knife.
Cover dough with warm damp cloth and let rise in warm place (80° to 90°) for 50 to 60 minutes.
Stir down dough; turn into well-greased casserole.
Let rise in warm place until light (30 to 40 minutes).
Recipe may be divided with spoon to make 2 small loaves in meat loaf size pans.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes at 350°.
When done, brush with butter; remove from pans and salt lightly on top.

title: sweet-sour dressing
directions: (You can buy red vinegar with garlic and rice vinegar, seasoned.)

title: cherokee bean bread
directions: In a large bowl, mix cornmeal, baking powder and salt.
Stir in milk, eggs, beans and bean liquid.
(If canned beans are used, increase the milk 1 cup and omit the bean liquid.)
Preheat oven to 450°. Place bacon drippings or vegetable shortening in a 10-inch cast iron skillet or a 9-inch pan. Put in oven while preheating.
Spoon batter into skillet. Bake for 20 minutes or until done and lightly browned. Makes 9 to 15 servings.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Combine jello and boiling water.
Cool until lukewarm.
Using an electric mixer, blend in softened cream cheese.
Add Cool Whip and blend with a spoon.
Finally, add drained pineapple.
Pour salad into mold and close the cover.
Keep it in the refrigerator overnight.
To unmold, leave it on the counter for 15 minutes, then place in water for 20 seconds.
Take cover off and invert on a plate.

title: hamburg steaks
directions: Mix beef, crumbs, milk and seasonings.
Heat shortening in frying pan.
Add meat mixture by tablespoonfuls and flatten into thin cakes.
Cook cakes until golden brown, turning once.
Remove and keep hot in oven or over low heat.

title: hot crab philly spread
directions: Blend all ingredients together well.
Spoon into ovenproof dish.
Sprinkle with 1/3 cup toasted, sliced almonds.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Serve hot with crackers or party bread.

title: easy red beans & rice
directions: Cook sausage over low heat 5 - 8 minutes. Add onion, green pepper, and garlic; cook until tender. Drain, if necessary. Add beans, tomatoes, and seasonings. Simmer uncovered 20 minutes. Serve over rice.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients
together;
form mixture into a ball and refrigerate for at
least
an
hour before rolling in nuts.

title: quick french dressing
directions: Mix well in blender or jar.
Chill.

title: krazy cake
directions: Mix well. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: oven-baked spaghetti(serves 4)
directions: Grease ovenproof dish. Place spaghetti in dish. Pour tomatoes over. Add onions. Sprinkle with oregano and season well. Slice the cheese finely and arrange over top of dish. Mix well. Sprinkle with Parmesan and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: hot potato(microwave)
directions: Peel potatoes and slice thinly into a 2-quart baking dish. Add salt water.
Cover.
Cook on High for 18 minutes, stirring every 5 minutes.
Drain.

title: diabetic peach cobbler
directions: Mix Equal, cornstarch and lemon juice with juice from peaches. Put pastry crust in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put in peaches.
Pour mixture over peaches and dot with butter.
Put on other crust and cut slits for air.
Bake at 350°.

title: paradise dessert pizza
directions: Assemble ingredients prior to recipe preparation.

title: cinnamon bread(sticky buns)
directions: Spread evenly over bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan the raisins and nuts.
Cut bread into 1-inch cubes; layer on top of nuts and raisins.
Melt butter, brown sugar, pudding, cinnamon and milk in saucepan until very hot (not boiling).
Pour over bread evenly. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
In the morning, bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
When done, invert pan and remove buns.

title: bar-b-cups
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain fat.
Season with salt and pepper. Add barbecue sauce.
Grease muffin pans; line with canned biscuits.
Spoon meat into cups.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: cheese and ham balls
directions: Mix all ingredients, except pecans.
Mix well.
Chill; shape into two balls.
Coat with pecans.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Serve with crackers or chips.
Makes 2 balls.

title: creamed green beans
directions: Cook green beans following label directions.
Soften cream cheese.
Add other ingredients.
Add to beans and heat.
Serves 4.

title: ginger cake
directions: Cream margarine; gradually add 2/3 cup sugar, beating at medium speed until lightly fluffy.
Add molasses and egg; beat well.
Combine flour, baking soda, ginger, cinnamon and mace. Gradually add to creamed mixture; stir well.
Divide dough in half. Wrap each portion in plastic wrap; freeze for 30 minutes.

title: cheese rolls
directions: Let cheese set out at room temperature for a while so it will mix better.
Cut both cheeses into chunks in mixing bowl.
May need to add just a little milk to mix.
Use mixer to mix, adding garlic powder to taste.
Will taste a little stronger after it sets.
Roll a little at a time into small logs.
Put paprika on foil and roll log through it.
Put on plate or individually wrap.
Eat with Ritz crackers.
(May need to refrigerate before rolling into logs.)

title: omelet
directions: Combine eggs and milk or half and half. Salt and pepper.
Beat slightly.
Melt butter in heavy 10-inch frypan with sloping sides or omelet pan over direct heat. Add egg mixture. Cook over very low heat until set, but top is still shiny.
To speed cooking, run a spatula around edges of pan during cooking; lift omelet and let egg mixture flow below omelet.
Fold omelet in half. Turn or roll out of pan onto warm platter. Serve at once.
Yields 4 servings.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Mix thoroughly the sugar, flour, cocoa and salt.
Add milk, beaten egg yolks and margarine.
Cook, stirring constantly, for 8 to 10 minutes, or until thick.
Add vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell; cover with meringue.

title: deviled clams
directions: Add all ingredients together. Squeeze mixture with hands. Fill clam shells.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs. Fry in hot fat until brown.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburger and onions until done.
Drain grease.
Place hamburger meat and onions into crock-pot.
Add drained tomatoes and kidney beans; mix well.
Then add salt, chili powder, ketchup, tomato sauce and bay leaf.
Mix well and cook on low for 10 to 12 hours.

title: a little taste of heaven
directions: Follow recipe on box adding 1/2 cup coconut.
Bake in two (9-inch) cake pans.
Cool cake.

title: breakfast puffs
directions: Mix together Crisco, sugar, and egg. Sift together dry ingredients. Add flour mixture alternately with milk to cream mixture. Fill cupcake papers 2/3 full in cupcake pan & bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Remove from papers and roll in melted oleo & cinnamon & sugar.

title: brownie strawberry delight
directions: Layer bowl or 9 x 13-inch pan with pieces of brownies.
Add layer of pieces of strawberries.
Top with Cool Whip if needed. Repeat layers again.

title: crab meat mold
directions: In a double boiler, mix cream cheese, soup and mayonnaise. Blend until smooth.
Add celery and onion.
Blend the 2 packages of gelatine with 1/4 cup cold water.
Add to double boiler mixture.
Remove from heat.
Fold in crabmeat.
Pour into oiled mold.
Allow to set 3 hours or overnight before unmolding.
Serves 12.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Fry bacon; saute onion, celery and green pepper. Add all remaining ingredients, except shrimp and cook 30 minutes or so. Add shrimp that have been cleaned and shelled. If shrimp are raw, let cook for about 10 minutes; if shrimp are precooked, let cook for about 5 minutes or just until shrimp are hot. Serve over white rice. Serves 6.

title: martha washington balls
directions: Pour sugar in a large bowl; cream margarine in sugar then pour Eagle Brand milk into mixture and blend well.
Add coconut and pecans.
Shape into one inch balls.

title: souper cheezy potato wedges
directions: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees. Melt butter in large skillet.
Combine flour with the Greek seasoning and stir to mix. Add to the butter and stir until blended.
Gradually add the milk, stirring constantly until mixture begins to thicken.
Remove from heat and stir in dip, soup, and cheese.
Stir until cheese melts. Pour the potato wedges in a 9x13x2 inch baking pan. Pour the cheese sauce over the potatoes.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until potatoes are fork tender.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with paprika, if desired.
Serve warm.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix. Put in casserole dish.
Top with 1 1/2 cups cracker crumbs soaked in 1 stick melted oleo.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: beans-beef-bacon casserole
directions: Cut bacon into 1-inch pieces and brown with beef and onion. Drain off the grease.
Drain the 3 cans of beans.
Combine the beans along with rest of ingredients listed.
Stir above into beef-bacon-onion mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: heavenly chocolate ice cream
directions: Combine candy and Eagle Brand milk.
Heat until candy melts. Cool, stirring occasionally.
Add 1 quart milk; beat until blended.
Pour into freezer.
Add chocolate syrup; add milk to fill.
Freeze.

title: walnut chicken
directions: Mix 1 tablespoon oil, 2 teaspoons soy sauce and 1 teaspoon cornstarch in small bowl.
Stir in chicken to coat.
Cover and refrigerate 30 minutes.

title: chinese meat balls
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Roll into 1-inch meat balls.
Bake uncovered on roasting rack in slow oven (275°) for 1 hour.
Makes 50 meat balls.

title: chocolate raspberry cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, sift 1 cup powdered sugar, flour and cocoa.
Beat egg whites at medium speed until foamy, then at high speed beat in salt and cream of tartar.
Then gradually add sugar and beat until stiff.
Fold in extracts and then flour mixture, 1/3 at a time, until blended.
Spoon into a tube pan.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until cake springs back. Invert cake in pan on funnel until well cooled.

title: quacker jacks
directions: A heaping c. of happiness,

title: italian quiche
directions: Put pepperoni, Mozzarella cheese and Swiss cheese in pie shell.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add eggs, milk and butter.
Beat at medium speed until mixed well.
Add nuts and coconut.
Bake in unbaked pie shells at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until centers are completely cooked.
This will also freeze well.

title: lemon delight
directions: Line spring-form pan with ladyfingers.
Beat egg yolks with milk and lemon juice.
Beat egg whites until stiff in glass or ceramic bowl (not plastic).
Thoroughly wash bowl, beaters and hands to remove any trace of grease before beating whites with the cream of tartar.
Fold beaten whites into the milk-yolk mixture. Put into pan lined with ladyfingers.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: lois' rhubarb nut bread
directions: Mix brown sugar, oil, eggs, milk and vanilla.
Sift together flour, salt and soda.
Add to the first ingredients.
Add rhubarb and nuts.
Mix well.
Pour into 3 well-greased bread pans.
Mix together 1 cup sugar and 2 tablespoons butter and sprinkle over loaves and bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: almond joy cake
directions: Cook cake according to directions on box for 9 x 12-inch cake. Ten minutes before cake is done, mix and melt together milk, coconut, sugar and marshmallows.
Let mixture cool and pour over hot cake.

title: cheesecake squares
directions: Use microwave to soften cream cheese first.
Mix cream cheese, slightly beaten egg yolk, vanilla, and 3/4 c. sugar. Spread 1 can of crescent rolls over the bottom of a 9 x 13 pan. Pour the cheese mixture over this.
Then top the mixture with the other can of crescent rolls.
Use the egg white to baste the top of the pastry.
Then sprinkle the remaining 1/2 c. sugar over this.
Bake at the temperature directed on the crescent roll can for 18-23 minutes or until pastry is done and egg white is absorbed and shiny.
Cut into squares.
Good warm or after they have been chilled.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour into greased 2-quart baking dish.

title: easy german chocolate cake
directions: Grease sheet cake pan.
Layer with mixture of coconut and pecans.
Mix cake mix as directed on box and pour on top of coconut and pecans.
Melt margarine and cream cheese.
Add powdered sugar.
Mix well.
Pour on top of cake batter.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until done.

title: smoke oyster dip
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients, mixing well.
Stir in olives and oysters.
Refrigerate.
Yield: 2 cups.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix together and pour over chicken.
Mix 1 cup self-rising flour, 1 cup milk and 3/4 cup melted butter.
Pour this on top. (This makes crust.)
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except potato chips.
Top with chips. Bake at 350° in 2-quart casserole for 30 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: cinnamon fruit medley(great salad for christmas)
directions: Combine candy, vinegar and salt in a small saucepan.
Cook over low heat until candies are dissolved, stirring constantly.

title: gazpacho
directions: If you use the blender to chop the vegetables, cover them with a small amount of water before the blending.
Drain them well before mixing with remaining ingredients.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix crumbs and 1 stick of oleo, melted.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat powdered sugar, 1 stick oleo, eggs and vanilla for 10 to 15 minutes until creamy.
Spread on top of crust, then add a layer of bananas (2 1/2), 1/2 of pineapple and 1/2 of Cool Whip.
Repeat layers:
bananas, pineapple and Cool Whip.
Garnish by sprinkling nuts on top of Cool Whip and adding a few chopped cherries for color.
Refrigerate overnight or until firm, about 2 hours.

title: cocktail sausage balls
directions: Mix ingredients together, then form into 1-inch balls.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: simple sausage balls
directions: Grate cheese and mix with sausage and Bisquick mix. Roll in balls and bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Can be frozen and used as a snack for lunch boxes.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: cider syrup
directions: Mix all ingredients, except butter, in medium saucepan.
Boil for 1 minute.
Blend in butter.
Serve warm over pancakes, waffles or French toast.
Great for company.

title: tutti-frutti ice cream
directions: Combine sweetened condensed milk, lemon juice, sugar and fruit; blend well.
Add 3 cups milk and water.
Pour mixture into freezer can of a 1-gallon hand-turned or electric freezer.
Freeze according to manufacturer's instructions.
Allow ice cream to ripen at least 1 hour.
Yields 2 quarts.

title: herb's curry chicken stir-fry
directions: Cut chicken into 1-inch cubes.
Mix curry powder with boiling water.
Marinate cubes in water/curry mixture for 20 minutes.
Add 3 tablespoons of cooking oil and 1 teaspoon of soy sauce to wok and heat until soy sauce bubbles.
Drain and discard water from chicken.
Add chicken to oil mixture in wok.
Stir and brown chicken on high heat for 5 minutes.
Lower heat; cover and simmer until cooked through.

title: caramel frosting
directions: Melt butter. Add brown sugar and evaporated milk. Cook 2 minutes over medium heat, stirring constantly. Remove from heat. Stir together confectioners sugar and vanilla. Combine with butter mixture and beat until smooth. Let cool slightly, then frost layers.

title: grape juice cocktail
directions: Shake in cocktail shaker with ice.
Serve in cocktail glasses. Decorate with maraschino cherry.

title: fruit cake
directions: Grease 2 loaf pans or 1 tube pan with butter and line with wax paper.
Cook in a slow 250° oven 1 hour.
Cool before removing from pan.

title: flossie's dinner rolls
directions: Scald and cool milk, butter or Crisco, sugar and salt. Sprinkle yeast over warm water and let it stand until it dissolves.
Add yeast mixture to the milk mixture.
Then add 1 1/2 cups flour; beat well.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add remaining flour to make a soft dough. Turn out onto a lightly floured board and knead until smooth (it should bounce back when touched with a finger).
Place dough in a buttered bowl and turn to grease completely.
Cover with plastic wrap and put in a warm place to rise until doubled in bulk, about 1 hour.

title: nutty peach crisp
directions: Layer all ingredients in ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes at 325°.
Let stand at least for 15 minutes.
Top with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: potato casserole
directions: Defrost hash browns.
They don't have to be totally defrosted. Melt oleo and mix with soup, Cheddar cheese, onions and sour cream.
Serves 8.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar and Karo.
Microwave on High for 4 minutes.
Add the peanuts; stir and microwave for 3 to 5 minutes.
Add the butter and vanilla; stir and microwave for 1 to 2 minutes.
Stir soda gently until light and foamy.
Pour onto a greased cookie sheet or pizza pan.

title: baby food cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Be sure to mix well.
Pour in tube cake pan and bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: broccoli and chicken casserole
