directions: Select quality, convenient local grocery.
Purchase suitable brand-name taco seasoning package.
(Tip:
Packages usually about 4 x 6 inches in size and of foil construction.
Base selection of hot or mild variety on personal preferences or stomach condition of family.)

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine sugar, water, jello and cornstarch.
Bring to boil and cook until thickened.
Add red food coloring.
Mix with strawberries.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Cool.
Top with whipped topping.

title: big mack sauce
directions: Mix together.
Cover and refrigerate.
Spoon over hamburgers. Makes 2 cups.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine ingredients; shape into a ball.
Ice with sour cream. Set in refrigerator for at least 1/2 hour.
Take out 1/2 hour before serving for softness.
Ball stays up to 2 weeks.
Can be frozen (but do not ice).
Serve with crackers.

title: easy sticky cinnamon rolls
directions: Grease Bundt or angel food cake pan.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup chopped pecans in bottom.
Place frozen dinner rolls in pan on top of pecans.
Sprinkle the dry pudding on top.
Melt butter and mix with brown sugar and cinnamon; pour over top of pudding.
Let rise, uncovered, overnight on counter.

title: applescotch crisp
directions: Coat a 9 x 13-inch pan with vegetable cooking spray.
Spread apples in bottom of pan; dot with margarine.
Combine brown sugar and cinnamon, and sprinkle over apples.
Sift together flour, sugar, salt and baking powder in large bowl.
Add oil and eggs, mixing by hand until smooth (batter will be thick).

title: round steak supreme
directions: Brown round steak in oil.
Put in casserole dish.
Add tomato soup, water or milk and onion.
Cover; put in oven at 300° to 325° for 3 to 4 hours.
Can also use cream of mushroom soup.

title: my fudge(pralines)
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa; add Karo and milk (I use a #8 iron skillet.)
Bring to boil and boil 3 minutes.
Set off the stove; add butter, vanilla and nuts and stir until lightly hard. (Sometimes I put pan in some cold water to help cool quickly; also if pecans are frozen, it will harden quicker.)
Drop by teaspoons onto wax paper before it hardens.
When completely cool, it may be put into a tight container to store.

title: salmon patty
directions: Pam hands before making patties (easier).
Fry patties in 1/4-inch oil until crusted.
Microwave 55 seconds to ensure egg is well cooked inside patty.
Serve with lemon wedge or white sauce.

title: favorite pancakes
directions: Beat egg.
Add remaining ingredients.
Beat with a rotary beater or mix thoroughly with a wooden spoon until smooth.
Fry on medium-hot griddle.

title: mock ravioli
directions: Cook macaroni, until tender.
Saute onion and garlic.
Add meat, cook until brown.
Add 3/4 c. spinach, water, tomato sauce, tomato paste, herbs, salt and pepper.
Mix together spinach, grated cheese, salad oil, beaten eggs and bread crumbs.
Butter a baking dish, add layers of macaroni, spinach mix and meat sauce. Repeat.
Sprinkle cheese on top, let set a few hours or overnight. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Beat eggs thoroughly.
Add sugar.
Beat well.
Add oil and continue beating.
Add vanilla.
Sift together the flour, baking powder, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Add to egg mixture when thoroughly blended.
With a spatula or spoon, stir in the carrots, nutmeats and dates.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Can also bake in a 16 x 10 1/2-inch pan.
Frost cake when cool.

title: chocolate nut toffee
directions: Combine sugar and butter.
Cook over low heat, stirring occasionally, until candy thermometer reaches 300°.
Spread mixture onto wax paper lined pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over hot candy.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Spread melted chocolate evenly over candy.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Cool completely.
Break into pieces.

title: apple pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch, spices and salt.
Mix with apples and place in 9-inch pie crust.
Add butter and sprinkle with cinnamon candies.
Top with crust.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: "8-minute light'n fruity pie"
directions: Completely dissolve Jell-O in boiling water, stirring about 3 minutes.
Add ice cubes and stir constantly, until Jell-O is thickened, about 2 or 3 minutes.
Remove any unmelted ice.
Using wire whip, blend in Cool Whip, then whip until smooth.
Fold in fruit.
Chill, if necessary, until mixture will mound.
Spoon into pie crust.
Chill for 3 hours.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw, drain and squeeze dry spinach.
Chop onion.
Combine all ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight.
Cut out large hole in loaf of bread.
Fill hole with dip.
Dip is very good with raw vegetables, crackers, chips or the "dug" out bread.

title: lasagne
directions: Mix hamburger, spaghetti sauce and water.
Place 1 layer of lasagne noodles in the bottom of a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Place 1/2 of mixture on top of noodles.
Place 1/2 of the 2 cheeses on top of mixture.
Place another layer of noodles on top of this.
Top with remaining mixture and cheeses.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: cranberry muffins
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon, ginger, nutmeg, salt and orange peel.
Cut in shortening; stir in juice, eggs and vanilla just until moistened.
Fold in nuts and cranberries.
Fill 18 greased muffins or use paper liners.
Bake at 375° for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: turkey stroganoff
directions: Saute the onion.
Add the ground turkey in lumps and fry lightly.
Add garlic, salt, pepper, mushrooms, flour and soup. Simmer 10 minutes or longer.
Stir in the sour cream.
Heat and serve.

title: polka daters
directions: Mix chopped dates and hot water.
Cool.
Beat until creamy the soft butter, sugar and eggs.
Sift together and stir in flour and baking soda gradually.
Stir in date mixture the vanilla and half of chocolate morsels.
Spread in a 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Top with half chocolate morsels and 1/2 cup chopped nuts.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 30 minutes.
Makes about 30 bars.

title: ambrosia
directions: Peel and slice the oranges, removing all the white membranes and any seeds.
Put a double layer in the bottom of a pretty glass bowl.
Sprinkle lightly with sugar and cover with a layer of coconut.
Repeat the process until all the fruit is finished and finish with a layer of coconut.
Sprinkle with sherry if desired. May add pineapple tidbits if desired.
Serve very cold.

title: new york cake
directions: Bake white cake mix according to directions in extra large flat cake pan (I use a 12 x 15-inch pan).
Cool.
Mix 2 boxes pudding mix according to directions on box.
Blend in softened cream cheese.
Spread over cooled cake and refrigerate about 45 minutes.
Pour drained pineapple over this and spread.
Spread Cool Whip on top of this.
Sprinkle coconut and nuts and garnish with cherries.
Refrigerate.
Cake is better made day before and kept in refrigerator.

title: fruit dip
directions: Beat milk, pudding mix and orange juice together.
Stir in sour cream.
Chill.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Serve with citrus or spinach salads.

title: spaghetti and meat sauce
directions: Cook spaghetti to al dente.
In large skillet, brown beef; add chopped celery, pepper and onion.
Stir until they are soft.
Add cornstarch and dry sauce mix and stir to blend well.
Add other ingredients, stirring constantly.
Turn heat to low.
Add cooked spaghetti; stir.
Cover and let flavors blend.
Turn off heat.
Let sit 5 minutes and serve with grated cheese and hot peppers. Serves 3.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Melt butter in saucepan or bowl.
Add brown sugar and mix well.
Add eggs and vanilla and mix well.
Add flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Mix.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle chocolate chips on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool and eat.

title: jody's nut bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Bake in buttered pan at 350° until done.

title: cookies and cream
directions: Dip each cookie in milk; shake and layer in 9 x 12-inch pan. Put a layer of cookies, then Cool Whip.
Continue to layer until finished.
Refrigerate for 2 to 3 hours or best overnight.
Simple and delicious!

title: bundt cake(lemon, coconut or orange)
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour in greased Bundt cake pan.
Bake approximately 1 hour at 350°.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add tomato sauce and soup and simmer for 2 minutes.
Cook noodles and drain.
Layer (2 times) noodles, meat and cheese, ending with cheese, into casserole pan. Cook until cheese melt in 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, oil and zucchini.
Add sifted dry ingredients; mix well.
Add vanilla, walnuts and raisins.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 5 x 9-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove from pans and cool.

title: cranberry party punch
directions: Pour lemonade into ice cube trays and freeze.
Just before serving, combine cubes, cranberry juice, ginger ale orange juice and Vodka in punch bowl.
Garnish with orange slices.
Makes about 2 1/2 quarts.

title: poor man's fruit cake
directions: Put sugar, water, raisins, lard, cinnamon, salt, cloves and nutmeg in a saucepan and bring to boil.
Set aside to cool.
Sift again the flour with the soda.
Add to the cooled mixture and mix well.
Add walnuts, mix well.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spray pan with Pam or lard.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: lemon poppy cake
directions: Beat eggs; add all ingredients and beat for 4 minutes.
Bake 1 hour at 350° in tube cake pan.
Cool 45 minutes.
You can put frosting on if desired.
Good without.

title: apple cake
directions: Sift all dry ingredients.
Add oil and eggs; beat well.
Mix in apples and nuts.
Bake in 2 (9 x 9-inch) greased pans at 350° for 40 minutes or until done.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken, onion, celery, carrots and salt in water until chicken is tender.
Mix 1 stick margarine into stuffing mix and seasoning packet.
Place half of stuffing mix in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Drain vegetables from chicken, saving 2 cups of broth.
Remove chicken from bone and place on top of stuffing mix. Mix the broth and vegetables with the soups; bring to a boil. Pour mixture over chicken.
Place remainder stuffing mix on top. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: italian chicken delight
directions: Dip chicken into beaten egg, coating well, then roll in breadcrumbs.
Brown in oil.
Drain chicken and place in casserole dish (single layer).

title: hershey kisses cookies
directions: Mix all together until well blended.
Mixture will be thick. Shape into 1 inch balls; roll in sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Take from oven.
Place Hershey Kiss in middle.
Press down firmly until cookie cracks around edges.
Remove at once from cookie sheet.

title: blueberry buckle
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease and flour a square pan.
Mix 3/4 cup sugar, shortening and egg thoroughly.
Stir in milk.
Blend in berries.
Spread batter in pan.
Mix the last 4 ingredients well for topping.
Put on topping.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: easy meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients. Bake in greased loaf dish for 1 hour at 350°.

title: roy's favorite baked chicken
directions: Coat chicken with Ranch dressing. Roll into Progresso Italian bread crumbs. Place chicken in an aluminum foil lined baking dish and bake at 400° for 35 minutes or until chicken is done.

title: baked lima beans
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into buttered dish.
Cover and bake 40 minutes in 300° oven.
Uncover and bake 5 minutes in hot oven to brown top.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix the first five ingredients together well.
Add flour and poppy seed.
Pour into 3 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: spinach pasta with fresh tuna and tomato
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan, heat olive oil. Add crushed and diced tomatoes, garlic, red pepper, salt and pepper.
Heat until boiling and cook, stirring occasionally, for 25 minutes. Cook fettuccine according to directions.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly and salt and pepper to taste. Pour in greased casserole dish.
Cook at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: cranberry chutney
directions: Bring all to a boil and simmer until cranberries burst.
May use canned mandarin oranges.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Beat eggs in large bowl, add sugar, buttermilk and oil.
Stir well with spoon.
Add flour and soda.
Stir well, add Raisin Bran. Store in large Tupperware.
Bake in cupcake cups.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: white bread
directions: Scald milk; stir in sugar, salt and margarine.
Cool to lukewarm.
Measure warm water into a large warm bowl.
Sprinkle in yeast; stir until dissolved.
Add lukewarm milk mixture and 3 cups flour; beat until smooth.
Add enough additional flour to make a soft dough.

title: jello-cottage cheese salad
directions: Sprinkle dry jello on cottage cheese; mix.
Blend in other ingredients.
Very fast and very good!

title: jezebel dip
directions: Mix in blender.
Keep in covered jar in refrigerator.
Dip will keep for weeks.
To serve, place three 8 ounce blocks of cream cheese on platter at room temperature.
Pour Jezebel dip over top of cream cheese and serve with crackers.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown sausage, onion, green pepper and garlic; drain.
Add next 6 ingredients.
Simmer, uncovered, 20 minutes.
Prepare Creamettes spaghetti according to package directions; drain.
Toss with butter.
Serve sauce over spaghetti with Parmesan cheese.
Makes 8 servings.

title: peanut butter play dough
directions: Mix well until blended.
Add more milk if mixture is sticky. Use as play dough and then eat your creations.

title: corn relish
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: eeeeezy peach cobbler
directions: Slice peaches in round casserole dish which has been sprayed with Pam.
Mix sugar and flour (if peaches are tart, you might want to increase the sugar a bit).
Pour over peaches.
Put several pats of margarine over the layer and sprinkle with the almond flavoring.
Top with pie crust and bake in a 350° oven until crust is brown.
This is delicious with ice cream, Cool Whip or nothing.

title: chilled raspberry parfaits
directions: In a blender, combine 2 cups berries and nectar.
Cover and process smooth.
Sieve to remove seeds.
Combine about 1/3 cup puree in saucepan with gelatin; let stand 5 minutes, then heat and stir until gelatin is dissolved.
Remove from heat; stir in lemon juice, Equal and remaining puree.
Place in a large mixer bowl. In chilled small mixing bowl, beat evaporated milk until soft peaks form and mixture triples in volume.
Gradually fold in gelatin mixture.
Gently fold mixture into the 1 cup whole berries.
Turn into parfait glasses over a layer of raspberries. Makes 6 servings.
Cover and chill 4 to 8 hours.

title: pork chop-onion-rice bake
directions: Brown pork chops in shortening.
Spread rice in bottom of baking dish.
Reserve 1 tablespoon seasoning from onion soup mix; sprinkle remaining mix over rice.
Drain mushrooms, reserving liquid, and distribute mushrooms and pimento over rice.
Add hot water to mushroom liquid to total 3 cups.
Pour over rice.
Arrange chops on top of rice and sprinkle with rest of seasoning.
Cover tightly with foil and bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour. Uncover and bake 10 more minutes or until any excess liquid evaporates.

title: sandwich spread
directions: Grind peppers, tomatoes and onions together. Pour boiling water over it for 5 minutes. Drain good. Add vinegar, sugar and salt. Cook 30 minutes. Mix flour and water, then add mustard while cooking. Take off stove. Add mayonnaise. Put in jars and seal. Makes 8 pints.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Break ingredients into small pieces.

title: banana cream pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt in saucepan.
Gradually add and heat milk, stirring constantly until thickened and boiling.
Boil 1 minute and remove from heat.
Add 1/2 mixture to bowl of egg yolks.
Stir and gradually add back to saucepan, stirring constantly.
Boil 1 minute.
Add butter and vanilla.
Blend and remove from heat and cool.
Line a 9-inch pastry in pie pan with sliced bananas on top.
Pour filling over bananas.
Chill.
Top with whipped cream and banana slices.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Mix
together and bake in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan for 35 or 40 minutes at 350°.

title: honeyed chicken
directions: Arrange chicken in a low baking dish.
Brush with soft butter and drizzle with honey combined with soy sauce.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, until chicken is tender, brushing with honey sauce frequently.
Remove chicken from pan.
Skim fat from gravy.
Add any remaining honey sauce and thicken with cornstarch, if desired. Serve over the chicken.
Makes 4 servings.

title: harvest potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except sausage and cheese.
Put in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Arrange links on top of potato mixture. Cover and bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until bubbly.
Sprinkle with the shredded cheese.
Bake, uncovered, 5 minutes.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Layer meat, potatoes (sliced) and onion (sliced) in casserole.
Season well and cover with soup.
Cover and bake at 325° until potatoes are done, about 45 minutes.

title: heavenly hash cake
directions: Combine in mixing bowl the butter, sugar and eggs. Beat for about 5 minutes or until creamy. Add flour and vanilla. Mix until smooth. Add nuts, if you want them. Pour into greased 13 x 9 baking pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes (cake will fall in the middle). When cake is done, turn off oven and pour about 1/2 bag of miniature marshmallows over top of cake. Leave cake in oven while you make topping.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Cook, drain and chop broccoli; place in bottom of 2-quart casserole dish.
Cut cooked chicken in bite size pieces on top of broccoli.

title: date and nut cake
directions: Sprinkle soda over dates. Cover with boiling water and cool. Cream shortening and sugar. Add egg.
Alternate flour and salt mixture with dates.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: olive nut spread
directions: Mix all ingredients; if does not spread well, add a few drops more of olive juice.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Press crescent rolls out onto jellyroll pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: ham roll-ups
directions: Mix and spread on ham roll and refrigerate overnight and slice.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: (If your family likes cheeseburgers in buns, watch them go for this pie.)

title: glazed nuts
directions: Put desired amount of raw pecans in deep fryer. Fry just until they turn light brown, about 30 seconds to 1 minute. Pour up on cookie sheet, lined with paper towel and salt generously.

title: light and lively salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients, then add the remaining ingredients. Mix well.
Place in refrigerator 4 to 6 hours.

title: sausage-potato au gratin
directions: Cook sausage and onion in oil until brown (about 5 minutes). Stir in potatoes, cheese sauce (from au gratin package), water and pepper.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in carrot strips and simmer until done, about 10 minutes.
Stir in broccoli and cheese; heat on low 5 to 10 minutes.

title: very ritzy chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Dip chicken in eggs.
Place bread crumbs in shallow bowl; coat chicken with bread crumbs.
In large skillet, heat oil until hot.
Place chicken in skillet and brown lightly on both sides.
Remove from skillet and place in baking dish.
Top each breast with a slice of Mozzarella cheese.
In saucepan, mix together the heavy cream, Parmesan cheese, parsley, salt and pepper.
Cook until mixture is hot and has thickened. Pour over chicken and bake for 25 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: peach pie alaska
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add ice cream by spoonfuls.
Stir until melted and smooth.
Blend in whipped topping and fruit.
Chill, if necessary, until mixture will mound. Spoon into crust.
Chill about 3 hours or freeze until firm. Makes 8 servings.

title: karo fat free chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray a 9-inch square pan with cooking spray.
Combine dry ingredients until mixed.
Whisk egg whites, water and syrup.
Stir into dry mixture until smooth.
Pour into pan.
Bake 30 minutes or until cake springs back.
Cool.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix together the corn, sugar, salt and baking powder.
Combine eggs with butter and milk and alternately with flour a little at a time.
Bake in a buttered casserole at 350°
for 1 hour.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook lasagna noodles as package directs. In bowl, combine Ricotta, Parmesan cheese and eggs.
Mix well.
On bottom of 15 x 9-inch greased baking dish, spread 1/2 cup pasta sauce.
Top with half each of the lasagna noodles, Ricotta cheese mixture, sausage, pasta sauce and Mozzarella.
Repeat layering. Top with parsley.
Cover; bake 1 hour or until hot and bubbly. Uncover; let stand 15 minutes before serving.

title: coffee can bread
directions: You will need 2 (1 pound) coffee cans.

title: quick pasty casserole
directions: Place chipped potatoes into lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Crumble ground beef over potatoes.
Add mixture of onions and rutabaga on top of ground beef.
Season and slice margarine over all.
Cover with foil and bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour. Remove from oven; drain off grease.
Add mixture of soup and water, pouring evenly over surface of casserole.
Cover with foil and bake an additional 15 minutes.
Remove, uncover, and add crescent rolls on top, unrolling each section to make a flat crust.
Bake uncovered 10 to 15 minutes or until brown.

title: good chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco and margarine with sugar.
Add salt, baking powder and cocoa to flour and sift.
Then add eggs, one at a time, alternately with flour and milk.
Add vanilla and bake in tube pan for 1 hour and 25 to 30 minutes at 325°.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Saute zucchini and onions in 3 tablespoons butter until tender.
Place in a buttered 1 1/4-quart casserole.
Combine cheeses, salt, oregano and pepper.
Sprinkle bread crumbs over mixture.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: fat free biscuits
directions: Mix milk and yogurt.
Add flour.
Dough will be sticky.
Roll out and cut with round cutter.
Bake at 450° for about 20 minutes.

title: lazy day pie
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix dry ingredients.
Put in pan on margarine.
Put fruit on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let cool.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Mix flour, salt and baking powder in another bowl.
Mix both of these mixes together.
Chill about an hour.
Roll very thin; cut out cookies.
Bake at 425° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with sugar while warm.

title: buttery potato fans
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Lightly grease a baking sheet.
Cut unpeeled potatoes into 1/4 inch slices, but do not cut all the way through.
Place potatoes on prepared baking sheet.
Spread slices slightly apart.
Mix butter and oil in a small bowl.
Lightly brush over potato skins and between slices.
Sprinkle with salt. Bake 40 minutes or until potatoes are tender and edges are brown. Spread with sour cream or serve on the side.

title: easy hot rolls
directions: Mix ingredients until yeast granules are dissolved and mixture is smooth.
Stir in flour, kneading in the last if necessary.
Put ball of dough into a well-greased bowl, turn over to coat surface with Crisco.
At this point, dough may be covered and allowed to rise or can be placed in refrigerator overnight.
Punch raised dough down.
Pinch off and form in cloverleaf rolls in greased muffin tins.
Let rise until doubled in size.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Makes 15 rolls.

title: larry's beef stroganoff
directions: Remove all fat from tenderloin and cut into julienne strips. Put butter and oil in a saute pan and heat.
Add tenderloins, mushrooms, shallots, paprika and salt and pepper.
Cook quickly until beef is rare.
Add cognac and flame.
Remove from pan. Deglaze pan with white wine.
Add demi-glace and reduce to 1/3 volume.
Finish the sauce with sour cream.
Return the tenderloin to the pan; add the pickles and simmer for 5 minutes.
Boil egg noodles until tender.
Drain noodles and make nest on plates.
Top the noodles with the finished stroganoff and garnish with chopped parsley.

title: almond chicken
directions: Melt half the butter in a large skillet; saute mushrooms and peppers about 2 minutes.
Add rest of butter, flour, 5-Spice, salt and pepper to taste.
Add soy sauce, chicken and sherry.
Cook until sherry has been absorbed.
Add chicken stock and simmer 10 minutes.
Serve topped with almonds over rice.

title: roasted potatoes
directions: You will also need a baking pan.

title: potato dish
directions: Cook potatoes; set aside.
Cook hamburger; drain.
Add Sloppy Joe mix to hamburger.
For first layer in baking dish, put potatoes, Sloppy Joe mix, vegetables and cheese; repeat for second layer.
Cook at 350° until hot and cheese melts.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Layer in a Pyrex pie plate.
Spread cream cheese, then sour cream.
Crumble shrimp.
Pour cocktail sauce.
Top with scallions. Serve with crackers.
Delicious!

title: scalloped cabbage
directions: Layer cabbage and ground soda crackers with pats of butter or margarine and add salt and pepper to each layer.
Fill your casserole with the layers.
Top with butter or margarine.
Pour milk over this until the crackers are all soaked and not too much milk.
Bake at 350° until light brown and cabbage is tender.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables according to directions on package until just tender.
Put into a greased casserole.
Mix onion, celery, cheese and mayonnaise.
Spread over vegetables.
Melt butter; mix with cracker crumbs and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mince pie
directions: Mix
together
well and pour into pastry-lined pie pan. Cover with top crust.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Boil chicken breasts until tender.
Remove skin, bone and chop real fine.
Brown chicken and onion.
Add Cheddar cheese and 1 can green chilies; stir until cheese melts.
Set aside until cool. Lightly fry tortillas in pan.
Roll chicken mix into tortillas. Put into pan.

title: potato wedges
directions: Melt margarine in pan.
Combine Parmesan cheese, flour, celery and garlic salt.
Roll potatoes in mixture.
Lay potatoes in pan with melted butter.
Bake 30 minutes on one side, then turn them over and bake 30 minutes more.
Bake at 350°.

title: deluxe pecan pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In small bowl, beat eggs, sugar, salt, butter or margarine, syrup and cream.
Stir in vanilla and pecans. Pour into a pastry-lined pie pan.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes or until filling is set and pastry is golden brown.
Serve plain or with ice cream.

title: antipasto salad
directions: In a large bowl, stir together corn oil, vinegar, garlic, basil, salt and red pepper.
Add warm macaroni and Parmesan cheese; toss to coat well.
Cover and refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.
Add broccoli, pepperoni and tomatoes; toss until well mixed.
Serve on lettuce lined platter; sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.

title: summer sausage
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Form into 2 loaves and wrap in plastic wrap.
Refrigerate 24 hours.
Bake at 300°
for 1 hour.

title: caponata(serves 12 to 15)
directions: Put into mug and stir well.
Sip and enjoy.

title: kool-aid play dough
directions: Combine ingredients.
Add 2 cups boiling water.
Knead dough; more flour may be added if needed.

title: poor man's casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Drain and add A.1. sauce, sugar and beans.
Reduce heat and simmer 7 to 10 minutes.
Remove from heat and cover mixture with sliced cheese.
Cover and let stand for a few minutes before serving.

title: apple cranberry casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour into 2-quart greased (with Pam) casserole.

title: date pudding
directions: Make batter and pour into greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Cover topping over mixture.

title: boston crabies
directions: Combine margarine and cheese spread; mix well.
Add mayonnaise, seasoned salt, garlic salt and crab meat to margarine and cheese mixture.
Spread on split English muffins and put in freezer for 2 hours.
Remove and cut into serving pieces; return to freezer.
When ready to serve, place under broiler for approximately 5 minutes or until browned.

title: hot clam appetizer
directions: Saute
pepper
and onion in butter, then add everything but cheeses
and paprika.
If it seems dry, add some water to it, then
place
in a casserole.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and paprika.
Top with Provolone.
Bake 15 minutes at 375° or until melted.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Pour boiling water over the rhubarb and then drain.
Place the drained rhubarb in a bowl and add all the other ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° until rhubarb is tender and crust is baked.

title: russian tea cookies
directions: Mix margarine, sugar and vanilla.
Add flour and salt.
Add nuts.
Form dough into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for about 8 minutes.
Roll in confectioners sugar immediately.
Let cool and roll again.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix well first 5 ingredients.
Place in casserole dish.
Crush Ritz crackers and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until bubbly.
Serves 6.

title: moors and christians
directions: Cook bacon in skillet until lightly browned.
Remove and drain. Add onion and garlic to skillet and cook until tender.
Combine onion, garlic, beans, bacon, 2 cups water and remaining ingredients (except rice) in a large saucepan and simmer slowly for 1 1/2 hours or until beans are tender.
Serve spooned over hot cooked rice with additional chopped onion to taste.

title: favorite green bean casserole
directions: Combine green beans, soup and onions (reserving a few onions for garnish) in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°. Serves 6.

title: chewy pecan squares
directions: Mix 1 cup flour and 1/2 cup sugar; cut in butter until forms fine crumbs. Pat into greased 8-inch square pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Remove. Mix 1/4 cup flour, 1/2 cup sugar and remaining ingredients. Pour over crust. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until top is set. Cool. Cut into squares.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix together and keep in airtight container.
Use 1/3 cup chocolate mix and 2/3 cup boiling water.
Mix well.

title: pepper steak
directions: Brown cubed or chopped steak and put in crock-pot.
Brown in oil the onion and garlic.
Add bouillon and water and bring to boil.
Add cornstarch; stir until clear glaze.
Add soy sauce to taste, celery and pepper.
Simmer in crock pot.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Saute onions and celery.
Add to stuffing mix.
Add sage; mix well.
Add enough chicken broth for desired consistency.
Place chicken in bottom of casserole.
Mix soup and milk.
Pour over chicken.
Cover with stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: oreo cookie cake
directions: Cream the butter and cream cheese; add the sugar.
Prepare pudding mix and add to mixture.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Layer bottom of pan with 1/2 of the crushed Oreo cookies. Add creamed mixture and layer the top with rest of Oreos.

title: nut biscuits
directions: Stir flour, salt and baking powder together. Rub or cut in the lard and add the nuts and sugar.

Add milk gradually until the mixture is soft and spongy. Turn onto a slightly floured board and roll lightly until of a uniform thickness, about 1/2-inch thick. Cut with a small floured biscuit cutter.
Place on a greased pan and bake for 12 or 15 minutes in a quick oven.
Butter and serve while hot.

title: chicken magnifique
directions: In Dutch oven, brown chicken in butter.
Remove.
Brown mushrooms.
Stir in soup, garlic and seasonings.
Add chicken. Cover and
cook
over
low heat for 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Blend in half and half.
Heat slowly.
Garnish with slivered almonds.
Serve with rice pilaf.

title: fruit pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour together; add cherries, pineapple and juice.
Cook on top of stove until thick.
Remove from heat and add jello.
Let cool.
After mixture is cool, add bananas and pecans.
Pour in pie shells and refrigerate.
Top with whipped cream, if desired.

title: tamale pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Crumble beef into heated skillet. Cook over moderate heat until meat loses its red color.
Add onion, celery and garlic during the last five minutes cooking time. Drain off grease.
Drain tomatoes.
Reserve 3/4 cup of the tomato juice and mix it with cornmeal.
Cut tomatoes in small pieces. Add cornmeal mixture.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, five minutes.
Add corn and its liquid, olives and their liquid, chili powder, Worcestershire sauce, salt and meat mixture.
Mix well.
Spoon mixture into 2 qt casserole.
Sprinkle top with cheese.
Bake, uncovered, in a 375° oven for 30 minutes. Makes six servings.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Whip cream cheese, adding milk and lemon juice.
Add remaining ingredients and place in a shallow ovenproof dish.
Sprinkle with paprika and slivered almonds.
Bake at 350° until hot.
Serve with crackers, Wheat Thins are best.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix thoroughly and refrigerate. Makes 4 cups.
Serve with fresh veggies.

title: ramen noodle salad
directions: Remove seasoning packet from Ramen noodles and reserve for another use.
Break noodles into pieces.
Melt butter in a large skillet on medium high heat.
Add Ramen noodles and nuts and saute until lightly browned.
Drain on paper towels.

title: party potatoes
directions: Pare potatoes and boil until tender. Drain. Beat softened cheese and sour cream with a mixer at medium speed until well blended.
Add hot potatoes gradually, beating constantly, until light and fluffy.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Place in 2-quart casserole dish. Dot with butter and sprinkle with paprika. Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: In a 10-inch skillet over medium heat, cook beef, onion and chili powder until beef is browned, stirring to separate meat. Spoon off fat.
Stir in soup and beans; heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low.
Simmer for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally. Arrange salad greens and tortilla chips on serving plate.
Top with hot meat mixture.
Top with tomato.
Garnish as desired. Serve with additional tortilla chips, if desired.

title: peanut butter round ups
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Place shortening and sugars in a bowl. Beat until light and fluffy. Add eggs and beat well. Blend in peanut butter. Sift together the flour, salt, and soda. Stir into peanut butter mixture. Stir in the oats.

title: cranberry meatballs
directions: Combine meat, tomato juice and bread.
Mix well.
Add salt, pepper, Worcestershire, parsley and egg.
Roll into balls and brown in small amount of butter.
Beat cranberry sauce with lemon juice and brown sugar.
Pour over meatballs and simmer 30 minutes.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix 1
cup
graham
crumbs,
cup sugar and 1/4 cup melted butter
well
and press into bottom of spring-form pan. Blend well in
blender
1 1/2 cups sour cream, 2 eggs, 1/2 cup sugar, 1 pound
cream cheese and 2 tablespoons melted butter. Pour into pan
with graham crust and bake 30 to 35 minutes at 325°.
Open oven and turn on broiler.
Brown top lightly.

title: apple nut dessert
directions: Beat egg in small bowl with electric mixer.
Gradually beat in sugar and vanilla.
Fold in flour mixed with baking powder, then fold in apples and nuts.
Turn into greased and floured 9-inch layer or square pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for about 30 minutes.
Spoon into dessert dishes while warm and top with a spoonful of ice cream.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Cut marshmallows.
Add orange juice.
May use graham cracker crust or a regular pie crust, cooled.
Fill pie shell with peaches, cream, nuts and marshmallow mixture.
Place in refrigerator to chill several hours or overnight.

title: barnett salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together and serve over favorite salad.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Put eggs in bowl.
Beat well.
Add oil, sugar and vanilla. Mix well.
Add flour a little bit at a time; mix well.
Add apples and nuts.
Grease pan with vegetable oil.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour until done.

title: no-bake chocolate cheesecake
directions: In a small microwave-safe bowl, place chocolate chips. Microwave on High (100%) for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes or until chips are melted and mixture is smooth when stirred. Set aside to cool.

title: vegetarian chinese casserole(meatless recipe)
directions: Place half the Chinese noodles in a casserole.
Top with drained vegetables, drained mushrooms (mix mushroom liquid with soup), diced chicken style product, soup, remaining noodles and cashews.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: grilled honey soy chicken
directions: In shallow nonmetallic dish, combine orange juice, soy sauce, honey, lemon pepper, ginger and garlic powder; set aside.
Place chicken breasts between two sheets of plastic wrap, pound until 1/2 inch thick; place in marinade.
Cover; refrigerate 4 to 6 hours or overnight.
At serving time, remove chicken from marinade, reserve marinade.
Place chicken on uncovered grill directly on medium hot coals.
Grill 10 minutes or until tender and no longer pink, turning chicken once.
During last 2 minutes, brush with reserved marinade.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Pick and wash berries and put aside on paper towels to dry. Cream together the cheese and coffee creamer and spread evenly in bottom of baked pie shell.
Place the biggest, nicest berries, points up, in the shell (this will take about half the berries). Put in refrigerator to chill while preparing the glaze.
Crush remaining berries and add water to make 1 1/2 cups berries and juice.
Add sugar blended with cornstarch and cook over low heat until thick, stirring constantly.
Add enough red food coloring to give deep color and cook 2 minutes longer.
Cool.
Pour over berries in crust and chill until ready to serve.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: salsa
directions: Combine all ingredients in a food processor and chop.
Chill and serve.

title: basic vinaigrette
directions: In a bowl or in a small bottle, combine vinegar, salt and pepper.
Add oil and whisk or shake dressing until well blended. Lemon juice can be used in place of vinegar.

title: bean, hot dog and kraut bake
directions: Spread pork and beans in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Mix catsup, mustard, horseradish, honey and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour half over baked beans.
Chop onion and green pepper.
Cook in butter, then spread on top of beans.
Place 10 hot dogs on top of that, then place kraut over hot dogs.
Pour remaining liquid over top of kraut. Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Take out of oven and sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top.
Put back in oven for a few minutes.

title: crisco pastry
directions: Combine flour and salt in mixing bowl.
Cut in Crisco with pastry blender or two knives until mixture is uniform (mixture should be fairly coarse).
Sprinkle with water a tablespoon at a time; toss lightly with fork when all water has been added.
Work dough into a firm ball.
Divide into 2 parts and roll to fit pan. Makes 2 crusts.
Bake according to pie recipe.

title: tarragon vinegar
directions: Combine in a jar.
Let stand 24 hours, then remove garlic.

title: chicken in port wine
directions: Heat pan first, then add oil.
Brown chicken.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Cook and remove to heated plate.
Saute garlic, onion and mushrooms.
Add chicken and Port wine.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Remove chicken again.
Add sour cream and thicken with roux.
Add pepper again to taste.
Return chicken and serve over rice or pasta.
Serves 4.

title: stuffed french toast
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Cut the bread into cubes. Spread half the bread cubes into prepared pan. Cut the cream cheese into small cubes and sprinkle half of cream cheese over the bread in the pan. Repeat layering the remaining bread and cheese. Beat together the eggs, milk and maple syrup in a large bowl. Pour over the bread mixture. Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: microwave coconut pie
directions: I didn't have potatoes

title: german sweet chocolate pie
directions: Heat chocolate and 2 tablespoons of the milk in saucepan over low heat, stirring until chocolate melts.
Beat sugar into cream cheese; add remaining milk and chocolate mixture.
Beat until smooth.
Fold in whipped topping, blend until smooth.
Spoon into crust.
Freeze until firm.
Takes about 4 hours.

title: punch
directions: Mix together sugar, Kool-Aid, water, pineapple juice and lemonade.
Freeze.
Take out of freezer about 3 or 4 hours before serving.
Add chilled ginger ale just before serving.
Serves 36.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix all together and add Doritos on top.

title: country potatoes
directions: Cut baking potatoes into 1/8-inch slices.
Place in bowl with 2 tablespoons oil, salt, black pepper and cayenne pepper.
Place skin side down on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 422° until tender.
Add parsley if desired.

title: old-fashioned perfection salad
directions: Thoroughly mix gelatin, sugar and salt.
Add boiling water and stir to dissolve gelatin, then add cold water, vinegar and lemon juice.
Chill until partially set.
Now add cabbage.
For easy shredding, have cabbage refrigerator cold.
Also add pimiento and green olive slices.
Pour into an 8 1/2 x 4 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan. Chill the salad mold until firm.
Just before mealtime, unmold and garnish salad.

title: unbaked peanut butter bars
directions: Melt butter, peanut butter and chips over low heat, stirring constantly.
Cool slightly.
Stir in marshmallows, coconut and walnuts.
Spoon into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle a little coconut on top.
Refrigerate until firm.
Cut into 1/2-inch bars.

title: buttery black walnut brittle
directions: In a saucepan cook sugar, corn syrup and water until sugar dissolves and mixture comes to a boil.
Add butter; cook until mixture reaches 280° on a candy thermometer.
Stir in walnuts; cook until 300° (hard crack stage).
Remove from the heat and stir in baking soda.
Spread immediately into a greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
When cool, break into pieces.
Yield:
1 1/4 pounds.

title: baked potatoes
directions: Cut hot baked potatoes in half, lengthwise, and scoop out insides.
With an electric mixer beat oleo and potatoes until creamy, gradually add the milk; mixing well.
Add salt and pepper; stir.
Spoon mixture back into the potato shells.
Sprinkle with shredded cheese.
Arrange in baking dish.
Bake at 375° until heated through and cheese is melted.
Sprinkle lightly with paprika.

title: white chocolate candy
directions: Melt chocolate in saucepan until smooth.
Stir in peanuts, pretzels and raisins.
Spread on ungreased cookie sheet (cover only approximately 2/3 to 3/4 of cookie sheet).
Freeze 10 to 15 minutes.
Break into pieces.
Makes a quick and easy gift for the holidays.

title: apple cheddar cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease 9-inch square baking pan.
In large bowl, combine cornmeal, flour, sugar and baking powder.
In a medium sized bowl with mixer on medium speed, beat egg, milk and butter.
Add to flour mixture stirring until moistened.
Stir in apples and cheese.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake 20 minutes. Cool on wire rack 10 minutes.
Cut into squares serving warm.

title: garlic grits
directions: Cook grits as directed on box.
Add garlic cheese, grated cheese and oleo.
Add Worcestershire sauce and eggs along with milk.
Put in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: tuna casserole with chow mein noodles
directions: Place
about 2 inches of chow mein noodles in bottom of casserole.
Drain
tuna
fish
and
mix with cream of mushroom soup.
Put
tuna
mixture on top of noodles in casserole.
Put about
inch
of
chow
mein noodles on top of tuna mixture. Bake at 350° until bubbly hot, about 1/2 hour.

title: laurette's sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix chopped meat and bread crumbs together; form into small meatballs.
Brown; drain fat.
Place meatballs in oven pan. Combine remaining ingredients; pour over meatballs.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 325°.

title: cherry goody
directions: Grease bottom of a round glass pan.
Place cherries in pan. Cover cherries with unmade cake mix. Cut butter into pats and place on top of cake mix powder.
Bake at 350° until golden.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Drain liquid from salmon into measuring cup.
Add milk to make a cup of liquid.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Add onion and cook until tender, but not brown.
Blend in flour, salt and the pepper. Add milk and cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Flake salmon and add to sauce with lemon juice.
Stir in 1/2 cup corn flakes.
Refrigerate until chilled.
Divide into 8 or 10 portions and shape.
Roll in remaining crumbs to coat well.
Place on greased baking sheet and bake in hot oven, about 400°, 20 to 25 minutes until golden brown.
Serve with tartar sauce.

title: easy parmesan chicken breasts
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Spray baking pan with Pam.
Dip chicken in melted butter and coat with cheese mixture.
Place in baking pan and bake about 25 minutes or until tender.

title: crustless coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients, pour into pie pan and bake at 300 degrees until done, about 35 to 40 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate.

title: oatmeal cookie mix
directions: Put sugars, flour, salt, soda and baking powder in
a large bowl.
Cut in the shortening until mixture is crumbly.
Add oats and mix well.
Store in cool place.

title: cocktail sauce
directions: Combine all
ingredients.
Makes enough for 2 or 3 cans of shrimp or crab.

title: pasta salad
directions: Pour dressing over and toss again.
Refrigerate 2 hours before serving.

title: pineapple nut bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a loaf pan (9 x 5 x 3-inch).
Cream brown sugar, butter and eggs until fluffy.
Measure flour by sifting.
Blend dry ingredients.
Stir half the flour mixture into creamed mixture.
Add pineapple and juice, then remaining flour. Blend in nuts.
Pour into pan.
Mix granulated sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over top.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes or until toothpick stuck into center comes out clean.
Cool before slicing with a thin, sharp knife.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: taste like champagne
directions: Mix ingredients in punch bowl.
Add ice and serve.
Serves 18 to 20 people.

title: power cookies
directions: Cream together the sugars, butter and Crisco.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Mix dry ingredients and sift into cream mixture. Mix well.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Drop by teaspoonful on a greased cookie sheet 2 inches apart.
Bake in preheated 350° oven.
Best if shaped into rolls and chilled several hours before slicing and baking.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: For crust, unroll crescent rolls.
Pat into a 15 x 10 x 1-inch ungreased baking pan.
Bake in 375° oven for 12 minutes or until golden.
Cool completely.
In a medium mixing bowl, stir together cream cheese, sour cream and dressing mix until smooth.
Spread on top of cooled crust.
Top with chopped or sliced mixed vegetables. Sprinkle with cheese.
Cut into 2-inch squares.
Makes 35 appetizers.

title: canned apple pie filling
directions: Peel and slice apples (set aside).
Mix together sugar, food coloring, cinnamon, nutmeg, salt, lemon juice and water.
Cook until heated through.
Add to apples and boil for 20 minutes. Fill quart jars 1/2 full of liquid and fill with apples.
Make sure liquid covers apples.
Seal and put in canner.
Process 10 minutes.

title: toll-house cake
directions: Grease and flour tube pan.
Cream together butter, brown sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs.
Blend in flour, soda and salt alternately with milk.
Stir in chips.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
When cake is cooled, sprinkle with 10x sugar.

title: western cake
directions: Sift flour and sugar into bowl.
Combine margarine, cocoa and water in saucepan and cook to boiling.
Pour over sugar and flour and mix well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix.
Pour into greased sheet cake pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Prepare icing 5 minutes before cake is done.

title: white chocolate-covered-no bake
directions: Mix all ingredients and drop by teaspoons on waxed paper.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Combine and blend well the egg, flour, sugar and butter.
Fill pie shell with fresh peach halves, cut side up.
Pour mixture over peaches.
Bake in preheated oven at 400° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 300° and bake 50 minutes longer.

title: lima stew with meatballs
directions: Rinse beans.
Place in Dutch oven.
Add the water and boil 2 minutes.
Cover; let stand 1 hour (or soak overnight).
Do not drain.
Combine flour and cold water.
Stir into beans.
Cook until thickened and bubbly.
Add vegetables.
Fry beef with onion. Add to beans and vegetables.
Add tomato sauce.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Place bay leaf in bottom of casserole.
Spoon mixture into dish.
Cover and bake in 375° oven for 1 1/2 to 2 hours. Stir occasionally.

title: onion cheese supper bread
directions: Cook onion in 1 tablespoon margarine until transparent. Combine egg and milk and add to baking mix.
Stir just until moistened.
Add cooked onion and half of the shredded cheese. Spread dough in greased 8-inch square pan.
Sprinkle top with remaining cheese and poppy seeds.
Drizzle 2 tablespoons melted margarine all over.
Bake at 400° for 20-25 minutes.
Cut in squares while hot and serve.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Chop broccoli into small flowerets.
Chop onions.
Crumble the bacon.
Grate cheese.
Combine vinegar, sugar and mayonnaise. Pour over salad.
Stir with a fork.

title: easy nacho dip
directions: Split cream cheese in half and press in bottom of casserole dish.
Spread chili on top of cream cheese.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Heat in oven at 350° until warmed, about 20 minutes.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Tear bread into crumbs; place in saucepan.
Add butter, onion and soy sauce; mix well over low heat.
Pull stems off mushrooms and scoop out or hollow the mushrooms.
Cut mushroom stems in pieces and add to mix.
Cook 2 minutes on low heat.
Spoon mix into mushroom caps and bake at 400° for 5 minutes in a shallow dish, then place in broiler for 3 minutes, until toasted.
Serve warm.

title: calumet one egg cake
directions: Sift flour once; measure and add baking powder and salt.
Sift together three times; cream butter thoroughly.
Add sugar gradually and cream together until light and fluffy.
Add egg and beat very thoroughly.
Add flour, alternately with milk, a small amount at a time.
Beat after each addition until smooth.
Add vanilla.
Bake in a greased pan, 8 x 8 x 2-inch, in moderate oven (350°) for 50 minutes.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Stir ingredients and make into balls.
You can make them by buttering your hands and dipping them in cold water to keep from getting burned.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Melt margarine in casserole dish; add rice.
Add fryer parts; sprinkle with salt.
Pour 1 can beef consomme or chicken/rice soup over fryer.
Add 1 can water.
Cover and cook in oven for about 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
Serves 6.

title: bacardi rum cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour 10-inch tube or Bundt pan.
Sprinkle nuts on bottom of pan.
Combine cake mix, pudding, 4 eggs, 1/2 cup water, oil and 1/2 cup rum and pour into pan.
Bake at 325° until done.

title: teriyaki beef kabobs
directions: Marinate beef cubes in sauce for 12 hours, then broil.
Great on the outdoor grill.
Serves 4.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well. Add vanilla.
Sift flour, salt, soda and baking powder.
Add creamed mixture, alternating with sour cream, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
Drop by heaping spoonfuls on well-greased cookie sheet, well apart.
Flatten with a spoon.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: thanksgiving pilgrim punch
directions: Stir juices and ginger ale; add sherbet.
(Should be easiest recipe in book!)

title: taco dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and French onion dip together.
Spread in bottom of pan.
Put taco seasoning in hamburger.
Put hamburger on top of cream cheese and dip.
Then add layer of everything else.

title: feijoada
directions: Place beans, sausage, dried beef and bacon or salt pork in soup pot.
Cover with water and boil for 2 hours or until beans are soft and mixture is thickened.
Keep adding water so mixture does not dry out.

title: crispy buttermilk chicken(ultra low-fat)
directions: Mix together buttermilk, garlic salt, garlic and black pepper. Dip chicken breasts in mixture and roll in corn flakes.
Bake on baking sheet sprayed with nonstick cooking spray at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.
Recipe makes 4 servings.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Combine in a large bowl or 13 x 9-inch pan the following layers: 1. lettuce and onion, 2. 1/2 cup salad dressing,
3. celery, peppers and peas,
4. 1/2 cup salad dressing, 5. sugar, 6. cheese, 7. bacon.
Cover and refrigerate at least 8 hours.
Add water chestnuts and toss before serving.

title: grandma's molasses cookies
directions: Sift together first 5 ingredients.
Cut in shortening to fine crumb consistency.
Heat molasses and add to flour mixture.
Chill dough until stiff enough to roll.
Roll 1/8-inch thick on lightly floured board.
Shape as desired.
Bake 8 minutes on lightly greased cookie sheet in moderately hot oven (400°).
Keep in tightly closed cookie tin.
Makes 8 to 10 dozen cookies.

title: sour cream halibut
directions: Mix wine and salt.
Marinate halibut fillets in this mix for at least 1 hour (longer if possible; it will enhance the flavor of the halibut).
Drain fish on paper towel.
Dip both sides in crumbs; place on greased baking dish.
Mix mayonnaise, sour cream and onion.
Spread mix over fish and sprinkle top with remaining crumbs and paprika.
Bake at 500° for 15 minutes or until fish flakes when tested with a fork.
Serves 4.

title: sausage and rice casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain off fat.
Saute onion, celery and bell pepper.
Cook vegetables until they are tender.
In saucepan, pour the water and mix in the cup of rice and chicken noodle soup mixes. Stir and bring to a boil.
Boil this mixture for 10 minutes.
Pour into the sausage mixture.
Add mushrooms and almonds to the mixture.
Pour contents in an ungreased casserole dish and add the clear chicken broth.
Place the uncovered casserole dish in oven at 350° for an hour.

title: ham loaf
directions: Combine ingredients and bake 2 hours at 325°.
Mix small amount of brown sugar, mustard and vinegar.
Can serve with sauce made of whipping cream, horseradish, 1 tablespoon mayonnaise and 1 tablespoon Worcestershire sauce.
Serves 8.

title: baked beans(to can)
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Cook until soft and tender, then drain. Mix altogether and cook a few minutes.
Add to beans and put in jars.
Cook in jars 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Makes 14 quarts.

title: santa's shortbread cookies
directions: Beat butter at medium speed with an electric mixer until creamy; gradually add powdered sugar, beating well.
Add vanilla, beating until blended.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt; add to butter mixture, beating at low speed until blended.
Divide cookie dough in half; shape each portion into a 10-inch log.
Wrap in wax paper and chill 8 hours, or freeze up to 6 weeks and thaw in refrigerator.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes or until done.
Approximately 100 calories per muffin with a trace of fat.

title: onion cheese ball
directions: In a mixing bowl.
Beat cheeses, onion and worcestershire sauce until well blended.
Shape into a ball and roll in parsley. Chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: tasty carrot nut pudding
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine flour, sugar, cinnamon, oil, eggs and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in carrots and 3/4 cup nuts.
Pour batter into greased 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 300° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool; cut into squares.

title: easy chocolate pie
directions: P. S. Can be any flavor pie!

title: broccoli and chicken casserole
directions: Butter baking dish and layer with broccoli, then chicken pieces.
Combine soups, mayonnaise and cheese and spread over chicken.
Sprinkle on cracker crumbs.
Cover and bake 30 minutes at 375°.

title: pink arctic salad
directions: Add mayonnaise and sugar to cream cheese; mix well.
Add pineapple, then cranberry sauce to cream cheese.
Mix well.
Fold in Cool Whip and nuts.
Put into cupcake papers (in cupcake pans) or 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Freeze.
Store in baggie in freezer. Makes 16 cupcake papers.

title: moist corn bread
directions: In a bowl, combine cornmeal and baking powder.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into a 12 x 9 x 2-inch buttered baking dish.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until top is golden brown.
Delicious when you serve chili.

title: homemade sherbet
directions: Mix and freeze in ice cream freezer.

title: 100 krispie cookies
directions: Drop onto ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: southern biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Mix dry ingredients well in bowl.
Cut in shortening (or lard) with pastry blender.
Stir in almost all of milk.
Add enough milk to make a soft puffy dough, easy to roll. Knead dough 6 times.
Roll dough on floured surface, preferable foil.
Roll smooth and cut with cutter.
Place close together on ungreased baking sheet.
Brush melted grease on top.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 20.

title: white clam sauce
directions: Heat oil.
Add garlic.
Sizzle gently.
Stir in clam juice, pepper, oregano, parsley and little necks.
Simmer, uncovered, until the little necks are opened.
Add butter and stir gently so little necks don't come out of shells.
Serve over hot linguini.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix cake mix, 1 egg and margarine and pat into an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat the cream cheese, 2 eggs and powdered sugar together for 5 minutes.
Pour cream cheese mixture over cake mix. Spread evenly.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Let cool before cutting into squares.

title: sesame chicken
directions: Mix 4 tablespoons of soy sauce and 2 teaspoons of sesame oil together.
Marinate chicken briefly.
Drain. Put on skewers and grill until done, basting with rest of marinade, from five to ten minutes, depending on heat.
They are done when the pink is gone and they are white in the center.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mash squash; add salt, diced onion, sour cream, soup and 3/4 bag of dressing mix.
Put in buttered baking dish.
Melt margarine and mix with remaining crumbs.
Spread over top of squash.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 to 50 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: chili cheese dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Heat until melted in quart size pan.

title: corn relish
directions: Combine
vinegar,
sugar,
mustard
seed
and salt in a Dutch oven;
boil
2 minutes, stirring to dissolve sugar.
Add remaining ingredients
to
sugar mixture, and boil 3 minutes. Cool.	Store in refrigerator in an airtight container.
Yields 3 1/2 to 4 cups.

title: hawaiian wedding cake
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well. Add baking powder and crumbs slowly with milk, coconut, walnuts and pineapple.
Mix together.
Fold in after everything else. Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan in 350° oven for 40 to 50 minutes.
Use Buttercream icing.

title: baked tomatoes provencale
directions: Cut tomatoes across the top.
Scoop out seeds.
Mix together shallots, garlic and herbs.
Place tomatoes (cut side up) on a baking sheet.
Salt and pepper them.
Sprinkle with the herb and garlic mixture, then with breadcrumbs.
Sprinkle with a little olive oil.
Bake in a preheated oven at 400° for 10 minutes.
An entree for 6 people.

title: punch
directions: Mix the ingredients and put in an empty milk gallon container; freeze it.
When you are ready to drink it, take out about 2 or 3 hours ahead of time and let thaw a little, then take out of container with a knife and pour ginger ale over it.

title: maraschino cherry cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add shortening, juice from cherries, milk and maraschino cherries. Beat with mixer on medium speed for 2 minutes.
Add unbeaten egg whites.
Beat 2 minutes more, scraping bowl constantly.
Fold in chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until top springs back when lightly touched.
Cool and ice with frosting.

title: kool-aid pie
directions: Place milk in bowl and chill, then beat until doubled. Gradually add sugar and Kool-Aid.
Pour into crust and freeze.

title: trash
directions: Melt together chips, butter and peanut butter.
Pour over Rice Chex.
Mix well.
Pour confectioners sugar in a large plastic bag. Pour in Rice Chex with chocolate.
Shake to cover well.
Pour Chex on waxed paper to dry and cool.
Refrigerate.

title: candy cane crisps(okay to freeze, from the collection of lori wilson)
directions: In large bowl of an electric mixer, beat butter and 1 cup of the sugar until creamy; beat in vanilla.
In another bowl, stir together flour and oats; gradually add to butter mixture, blending thoroughly.
Add 1/4 cup of the crushed candy canes and mix until well combined.
Roll dough into 3/4-inch balls, then roll in remaining sugar to coat.
Place balls about 2 inches apart on greased and flour-dusted baking sheets.
Flatten cookies with a fork, making crisscross pattern with fork tines.
Sprinkle each with about 1/2 teaspoon crushed candy canes.
Bake at 325° for 18 to 20 minutes or until edges are lightly browned.
Let cool on baking sheets 2 to 3 minutes, then transfer to racks and cool completely.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Form meat into 40 meatballs; brown lightly in vegetable oil. Cover and cook over low heat 5 minutes.
Drain excess fat.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook rice.
Mix ingredients together.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: pea salad
directions: Drain peas.
Add boiled eggs and onion.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add Miracle Whip and toss until peas are coated.
Add sugar and mix again.
Cover and refrigerate for 30 minutes before serving.

title: 18th century pound cake
directions: Cream the butter with vanilla and sugar until very, very fluffy.
Beat egg yolks until thick.
Add to creamed mixture. Beat whites until stiff. Fold in thoroughly.
Now fold in flour and beat vigorously for 15 minutes or longer.
Bake in a 325° oven for 1 1/4 hours.

title: grilled frog legs
directions: Have charcoal real hot.
Grease rack and put it close to hot coals.
Salt the legs and put on the grill.
Baste often with a mixture of oil and lemon juice.
This prevents drying out as much. Frog legs tend to dry out real bad.
Cook until they are golden brown and are tender.
Cooking time varies according to size of legs, small ones average of 15 minutes, medium around 25 minutes.

title: danish apple bars
directions: Sift flour and salt into bowl. Cut in butter until crumbly. Add enough milk to egg yolk to make 1/2 cup. Add to flour mixture. Mix until moistened. Divide dough almost in half. Roll out larger half. Place in a jelly roll pan. Press up on sides of pan. Sprinkle with cornflakes. Arrange apple slices over cornflakes. Combine sugar and cinnamon and sprinkle over apples. Roll out other half of dough to fit top. Makes vents in top. Moisten edges of dough with water. Seal. Spread egg whites over crust. Bake in a 375° oven for 1 hour or until golden brown. Combine powdered sugar, water and vanilla. Spread on bars while still warm.

title: butterscotch cookies
directions: Mix in order given.
Form dough into 4 rolls and refrigerate for 2 hours. Slice and bake on greased cookie tins at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: kathy's enchilada casserole
directions: Brown meat with onions.
In a saucepan, heat both soups, enchilada sauce and 1/2 cup milk.
Pour mixture into meat.
Add green chilies.
Lay flour tortillas across bottom of a 9 x 13-inch oblong pan.
Pour half of the meat mixture, then half of grated cheese, then 3 flour tortillas, meat mixture and cheese again. Bake at 350° until bubbling.

title: chinese casserole
directions: Brown the meat with the onion, celery and garlic.
Combine meat with all remaining ingredients (except chow mein noodles) and pour into 3-quart casserole. Do not salt.
Sprinkle with chow mein noodles and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook spaghetti as directed on box.
Combine tomato sauce, oregano, parsley, salt and pepper in saucepan.
Simmer 10 minutes. Brown sausage and drain.
Start layers with half the spaghetti, half the sauce, half the sausage, half the onion, half the green pepper, half the pepperoni and half the cheese.
Start over, ending with the cheese.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 375° or microwave until cheese is melted.
Use a large casserole dish.

title: pancake hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients with buttermilk to form a thick batter. Drop in deep hot oil.

title: apple walnut cake
directions: Combine apples and sugar; let stand.
Beat eggs lightly; beat in oil and vanilla.
Mix flour, soda, cinnamon and salt; stir into egg mixture.
Add nuts.
Combine with apple chunks.
Pour into greased pan 13 x 9 x 2-inches.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix in 2-quart casserole.
Cover and refrigerate overnight. Remove from fridge and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, covered. Stir once during baking.

title: caramel corn
directions: Melt margarine and brown sugar.
Add marshmallows.
Heat until marshmallows are melted, stirring constantly.
Pour over popped corn and mix well.

title: vanilla butternut pound cake
directions: Cream shortening, oleo and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time. Add milk and flour, alternating each.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 45 minutes.
Start in cold oven.

title: lemon pie
directions: Combine in saucepan the first 3 ingredients; stir in gradually the boiling water and cook over low heat.
Continue stirring and boil 1 minute, slowly.
Stir half the mixture into egg yolks. Beat egg mixture back into remaining hot mixture.
Boil 1 minute, stirring.
Remove from heat.
Stir in margarine and juice.
Cool. Pour into cold baked 9-inch pie shell and top with meringue.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: praline bars
directions: Place crackers on jelly roll pan with sides.
Melt butter in saucepan. Add sugar and pecans.
Boil slowly for 2 minutes.
Pour over graham crackers.
Bake at 300° for 15 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes and then cut into bars.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: broccoli and ham casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Layer ham and cheese on top of broccoli.
Mix eggs, milk and Bisquick with mixer; pour over ham, cheese and broccoli.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: little porkies
directions: Mix all up and shape into 6 (3/4-inch) oval patties.
Stick 3 or 4 whole cloves on top of each.
Arrange spoke-fashion in a 10-inch glass pie plate.

title: swiss steak
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper; rub into both sides of steak or pound in with meat mallet or edge of heavy plate.
Cut into 6 portions.
Peel and slice onions.
Preheat skillet; add half of shortening, then onions.
Brown lightly.
Remove from skillet. Add remaining shortening; brown steak on both sides.
Reduce heat. Add celery, garlic, chili sauce and water.
Cover; simmer 1 hour. Cut green pepper into slices.
Add pepper and onions to meat. Continue cooking 30 minutes or until meat is tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Drain fruit.
Mix all but marshmallows.
Add marshmallows right before serving.

title: bacon and corn casserole
directions: Brown bacon; break in large pieces.
Cook onion in 2 tablespoons drippings.
Cook 5 minutes.
Stir in corn, milk and seasonings.
Bake 10 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat
eggs
until
thick
and add corn.
Combine flour, pepper and
salt.
Stir
milk into dry ingredients.
Blend in butter. Combine
with
corn
mixture.
Beat
well
by hand or electric mixer.
Pour into greased 1 1/2 quart casserole dish. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Pudding is done when knife is inserted in middle comes out clean.

title: garlic bread
directions: Crush the garlic with the salt to a smooth paste and put in a bowl with the pepper, butter and herbs; cream well.
Cut the loaf along in 1-inch slices to within 1/2 inch of the bottom.
Spread the slices on each side with the garlic butter and press together again.
Wrap in foil.

title: small family dinner rolls
directions: In a large mixing bowl, dissolve the yeast in water.
Stir in sugar, salt and half the flour; beat until smooth.
Add the egg, Crisco and remaining flour.
Scrape down the sides of the bowl and cover; let rise in a warm place until doubled, approximately 45 minutes.
Grease muffin tins.
Punch dough down.
Turn out on floured surface and press flat.
Cut with a cutter or shape into clover leaves.
Place in tins and let rise again.
Sprinkle with seed.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: homemade biscuits
directions: Mix flour and sugar; cut in shortening until mixed well.
Add milk; mix well.
Flour hands.
Place large spoonful of dough into hand; knead back and forth.
Place on greased cookie sheet and bake at 500° for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: garbanzo salad
directions: Rinse garbanzos in cold water. Combine with other ingredients and allow to stand in refrigerator for several hours. Serves 3-4.

title: braised liver and onions
directions: Roll liver in flour.
Brown on both sides and put in baking pan.
Saute onion in butter.
Cover liver with onions and then pour bouillon over liver.
Do not cover completely.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° until fork-tender.
Salt to taste.

title: easy boston cream pie
directions: Put one cake layer on serving plate. Spread with pudding to within 1/2-inch of outer edge. Top with second cake layer, pressing down firmly. Combine semi-sweet chocolate pieces and evaporated milk in small saucepan. Stir over medium heat until chocolate is melted and mixture is smooth. Spread chocolate mixture on top layer. Keep at room temperature until ready to serve.

title: three weeks slaw
directions: Let cabbage, bell pepper, onions and sugar stand while preparing oil, vinegar, celery seed and salt.
Bring oil mixture to a boil.
While hot, pour over cabbage mixture and stir.
Will keep for 3 weeks in refrigerator.

title: everything cake
directions: Melt butter in baking pan.
Mix flour, baking powder, sugar and salt.
Add egg and milk to mixture and pour into baking pan. Drop in any kind of fruit.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until brown.

title: oreo cookie dessert
directions: Spread 3/4 of Oreos in the bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour melted butter or oleo over crushed Oreos.
Mix cream cheese and powdered sugar until well blended.
Mix milk and pudding in blender.
Mix cream cheese and powdered sugar mixture and milk and pudding mixture together; fold in Cool Whip.
Pour over Oreos in pan.
Sprinkle remaining Oreos on top and chill.

title: borscht(served cold, yields about 7 cups)
directions: Place first 5 vegetables and water into a large saucepan or soup kettle.
Bring to a boil and gently simmer, covered, 20 to 25 minutes.
Add margarine, stock, cabbage and vinegar and simmer until vegetables are tender.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Serve as is or put mixture into a blender and blend until smooth.
Chill and serve garnished with a tablespoon of sour cream and cucumber or fresh dill, as desired.

title: apple crunch
directions: Put apples in deep, buttered baking dish.
Add 1/2 cup water. Mix cinnamon, flour, sugar and butter with pastry blender or fork; pat over the apples.
Bake at 350° until the crust is brown and apples are tender, about 30 minutes.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Cream together margarine, brown sugar and salt. Stir in corn syrup, well beaten eggs and vanilla. Turn into pastry. Sprinkle pecan halves over mixture. Bake in 450° oven for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° and bake until firm. Cool before serving.

title: pineapple fluff(icebox dessert)
directions: Beat Eagle Brand milk and juice of lemons until thick, then you add the rest of the ingredients. Pour into crust.

title: easy company breakfast or brunch casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Mix remaining ingredients together and add to sausage.
Pour into 2 quart casserole dish and refrigerate overnight.
Next morning bake in 350° oven for 40 to 50 minutes.
May be cooked immediately.

title: darlings(a bar cookie)
directions: Mix mixture together and press into a square pan.

title: refrigerator pickle
directions: This is a crunchy pickle.
There is no cooking and it keeps indefinitely.

title: easy pineapple cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed.
Pour into 2 (9-inch) greased round layer pans.
Bake at 350° for 28 to 33 minutes.
Cool for 10 minutes.
Combine Cool Whip, pineapple and pudding mix.
Spread on cake and store in refrigerator.

title: zesty mexican dip
directions: Saute onions, celery and bell pepper in bacon fat for 5 minutes, until limp but not brown.
Add black beans, chicken stock and ham hocks; cook until the beans are almost done.
Add rice and cook until rice is tender (about 20 minutes).
Add seasonings and vinegar.
Serve with chopped onion.

title: almond lemon chicken
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Beat in 5 tablespoons of oil. Add chicken and marinate 1 hour at room temperature.
In a large skillet, saute almonds in 1/2 tablespoon of oil until golden. Remove and reserve.
Wipe out pan.
Drain chicken.
Reserve marinade.
Cook chicken over high heat in remaining 1 tablespoon of oil until brown on each side, 6 to 10 minutes total or until just tender.
Remove chicken.
Strain marinade into pan.
Add chicken broth and cornstarch mixture.
Cook over high heat, stirring occasionally, until sauce reduces by half, about 5 minutes.
Add marmalade and stir over medium heat until melted. Stir in butter, parsley and red pepper.
Return chicken to pan. Heat through and add almonds.

title: beef and tators
directions: Cook hamburger until crumbly.
Put in 2-quart casserole.
Top with onions and Tater Tots.
Mix soups and green chilies together. Spoon over hamburger mixture.
Cook 30 minutes at 350°.
Turn dish once.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or cream of chicken

title: cabbage roll soup
directions: Saute beef in large soup pot; drain. Add onions, cinnamon, allspice, salt and pepper to taste. Cook until vegetables are yellow. Stir in broth, water and tomatoes. Cover and simmer 30 to 45 minutes. Add rice. Cover and remove from heat. Let stand 15 minutes. This recipe makes 6 to 8 servings, but I like to double it and freeze half. It freezes very well and it's always nice to have some on hand for cold evenings when you don't feel like cooking.

title: chocolate chocolate chip cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat thoroughly.

title: chocolate chip pudding cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together (it doesn't matter what order). Put on a greased pan in a 375° oven for 20 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix together and put in buttered casserole dish.
Cook at 350° covered for 1 hour.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix ingredients together and bake in unbaked pie shell (9-inch) at 350°.

title: banana pudding
directions: Heat milk on medium heat.
Add eggs.
Bring to a boil.
Mix in sugar and flour stirring slowly.
Pour over graham crackers and bananas.
Layer.
Can use vanilla wafers instead of graham crackers.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Mix crumbs and melted butter together and press into pan.
Mix powdered sugar, butter and eggs until smooth.
Spread over crust. Dip banana into juice and layer over sugar mixture.
Spread drained pineapple over bananas, then spread with Cool Whip and garnish with cherries.

title: calico cabbage
directions: Butter bottom and sides of a large casserole dish with portion of the butter.
Mix together all the ingredients in the butter dish and put remaining butter on top.
Cover with lid or foil and bake at 350° for one hour.
Do not add water or any other liquid.
Stir frequently.

title: sticky cauliflower
directions: Break cauliflower into small flowerets.
Cook to crisp-tender and drain.
In a wide skillet, melt butter enough to coat flowerets.
Spread cauliflower in pan and roll with spatula to coat all.
Sprinkle with pepper and sprinkle with a tablespoon or more of flour.
Roll again to make sure all are coated.
It becomes a little sticky.

title: "watch your weight" chocolate pie
directions: Mix well the peanut butter, honey, and Rice Krispies, pressing into a pie pan. Slice bananas over the crust. Mix chocolate pudding with milk; pour over banana slices and chill 30 minutes. Spread Cool Whip over top.

title: cream of cauliflower soup
directions: Make broth from bouillon cubes, enough to cook vegetables.
Add vegetables.
Cook until tender.
When the vegetables are done, add the margarine, pancake batter and sour cream.
Sprinkle with parsley flakes.
Simmer for 5 minutes longer.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Simmer chicken breasts until tender in water seasoned to taste with salt, pepper, onion, carrot and bay leaf.
Cool and cut in bite size pieces.
Saute celery and onions in butter. Mix with chicken soup, water chestnuts, mushrooms and mayonnaise.
Pour into 3-quart oblong casserole.
Top with unrolled crescent roll dough, stretching to cover casserole.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake 30 minutes in 350° oven.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: peanut butter pizzas
directions: Spread each bread half with 1 tablespoon peanut butter.
Top each with 1 tablespoon tomato sauce.
Sprinkle each with 2 tablespoons cheese.
Broil 6-inches from source of heat, 2 to 3 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Makes 2 servings.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook noodles as package directs; drain, then toss with 2 tablespoons oil until well coated.
In skillet, brown ground beef, then drain very well.
Add salt, pepper and spaghetti sauce and stir well.
Combine cottage cheese with sour cream.
Arrange half of noodles in 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish; cover with half of meat-sauce mixture, next a layer of cheese slices (using 1 package); then all of cottage cheese mixture.
Top with remaining noodles, then rest of Mozzarella in 1/2-inch strips, laid "lattice-fashion" across top.
Then spoon rest of meat-sauce mixture into lattice spaces.
Cover tightly with Saran or foil and refrigerate.
About a half hour before serving, start heating oven to 350°.
Brush surface of cheese strips with oil.
Bake 30 minutes or until cheese melts and is golden.

title: frozen biscuits(from friend vivian ballard, amarillo, texas)
directions: Mix thoroughly all dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening as if making a pie crust.
Add sour cream.
Mix thoroughly.
Roll out dough; cut into biscuits.
Place on a cookie sheet and freeze. Place frozen biscuits in bag and use as needed.
When ready to bake, butter both top and bottom of biscuits.
Bake in a 450° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
(The biscuits do not need to be thawed before baking.)

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar, add eggs one at a time.
Add dry ingredients then bananas and nuts.
Put in a lightly greased and floured loaf pan.
