Bake in moderate oven for 40-60 minutes.
Test with toothpick-when toothpick comes out clean, bread is done.

title: williamsburg chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except potato chips.
Just before baking, add 3/4 bag chips (crumbled) and mix.
Crumble the remainder of chips and place on top of mixture which has been placed in casserole.
Bake in 450° oven for 15 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: green tomato relish
directions: Grind tomatoes, peppers and onions.
Squeeze out juice.
Add vinegar, sugar and spices.
Mix well.

title: tabooley(wheat garden salad)
directions: Combine vegetables in large bowl.
Squeeze wheat dry and add to vegetables.
Add lemon juice and rind (optional).
Add olive oil.
Add salt and pepper (I like fresh ground) as for any salad. Toss lightly with 2 large spoons.

title: crab cakes
directions: Beat egg; add crab and butter.
Mix gently.
Refrigerate for 1/2 hour to firm up.
Form into patties.
Saute in butter until brown.
Serve with potato or pasta salad.

title: southern peanut pie
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Beat well; add peanuts.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, then lower heat to 350° for approximately 30 minutes.
Serve at room temperature. Serves 8 to 10.
Top with Cool Whip and chopped peanuts.

title: german skillet beans
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; reserve drippings in pan.
Crumble bacon; set aside.
Saute onion in drippings until tender.
Add bacon and remaining ingredients.
Simmer 5 to 10 minutes or until thickened and heated thoroughly, stirring occasionally.
Makes about 4 servings.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Let eggs, butter and milk set out to get room temperature. Beat eggs and margarine real well with sugar.
Mix food coloring, water, cocoa and salt in a cup.
Add alternately flour and buttermilk.
Dissolve baking soda in vinegar in cup.
Stir in with a spoon.
Do not beat.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch cake pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chocolate refrigerator cake
directions: Line straight-sided loaf pan, 11 x 4 x 2 1/2-inch, with waxed paper, leaving overhang.
Separate ladyfingers.
Place 8 halves in a row in bottom of pan.

title: barbecued meatballs
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients in bowl, mixing well.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place in shallow baking pan.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Heat barbecue sauce in chafing dish; add meatballs. Makes 10 servings.

title: strawberry-pecan torte
directions: Make cake as directed on package, substituting the egg yolks for eggs required.
Spoon cake batter into 3 buttered and floured 9-inch square cake pans.

title: marshmallow krispie bars
directions: Bake brownies in a 13 x 9-inch pan per package directions. Remove from oven and place marshmallows on top.
Return to oven for 3 minutes.
Combine chips, peanut butter and butter in saucepan.
Cook on low heat until smooth.
Add rice cereal and mix well.
Spread mixture over marshmallows and refrigerate until chilled.
If you use Kraft brand marshmallows, don't use the entire bag, only about 3/4 bag.

title: open-faced burger
directions: In a skillet
with lid, brown hamburger meat and onion. When slightly browned,
and well broken apart, add chili sauce and beans.
Simmer
covered
for 15 minutes.
Serve on toasted half of bun.

title: christmas mix
directions: Melt chocolate in a double boiler and pour over cereal mix. Mix all together and cool.

title: french toast
directions: Heat margarine or butter in skillet over medium heat until melted.
Dip bread into egg mixture.
Cook until golden brown, about 4 minutes on each side.

title: fall punch
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Slice lemon and lime and put them in punch.
I freeze some of the apple and cranberry juice into cubes ahead of time so punch is not diluted by ice.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Let cream cheese and butter stand until room temperature.
Mix all ingredients together until smooth.

title: carrot cake
directions: Cream together oil, sugar and eggs. Add flour, cinnamon and carrots. Pour into 4 (8 or 9 inch) pans or 13 x 9 inch pan. Bake at 350° until done. Test with a toothpick.

title: sauerkraut dumplings(hungarian recipe)
directions: Grate potatoes; add egg and salt with enough flour to make a thick dough.
Drop by tablespoon into a pot of boiling water. Cook about 10 minutes.
Drain.
Rinse with cold water.
Melt shortening in large frying pan.
Add drained sauerkraut.
Brown. Add dumplings.
Cook until dumplings are heated through, about 10 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: hm, hm, salsa by vinnie
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl except small can tomato sauce. Pour into blender and blend slowly to desired thickness (blend in 3 to 4 small batches at a time).
Mix in bowl and add some tomato sauce until desired consistency.
Enjoy with regular or fat-free chips.

title: hershey's almond torte
directions: Melt Hershey, marshmallows and milk in double boiler.
Cool in refrigerator.
Whip 1/2 pint whipping cream.
Fold cooled ingredients into whipped cream.
Line square Pyrex with crushed vanilla wafers.
Place whipped cream and cooled ingredients over crushed wafers.
Sprinkle wafers over top.
Refrigerate.

title: tortellini soup
directions: Toss stew beef with a couple of tablespoons of flour until covered.
In a large soup pot, add a little vegetable oil and brown beef.
When beef is browned, add to pot, beans, tomatoes, salt, pepper, beef broth, and Italian seasoning.
Add a little water if needed to make sure meat and beans are covered.
Bring to boil, lower heat, cover and simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
A half hour before serving, fill second pot with 4 quarts of salted water and bring to a boil.
Add tortellini and frozen vegetables.
Reduce heat to medium and cook till tortellini and vegetables are tender (about 10 minutes).
Stir occasionally.
When done, drain and add to beef mixture.
Simmer another 5 minutes.
Serve and garnish with grated cheese.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Wash peppers. Remove stalk ends and seeds. Parboil gently in boiling salted water for 10 minutes. Drain. Melt butter in saucepan. Add flour and mix well; cook 1 minute. Add milk and stir until boiling. Combine this sauce with salt, pepper, ketchup, meat and well drained corn. Fill the peppers and sprinkle with breadcrumbs. Place into a greased ovenproof dish with stock or water. Bake in moderate oven until tender.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown pork chops in frying pan.
Remove chops from pan and add cream of mushroom soup, milk, onion and green peppers to the drippings from pork chops.
Heat.
Put potatoes in casserole.
Pour soup mixture over potatoes.
Place pork chops in top.
Cover.
Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Place in large mixing bowl and mix with slotted spoon the flour, soda, salt, cinnamon, sugar, pecan nuts and raisins.
Make a well.
Into this well, put zucchini, beaten eggs and Crisco oil. Stir carefully until all ingredients are mixed.

title: garlic mashed potatoes
directions: Cover the potatoes with water and cook until tender.
Heat cream with butter.
Add garlic with skin removed.
Place everything in food mill or a ricer and process. Season and serve. Makes 6 servings.

title: radishes:  as a veggie!
directions: Remove stems and leaves.
Clean and wash radishes and leaves if you like mustard green flavor.
Cover radishes (and leaves, if desired) with chicken broth.
Drain and serve.
(Butter and season to taste.)
I personally like the greens too!

title: stuffed zucchini
directions: Cut zucchini and squash in half lengthwise.
Scoop out seeds and pulp, leaving a 1/4-inch shell.
Chop seeds and pulp and set aside.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients.
Use only half of sauce.
Place in a loaf pan; top with the rest of the sauce.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix and and fold in Cool Whip.
Put in graham cracker crust.

title: jambalaya
directions: Saute in large skillet bacon, onion and green pepper.
Add mushrooms, tomatoes, tomato sauce, garlic, broth, rice, fish, shrimp and season.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: tortilla soup
directions: Dissolve bouillon cubes in boiling water in large soup pot. Stir in chicken and cumin.
Simmer over low heat 2 hours.
Heat oil in saucepan.
Add green pepper, onion and garlic.
Saute until tender.
Stir into soup pot.
Add consomm, tomatoes, tomato sauce and green chilies.
Mix well.
Blend cornstarch with 1 tablespoon soup liquid.
Stir into soup.
Simmer 1 to 2 hours or until heated through, stirring occasionally.
Add salt and pepper.
In individual serving bowl, top with tortilla chips, shredded Monterey Jack cheese, chopped onion or chopped avocado if you like.

title: light brown glaze
directions: Heat margarine in 1 1/2 quart saucepan over medium heat, just until delicate brown in color. Stir in powdered sugar, vanilla and milk until smooth.

title: special days fruit salad
directions: Drain and reserve liquid from pineapple and mandarin oranges. Mix all fruits and pecans in large bowl and toss.
In separate bowl, combine the vanilla pudding mix, Tang and reserved fruit juices.
Whip to make a thick sauce.
Pour over fruit and allow to set in refrigerator overnight.
Makes 12 to 14 servings.

title: sour cream-chicken casserole
directions: Layer half of stuffing mix and half of butter in the bottom of a 2 quart casserole dish.
In a medium bowl, mix sour cream and soups, spoon over stuffing.
Top sour cream mixture with chicken. In a medium bowl, mix together remaining stuffing and butter; spread over chicken.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.
Make 6 to 8 servings.

title: cinnamon carrots
directions: Cook carrots in boiling water 10 minutes.
Drain.
Melt margarine in skillet.
Heat carrots and parsley thoroughly. Sprinkle with remaining ingredients.
Stir and cook 1 additional minute.
Serves 4.

title: chocolate drop cookies
directions: Using a heavy boiler, cook milk and cocoa.
Stir until smooth. Add sugar and salt.
Stir until it boils.
Cook to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and add butter and vanilla.
Don't stir. Set aside to cool.
Stir in other ingredients.
Drop by spoonful onto wax paper until hardened.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake in 9 x 12-inch baking pan for 35 minutes at 350°.
Makes 2 dozen brownies.

title: potato balls
directions: Roll mashed potatoes into several balls.
Beat eggs and then roll potato balls in the eggs and then in the bread crumbs.
Fry in hot oil in frying pan.

title: scallops italienne
directions: Cut scallops in half.
Heat wine, water, bay leaves, peppercorns and salt in 10-inch skillet.
Add scallops.
Simmer 2 to 3 minutes until scallops are cooked through.
Remove with slotted spoon.
Bring liquid to boil and heat until reduced to 1/2 cup.
Saute mushrooms in 2 tablespoons butter, 2 to 5 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients and roll into balls, then crisscross with fork.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: golden brown turkey recipe
directions: Okay, now I have your attention with the title of the recipe; well it is the truth.
No matter what size turkey you have, no matter whether it is frozen or fresh, free range or grocery store no-name brand, this recipe works!!!!

title: hardees biscuits
directions: Blend Crisco with flour and other ingredients.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.

title: snowflake salad
directions: Whip cream cheese in bowl until fluffy.
Whip dry whipped dessert topping and vanilla until thick and fluffy.
Add cream cheese to whipped topping and mix well.
Fold in drained fruit and marshmallows.
Place in refrigerator for 30 minutes, then garnish with cherries.

title: heavenly pudding
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Put all in blender and mix well.
Refrigerate or drink as is.
Makes 1 serving.

title: peanut butter things
directions: Cook sugar, syrup and peanut butter to full boil in saucepan. Add cereal to mixture in pan mixing thoroughly to coat evenly. Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper or lightly oiled cookie sheet. Let set until firm enough to handle.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix raw sausage with dry biscuit mix.
Add cheese and knead. Shape into small balls and bake 15 to 20 minutes in a 350° oven on well-greased cookie sheet.
They can be frozen before or after baking.

title: lavender jelly
directions: Combine flowers and apple juice. Bring to boil. Remove from heat. Cover and steep 15 minutes. Strain. Return 2 cups juice to heat. Add sugar and bring to rolling boil. Stir in pectin. Boil 1 minute. Pour into sterilized jars. Seal.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine flour, soda, salt and cinnamon in a large mixing bowl. Add eggs and oil, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened. Do not beat.
Stir in vanilla, butter flavoring, pineapple, 1 cup pecans and bananas.

Spoon batter into three 9-inch round, greased and floured cake pans. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean. Cool in pans for 10 minutes; remove from pans and cool completely. Spread frosting between layers and on top and sides of cake, then sprinkle 1/2 cup chopped pecans on top.
Refrigerate.
Let set 24 hours after baking.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Place sliced berries in baked pie shell. Chill. Cook in medium saucepan the Mountain Dew or 7-Up, cornstarch and sugar. Stir constantly until thick and transparent.
Add water and Jell-O. When mixture is cool and starting to set, pour over berries in shell.
Chill until set.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: squash dressing
directions: Stir all ingredients together.
Add salt and pepper.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown hamburger and sausage.
Add garlic, 1 tablespoon parsley, 1 tablespoon basil, 1 teaspoon salt, tomatoes and tomato paste. Simmer until thick, about 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Boil noodles, drain and rinse.
Combine cottage cheese, eggs, 1 teaspoon salt, pepper, 2 tablespoons parsley flakes and 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese.
Place half the noodles in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Add half the cottage cheese mixture, then 1/2 the meat mixture; repeat.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 375°.

title: no fail pie crust
directions: Blend flour, sugar and salt.
Cut in shortening until particles are the size of peas.
Beat egg; blend in vinegar and cold water.
Sprinkle over flour mixture a tablespoon at a time, tossing with fork to mix.
Gather dough together with fingers. Divide into small sections and wrap to freeze if desired.
Makes 5 (9-inch) crusts.

title: chocolate peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine in heavy saucepan corn syrup, cream, sugar, cocoa and butter.
Cook over medium heat until mixture forms a semi-hard ball in cold water (248°).
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter, marshmallow cream, vanilla and nuts.
Beat until thick; pour into buttered pan.

title: rice pudding
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients.
Add scalded milk and melted butter.
Mix well.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until mixture is firm.
Makes 6 servings.

title: venison delight
directions: Soak steak in salt water overnight.
Pound until tender. Sprinkle with salt, pepper and meat tenderizer.
Let stand 30 minutes. Beat egg and milk together. Dip steak in mixture. Dredge in flour.
Fry quickly in oil.
Arrange in deep casserole.
Place diced onions on top.
Make gravy with drippings and flour.
Pour over steak.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until onions are done.
Yields 8 servings.

title: avocado with sauce
directions: Heat in top of double boiler all except avocado. Cut avocado in half (unpeeled and seeded). Place on plate and fill cavity with warm sauce. Eat with spoon (you get more that way).

title: sausage crescents meat pies
directions: Cook sausage (crumbled).
Add onion, raisins, olives and chili and garlic powders to taste.
When cooked, process meat until raisins are ground small.
Cut crusts into circles (24).
Put 1 teaspoon meat mixture in circle and fold over to seal with fork. Brush tops with beaten egg to make brown.
Put on cookie sheet (Pam sprayed) and bake at 350° about 12 minutes.

title: gingerbread bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray a 12 1/2 x 8-inch baking pan with vegetable spray.
In a large bowl, beat margarine at medium speed until creamy.
Add brown sugar and beat at high speed.
Beat in egg whites; add molasses in separate bowl.
Sift together flours, dry skim milk powder, baking powder, baking soda, ginger, cinnamon, nutmeg and cloves.
Add sifted ingredients to margarine mixture and blend thoroughly.
Stir in nuts and mix well.
Place the dough in the center of the prepared pan.
Using a spatula, spread dough evenly in pan.
Place pan on center rack.
Bake for 25 minutes.

title: smoked venison
directions: Place meat in smoker at low temperature for 2 hours.
Lay a large oven roasting bag in a large pan, allowing room for expansion.
Place meat in bag, liberally sprinkle with garlic. Slice pepper and onion into strips; lay equal portions on meat and in bottom of bag.
Pour soy sauce on meat.
Pour water in bottom of bag and seal according to bag directions.
Preheat oven to 350° and cook for one hour.
By using the roasting bag the steam will put moisture back in the meat.

title: chocolate covered cherries
directions: Melt margarine. Add Eagle Brand milk. Mix together. Add powdered sugar and mix. Put mixture in fridge until cold and stiff enough to work with (about 2 hours). Drain cherries. Wrap the mixture around the cherries.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil margarine, sugar and milk for 8 minutes, stirring constantly.
Take off stove.
Add vanilla and peanut butter.
Now add marshmallow cream.
Stir well.
Pour in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: impossible chicken 'n broccoli pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 10 x 1 1/2-inch pie plate.
Rinse broccoli under running cold water to thaw; drain thoroughly.
Mix broccoli, 2 cups cheese, chicken and onion in plate.
Beat milk, eggs, baking mix, salt and pepper until smooth, 15 seconds in blender on high.
Pour into plate.
Bake until knife inserted comes clean, 25 to 35 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake 1 to 2 minutes until cheese melts.
Cool.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers and onions thin.
Put in a plastic or china bowl in layers.
Sprinkle salt between the layers, light on salt. Cover with a plate and weight it down with a heavy object.
Let stand for 1 hour or overnight.
Rinse and drain.
Put all in a big pan and stir to mix.
Simmer for a few minutes.
Stir often.
Put hot into pint jars (scalded) and put airtight lids on jars.

title: soul baked beans
directions: Brown ground beef, onions
and
pepper in skillet.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into baking dish and bake at 350° for about 20 minutes or
until mixture is bubbly.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: 100 year old tea cakes
directions: Mix butter, sugar and egg to a creamy mixture.
Add dry ingredients and milk.
Mix well until dough is stiff, then add a little flour, if needed.

title: prune cake
directions: Mix together and bake at 325° for 25 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Make icing and pour on warm cake.

title: quick 'n tasty nacho dip
directions: Spread the cream cheese in the bottom of a 9-inch pie plate. Spoon chili over cream cheese. Cover with shredded cheese and then toppings of your choice.
Microwave for about 3 to 3 1/2 minutes or until cheese melts or place in oven preheated to 350° until cheese melts.

title: sweet potatoes
directions: Place sweet potatoes in a casserole.
Mix rest of ingredients and pour over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: confetti omelette
directions: Fry bacon and crumble.
Cook onion until tender and add mushrooms.
Combine rest of ingredients, except cheese.
Toss cheese with flour.
Then add to egg mixture.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake 40 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: spicy salt substitute
directions: Combine ingredients.
Put in blender and mix well.

title: lemon pie filling
directions: Mix in saucepan the sugar, cornstarch and water.
Cook over moderate heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils.
Boil for 1 minute.
Slowly stir 1/2 of the hot mixture into egg yolks.
Mix well and add rest of mixture.
Boil 1 minute longer.
Remove from heat; continue stirring until smooth.
Blend in butter, lemon juice and rind.
Put in prepared crust and cover with meringue* and bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: pasta salad
directions: Dice vegetables; add to cooked spaghetti.
Add Italian dressing and Salad Surprise to suit your taste.
Toss together. Chill overnight.

title: hamburger noodle bake
directions: Layer uncooked noodles in bottom of buttered casserole.
Brown hamburger and onions; mix with all other ingredients except cheese.
Pour over noodles.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes. Top with grated Cheddar cheese or slices.
Serves 12.

title: potato souffle
directions: Peel potatoes and cook in water until tender.
Mash potatoes, using mixer.
Beat in 3 tablespoons butter and cream.
Melt remaining butter in skillet.
Add onion; saute until tender.
Add sauteed onion to whipped potatoes.
Season and cool.
Beat egg yolks into cooled potatoes.
Beat egg whites until stiff, not dry. Fold into potatoes.
Generously grease casserole dish.
Spoon in potato mixture.
Sprinkle top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake, uncovered, for 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Place under broiler for 4 to 5 minutes to brown.

title: easy cherry cream pie
directions: Whip together cream cheese, sugar and vanilla. Fold in whipped cream. Pour into shell and chill several hours.
Spoon on cherry topping and chill until served.

title: congo cookies
directions: Melt butter and add sugar.
Cool.
Beat in 1 egg at a time. Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Spread in greased 10 x 15 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cheesy swirls
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In small bowl combine cream cheese, onion and milk and mix
well.
Separate
dough
into 4 rectangles. Firmly press perforations
to
seal.
Spread
about
2 teaspoons cheese mixture
on	each
rectangle.
Sprinkle
with bacon.
Roll up at longest side	and seal.
Cut each roll into 8 slices.
Place on cooking sheet.
Bake
at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Sprinkle top with cheese.

title: sinful pie
directions: Melt oleo and mix with flour and pecans.
Press into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 375° until golden brown.
Let cool.
Then mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and half the Cool Whip.
Spread over cool crust.
Mix pudding and milk.
Spread over cream cheese mixture.
Refrigerate.
When set, put remaining Cool Whip on top. Sprinkle with chopped pecans, just enough to make it pretty.

title: cowboy cornbread
directions: Mix all together with Buttermilk until right consistency. Spread 1/2 of mixture in greased pan.
Then spread Onions over the mixture.
Spread the Jalapeno Peppers over the mixture.
Add the Mozzarella Cheese over the onions and peppers.
Cover with remainder of cornmeal mixture.
Sprinkle the Oil over top.
You can add more shredded cheese to top.
Bake for 1 hour at 350.

title: baked chicken with rice
directions: Spread rice evenly in bottom of 9 x 9 x 2-inch nonstick baking dish.
Sprinkle with 1/4 of onion mix.
Place chicken on top of rice.
Add remaining onion soup mix.

title: 5-flavor cake
directions: Cream margarine, shortening and sugar until light and fluffy. Add eggs, which have been beaten.
Combine flour and baking powder; add to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Stir in flavorings.
Pour into 10-inch tube pan and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until cake tests done.
Cool about 10 minutes before turning out.

title: ground beef pepper steak
directions: Mix ground beef, salt and pepper in bowl.
Shape into patties. Brown quickly on both sides in margarine in skillet.
Remove patties to hot platter.
Combine green peppers, garlic and soy sauce in skillet.
Cook, stirring constantly for 2 to 3 minutes.

title: coconut pie
directions: In pot, add beaten egg yolks, milk, sugar, cornstarch, margarine, salt, and vanilla.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until thick.
Remove from heat. Add coconut.
Mix well. Pour into a baked pie crust.

title: rachel's polish sausage meal
directions: In skillet, saute chopped onion in oil for 5 minutes.
Add white beans (drained).
Add tomatoes (juice, too) and dill weed. Simmer 5 minutes.
Chop tomatoes and add sausage, sliced in 1/4-inch rounds.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.

title: spinach balls
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Form into bite-size balls.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Can be frozen and re-warmed at 350°.
Serve on tray or chafing dish. Yields 100 balls.

title: baked sandwiches
directions: Mix ingredients together and spread on hamburger buns.
Wrap each bun in aluminum foil and bake 15 minutes at 300°.

title: extra easy beef fajitas
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Cut beef into 1/2-inch strips.
Mix beef, lime juice, garlic powder and pepper.
Wrap tortillas in foil. Heat in oven about 15 minutes or until warm.
Cut bell peppers into strips.
Cut onion into slices; separate into rings.
Spray 10-inch skillet with cooking spray.
Cook and stir onion in skillet 1 minute.
Add bell peppers.
Cook and stir 2 minutes.
Add beef mixture and beans.
Cook and stir about 3 minutes or until beans are hot.
Fill warm tortillas with hot beef mixture.
Serve with yogurt and salsa.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Melt butter in heavy pan, one with tight fitting lid.
Add onion and saute about 2 minutes until translucent, not brown.
Add rice, stirring to coat grains with butter; cook until translucent. Pour in stock.
Add salt and pepper, bring to boil over high heat and immediately cover with lid.
Reduce heat and simmer 23 minutes. Remove lid and fluff.

title: debbie's heavenly hash squares
directions: Melt chocolate chips and butter with the Eagle Brand milk in top of a double boiler.
In large bowl, place the marshmallows and peanuts and fold in the melted chocolate mixture.
Pour into oblong pan lined with waxed paper.
Chill for approximately 1 1/2 hours and remove from refrigerator and slice.
After slicing, return to refrigerator for 30 minutes.
Take out of pan and place on serving tray.
Do keep refrigerated until ready to serve.

title: cream cheese salad
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Shape into roll; add crumbs to roll.
Freeze.

title: salad dressing for potato salad
directions: Put the vinegar, water and dry mustard in a saucepan to heat. When it begins to boil, stir in the eggs that have been beaten with the flour.
Add the cream, salt and sugar.
Stir constantly until the mixture thickens.
Cool.
Before using, dilute with milk or cream to desired thickness.
Keeps well in refrigerator.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Put broccoli spears and chicken in casserole.
Mix cream cheese, mushroom soup, milk and Cheddar cheese.
Pour over broccoli.
Top with cornflake crumbs.
Add Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with cooked rice.

title: potato filling
directions: Brown onions and celery in margarine.
Add bread; add more margarine if necessary.
Mix instant potatoes as instructed on box, except very wet.
Add first 4 ingredients to potatoes.
Bake at 350°.

title: grilled marinated chicken breasts
directions: Early in day, mix marinade ingredients; pour over chicken. Cover and refrigerate.
Marinate at least 2 hours.
Remove chicken from marinade.
Grill for 15 minutes (approximately) or until all pink is gone.

title: mom's barbecue chicken
directions: Cook and bone chickens (save broth).
Saute celery and onions in butter or margarine.
Combine remaining ingredients in a saucepan; heat for 5 minutes.
Combine sauce, sauteed vegetables and chicken in electric frypan.
Simmer, breaking up chicken. Serve over snowflake rolls, biscuits, etc., or directly on plate.

title: cheesy ham nuggets
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Mix well with fork.
Cut ham into 20 (1-inch) cubes.
Dip in batter mixture.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: pimento cheese spread
directions: Grate cheese (which is at room temperature) on small section of grater.
Mash pimento so that it will blend with the finely grated cheese.
Mix with just enough mayonnaise to hold together and spread easily.
Add hot sauce, if desired.
Enjoy.

title: lentils and rice
directions: Soak lentils overnight.
Drain.
Boil in 2 quarts of fresh water without salt until tender (about half an hour).
Add washed, uncooked rice and the salt and boil another 20 minutes.
Brown the sliced onions in olive oil.
Add onions and half the oil to the lentil-rice mixture and cook another 15 minutes over a low flame until the water is absorbed.
This can be cooked ahead and is eaten at room temperature.

title: hash brown quiche
directions: Grease 9-inch pie plate with butter.
Press thawed hash browns between paper towels to remove excess moisture.
Spread in pie plate, pressing against bottom and sides to form a solid crust. Brush with melted butter, being careful to brush top edges.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes.
Remove crust from oven and layer diced chiles, onions, Swiss cheese and ham over bottom of crust.
Beat cream and eggs together and pour over cheese and ham.
Return to oven and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until knife inserted near edge comes out clean.

title: chocolate no-bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, salt and cocoa in a pan.
Add butter and milk and bring to a boil.
Boil until small amount forms a soft ball in cold water.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix sugar and margarine.
Add egg and extracts.
Mix thoroughly.
Measure flour; sift dry ingredients together and blend in.
Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours or longer.
Divide dough into balls. Roll out on lightly floured board and cut with cookie cutters (roll thin).
Place on a lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake 7 to 8 minutes at 350°.
Makes 5 dozen cookies.

title: maple-pepper chops
directions: In a large self-sealing bag, mix together the apple juice concentrate, apple cider vinegar, maple syrup, sage, salt and pepper.
Add pork chops and seal bag; refrigerate 4 to 24 hours.

title: mexican salad
directions: Toss together but do not add corn chips and dressing until just before serving.

title: sour cream bars
directions: Pour over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: seven-up fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple, saving juice.
Dissolve jello in 2 cups boiling water.
Add the 7-Up.
When it starts to set, add sliced bananas, pineapple, oranges and marshmallows.
Put in a 9 x 12-inch cake pan or large bowl.
Chill.

title: easy cheese spread
directions: Mix and place in a 3-cup casserole.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Serve on party rye bread.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Place milk, sugar and margarine in saucepan.
When it comes to a boil, reduce heat and let boil 4 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove; add peanut butter and vanilla; beat until it starts to thicken and pour quickly into greased pan.

title: sesame chicken
directions: Mix egg and milk in medium bowl.
Mix dry ingredients in plastic bag.
Dip chicken in egg mixture, then shake in bag. Brush with melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: glazed pecans
directions: Mix ingredients in microwave dish.
Cook in microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Take out and stir.
Cook 4 minutes and stir again. Cook 2 more minutes.
Spread out on aluminum foil to cool.

title: homemade brownies
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Mix everything together.
Bake in a 350° oven until done.

title: pepperoni casserole
directions: Fry pepperoni for a few minutes, then drain on paper towel. Cook noodles as directed.
Cut pepperoni into small pieces.
Mix sauce, cheese, pepperoni and noodles together in casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: mexican mac
directions: Brown hamburger meat until done. Add chili powder to meat and mix in. Add onion and green pepper. Cook until soft. Add tomato sauce and corn. Mix together. Heat to a boil and turn down. Boil macaroni until done. Drain. Place macaroni on plate. Spoon mixture on macaroni. Sprinkle with cheese. Makes 4 servings.

title: mittie's marvelous marshmallow salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and serve.

title: oven fried pork chops
directions: Trim fat from pork chops and set aside.
Combine egg white and next 4 ingredients.
Stir well. Combine bread crumbs, Italian seasonings, paprika and dash of garlic powder. Stir well. Dip chops in egg white mixture. Dredge in bread crumb mixture.
Place chops on a rack in a roasting pan coated with cooking spray. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Turn and bake 25 more minutes or until done.

title: crunchy jumble cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients.
Add Rice Krispies and chocolate chips.
Bake on greased cookie sheets for 12 minutes at 350°.
Should be lightly browned.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Mix well.
Roll out on floured surface.
Cut out cookies with cutter with desired shape.
Bake at 350° for about 6 minutes. Cool.
Decorate with frosting of choice.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Mix ingredients and put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes; cool and crumble.

title: holy cow cake
directions: Bake cake as directed.
Remove from oven; poke holes in cake with fork.
Pour over the hot cake the Eagle Brand milk and caramel ice cream topping.
Let cool completely.
Spread the Cool Whip over cake.
Crush the Heath bars; sprinkle over Cool Whip. Refrigerate cake until ready to serve.

title: old-fashioned cooked cheese the easy way
directions: In top of double boiler, break the cheese into small pieces. Add oleo, milk, flour, caraway seed and salt.
Cook over boiling water until mixture is well blended and smooth.
Makes a good spread on crackers or rye bread.

title: sausage soup
directions: Brown sausage and crumble.
Add onions, spices, tomatoes and broth.
Simmer 1/2 hour.
Add orzo and simmer until orzo is cooked.

title: pecan kiss's
directions: Beat egg white until fluffy.
Add brown sugar and vanilla flavoring.
Dip pecan halves in mixture and place on cookie sheet. Heat oven to 250° and bake for 30 minutes.
Turn oven off and leave in for another 30 minutes.

title: three bean stew with vegetables
directions: Chop the onions and tomatoes.
Peel and slice the carrots 1/4-inch thick.
Seed and mince the jalapenos for a hot and spicy taste.
Heat the oil in a medium size saucepan over medium heat. Add the onions and carrots, reduce heat to low, and simmer, covered, until somewhat tender, about 3 minutes.
Add the tomatoes, jalapenos, corn (frozen or thawed), the beans with their juices, and chilies.
Cover and simmer for as little as 20 minutes just to heat the ingredients or for as long as 45 minutes for a more mellow flavor.
Stir the beans to make sure they are not scorching; add a little water if they are.
Four servings.
Delicious over a bowl of pasta, rice or cornmeal puree.

title: hot spiced pineapple-cranberry punch
directions: Simmer spices, sugar and water together for 10 to 15 minutes. Double strain (to clear) into kettle containing juices and salt. Heat.
Serve from warmed punch bowl.
Yields 12 punch cups.

title: jerky(beef, deer, goat)
directions: Mix all of the ingredients in a large container with cover. Remove from container every day for two days and knead.
After second day, measure out portion (almost soft ball size).
Pat out and place between wax paper, then use rolling pin to roll out to a very thin piece less than 1/4-inch.
Remove top layer of wax paper and place on oven rack face down.
Remove last piece of wax paper. Sprinkle with soul seasoning.
Place rack in oven at 180° for 6 hours or longer.
Meat must be dry, but not hard.
Cool; cut in desired lengths.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: In bottom of large bowl, place 1/2 of lettuce.
Sprinkle with sugar, salt and pepper.
Layer eggs on top of lettuce.
Stand some of the egg slices around the edge, if desired.
Sprinkle generously with salt.
Next, layer in order peas, remaining lettuce, bacon and cheese.
Spread mayonnaise over top, sealing to edge of bowl.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Toss before serving.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Heat oil and cook onion until tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients and bring to boil.
Add spareribs.
Cook 30 minutes, covered, stirring occasionally.
Turn spareribs over and cook 15 to 30 minutes, uncovered.

title: caramel sandwich cookies
directions: In mixer bowl, beat margarine, sugar, cheese, egg yolk, 1/2 teaspoon almond extract, vanilla and salt until well blended.
Add flour; mix well.
Chill 2 hours on floured surface; knead dough to form a smooth ball.
Divide into thirds on floured surface; roll out each portion to 1/8-inch thickness.
Cut into desired shapes. Place on cookie sheets and brush with slightly beaten egg white and sprinkle with colored sugars.
Bake in 375° oven for 7 to 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: ready to eat pickles
directions: Sprinkle salt and celery seed over cucumbers, peppers and onion.
Mix well.
Mix separately 2 cups sugar and 1 cup vinegar. Mix until sugar dissolves.
Pour over cucumber mixture.
Put into jars and cover.
This will keep in refrigerator a month or more.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Mix all ingredients except sauce and 1/4 cup grated Parmesan cheese.
Spoon mixture into cooked shells.
Spray 11 x 14-inch glass dish with nonstick spray.
Pour 1 cup of sauce into dish; place filled shells in dish; cover shells with remaining sauce and Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: potato soup
directions: Dice bacon and fry with onion; drain off fat.
Combine with remaining ingredients.
Heat to boiling point.

title: amaretto apricot chews
directions: Stir together flour and baking soda.
In a large mixer bowl beat butter or margarine until softened.
Add brown sugar and sugar and beat until fluffy.
Add egg and 1 tablespoon Amaretto and beat well.
Add flour mixture and beat until well mixed.
Stir in oats, apricots and almonds.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 375° oven for 8 to 10 minutes or until done.
Cool on cookie sheet for 1 minute, then remove and cool thoroughly.
Stir together powdered sugar and enough of the 2 to 3 tablespoons Amaretto to make an icing of drizzling consistency.
Drizzle over cookies.
Makes about 54.

title: chicken sorrento
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix flour, salt, pepper and parsley flakes; coat chicken breasts with this mixture.
Brown in hot shortening; remove from skillet.
Add mushrooms to skillet; cook and stir about 5 minutes.
Drain off excess fat.
Stir in soup and oregano until smooth.
Remove from heat; stir in sour cream.
Place macaroni in an oblong baking dish, 11 1/2 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/2-inches.
With a fork, lightly mix in peas and half the soup mixture.
Arrange chicken breasts on top; pour remaining soup mixture over chicken.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover and bake for 40 minutes.
Uncover and bake for 20 minutes longer.
Makes 6 servings.

title: hawaiian pancake
directions: Melt the butter in a 12-inch iron skillet until hot, but not burnt, in a 425° oven. Combine flour, milk, eggs and nutmeg.
Beat lightly and leave the batter a little lumpy.
Pour into hot skillet.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with the sugar and lemon juice.
Serve with your favorite topping.
Serves 2.

title: seasoned salt
directions: Mix well and use as salt.
You may also add any herbs to taste:
parsley, thyme, rosemary, oregano, basil or tarragon.

title: jalapeno cornbread muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Combine all ingredients.
Pour into 2 hot 12-cup greased muffin pans (or line with paper baking cups) to 2/3 full.
Bake for 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 24 medium size muffins.

title: 24 hour vegetable salad
directions: Layer lettuce, onion, celery, peas and water chestnuts in order in a 13 x 9-inch dish.
In a small bowl, beat mayonnaise, sugar and milk.
Spread over top.
Refrigerate overnight.
Garnish with boiled eggs, grated cheese and bacon bits.
Can be prepared well ahead of time.

title: tomato topped asparagus
directions: Combine basil, oil, vinegar, salt, sugar and pepper in a jar. Cover tightly and shake vigorously.
Place asparagus in vegetable steamer (over boiling water), cover and steam 4 to 6 minutes. Arrange asparagus on serving platter and sprinkle with chopped tomato.
Drizzle vinaigrette mixture over asparagus.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Combine first 7 ingredients.
Roll into ball.
Refrigerate overnight.
Roll in pecan pieces or pieces of chopped corned beef.

title: easy fruit pie
directions: Melt margarine in pan or baking dish.
Mix sugar, self-rising flour, baking powder and milk.
Add to margarine.
Add fruit and juice on top of batter.
Use fruit and juice that you desire. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: mom's sandwich spread
directions: Grind bologna and cheese together.
Add mayonnaise and relish to taste and to achieve a spreadable consistency.

title: no-bake cheesecake
directions: Mix softened cream cheese, Cool Whip and powdered sugar.
Pour in ready made graham crust.
Refrigerate, then add cherry pie filling on top.

title: cantaloupe-cobbler
directions: Combine all ingredients except cantaloupe.
Pour into a flat baking dish.
Top with cantaloupe.
Bake at 400° until crust floats to the top and is golden brown.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream Crisco, margarine and sugar; add eggs.
Sift soda and baking powder into one cup flour.
Add to sugar mixture.
Add milk and flavoring.
Add flour to form soft dough.
Turn onto floured board.
Roll out to 1/4 inch thick.
Cut into any shape.
Bake about 10 minutes, until brown.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Mix butter, sugar, brown sugar and eggs.
Mix and add flour, baking powder, salt and baking soda.
Add vanilla, oatmeal, cornflakes and coconut and mix well.
Drop by teaspoons on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° to 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: okra casserole
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in butter.
Add flour and mix. Add tomatoes and cheese. Stir until cheese melts. Add spices and okra.
Bake in casserole dish for 20 minutes at 350°.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: egg nog
directions: In a very large bowl, beat egg yolks with sugar at low speed until blended, then at high speed until lemon colored. Fold in milk and nutmeg. Beat egg whites in a medium bowl until soft peaks form. In a separate bowl beat whipping cream until stiff peaks form. Fold both into milk mixture, leaving some lumps. Pour into a chilled punch bowl, sprinkle with additional nutmeg. Makes 19 eight ounce servings or 38 four ounce servings.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Stir sugar and corn syrup together in 1 1/2 quart casserole dish.
Microwave on High for 4 minutes.
Add peanuts.
Stir. Microwave on High 3 to 5 minutes until light brown.
Add butter and vanilla.
Blend well.
Microwave on High for 1 to 2 minutes.
Add baking soda.
Stir until light and foamy.
Spread on buttered cookie sheet.
Work fast because it hardens quickly.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix sugar, margarine and peanut butter well.
Add vanilla and mix until smooth.
Mold into small balls.
Melt wax, add chocolate chips and dip balls in chocolate.
Put on wax paper.

title: pineapple delight
directions: Place bread slices in greased pan.
Cream oleo and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Beat well.
Add pineapple, juice and all. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: butterscotch pudding cake(world war ii, sugarless)
directions: Mix together margarine and pudding mix.
Add eggs and syrup, then milk with soda, then dry ingredients and vanilla.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean when stuck in the middle of cake.

title: cream cheese fudge
directions: Melt cream cheese, butter and milk chocolate chips. Add vanilla and powdered sugar. Mix, then
add walnuts. Put mixture in an 8-inch square waxed paper lined pan. Then refrigerate for 2 to 3 hours.

title: zero salad dressing
directions: Combine ingredients in a jar with a tight fitting lid.
Shake well before using.
Add parsley, green pepper, horseradish or mustard if necessary.
May be used in any amount. Almost no calories.

title: make ahead salad
directions: Cook vegetables as directed on package; drain well.
Combine only vinegar, sugar and salad oil, boil 5 minutes.
While vegetables and dressing are still hot, pour over drained vegetables.
Let cool, then add remaining ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate.
Must be made several days before serving.

title: becca's peanut blossoms
directions: Beat together milk and peanut butter. Add vanilla and Bisquick. Roll into balls and roll balls in sugar. Bake in a 375° oven for 6 to 8 minutes. Take out of oven and press in a chocolate candy Kiss. Remove from cookie sheets and cool completely.

title: chicken ala jeckyl
directions: Cut up ham in bottom of dish.
Put in chicken.
Mix together soup, sour cream, broccoli, mushrooms and onion powder.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 40 minutes.

title: escarole with garlic(esscarola con aglio)
directions: Wash
escarole
thoroughly
in
several changes of cold water. Discard
any
bruised
or tough leaves and drain well. Heat oil in
large skillet and add garlic.
Saute for 1 minute on medium heat.
Do
not
brown garlic.
Add cleaned escarole and the rest of
the ingredients.
Saute on medium heat for 8 to 10 minutes. Serve immediately.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: cracker jacks
directions: Melt oleo.
Add sugar, syrup and salt.
Boil for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add baking soda and vanilla.
Mix well with popcorn.

title: hot turkey salad
directions: Brown 1 1/2 pounds hamburger with chopped onions.
Add 1 can grated spam.
Add 1 pound grated cheese (mozzarella works well). Add 1 quart spaghetti sauce.

title: pasta primavera
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients. Mix well.
Serve chilled.

title: heavenly jam
directions: Bring rhubarb, sugar and pineapple to boiling and boil 20 minutes; stir frequently.
Remove from heat and add Jell-O.
Stir while adding Jell-O.
Bottle.

title: festive egg nog(yields 6 servings)
directions: Blend the eggs until thick and foamy.
Add milk, sugar, vanilla and salt.
Blend well.
Chill thoroughly.
Dust with nutmeg before serving.

title: gold coast pork chops
directions: In skillet, brown chops; pour off fat.
Stir in soup, 1/4 cup water, onions, carrots, pepper and sage.
Cover; simmer for 15 minutes.
Stir occasionally.

title: delicious cookies
directions: Mix in order. Press down with fork and flour. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: fan potatoes
directions: Wash potato and, with skins left on, thinly slice potatoes, but not all the way through.
Put into microwave safe dish.
Pour Italian dressing over potatoes and microwave for 5 minutes on High.
Rotate dish and microwave another 5 minutes.
When done, fan potatoes onto serving dish.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: peach pie
directions: Mix milk, lemon juice and Cool Whip together with a spoon. Add remaining ingredients and pour into two pie shells.
Keep refrigerated.

title: layered dessert
directions: Mix butter, pecans and flour.
Press into 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes, or until golden.
Blend together sugar, Cool Whip and cream cheese.
Spread over cooled crust.
Mix pudding mix with milk.
Spread over cheese mixture. Top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with pecans.

title: peppered pork chops
directions: Sprinkle half of the crushed peppercorns over one side of pork chops; gently press into pork.
Turn pork; repeat with remaining peppercorns.
Heat margarine and oil in 12-inch skillet over medium-high heat.
Cook garlic in margarine and oil, stirring frequently, until golden.
Add pork; cook, uncovered, 5 minutes. Turn pork.
Add mushrooms, salt and apple juice.
Cover and simmer about 5 minutes longer, or until pork is done.

title: squash puppies
directions: Cook and drain squash.
Add flour, cornmeal, onion and egg to squash.
Then add 1/2 cup milk and 1 tablespoon baking powder. Mix.
Drop by spoonfuls into hot oil and bake until brown.

title: corkscrew macaroni salad
directions: Boil mushrooms.
Add peas.
Cover and cook 3 minutes.
Add ham. Heat until broth dissolved and peas tender.
Toss macaroni, pepper and tomato with salad dressing.
Stir in other.
Chill.

title: bayerische vanille creme(bavarian vanilla cream)
directions: Sprinkle gelatin over cold water to soften.
Heat to dissolve gelatin completely.
Mix together sugar and cornstarch.
Add eggs. Beat for 2 minutes.
Slowly add warm milk, beating constantly. Pour into 1-quart saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until custard coats a spoon.
Add gelatin and ice cream while custard is hot. Cool until slightly thickened.
Add vanilla.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into a 1-quart mold.
Chill until set.
Unmold carefully and serve with a garnish of fresh fruits.
Serves 6.

title: easy gourmet steak
directions: Place steak in baking dish.
Season with salt and pepper. Sprinkle with onion soup mix.
Spread on mushroom soup.
Pour wine over top.
Cover and bake at 300° for 3 hours.

title: lemon baby carrots
directions: Scrape and trim baby carrots, leaving 1/2-inch of green tops, if desired.
Arrange carrots in a vegetable steamer over boiling water.
Cover and steam 10 minutes or until crisp-tender. Transfer
carrots
to serving bowl.
Combine lemon juice and remaining ingredients;
stir well.	Pour over carrots and toss gently.
Yield:
4	servings.
(42	calories and 28% fat per serving.)

title: taco dip(low-fat)
directions: Mix all together; spread on tray.
Top with chopped onion, chopped lettuce, low-fat grated Cheddar cheese and sliced tomatoes.
Serve with taco chips.

title: banana shake
directions: In blender container, combine all ingredients except ice; blend well. Gradually add ice, blending until smooth.
Garnish as desired.
Refrigerate leftovers. (Mixture stays thick and creamy in refrigerator.)

title: batter for squash or eggplant
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Dip squash or eggplant in batter, then fry until done.
Drain on paper towels.

title: sure pop popovers
directions: Combine flour, milk, salt and oil.
Beat on high speed for 1 minute.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating 20 seconds after each addition.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground meat, drain fat.
In a deep pan or pot add meat, onion, garlic, tomato paste, tomato sauce and spaghetti mix.
Add 1/2 to 1 cup water.
Stir.
Heat on high until it begins to bubble, then turn on low and simmer for about 45 minutes.
You'll need a deep, oblong pan.
Slightly grease bottom.
Put a layer of noodles, layer of meat and layer of cheeses.
Repeat again.
Turn oven to 350° and cook about 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Beat all ingredients.
Fill rest of freezer with milk.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together well, then pour into 9-inch deep unbaked pie shell.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 50 minutes until center of pie is set.
Garnish with whipped topping or serve plain.

title: golden pecan pie
directions: Combine dry ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Add eggs, syrup, vanilla and oleo; beat with electric mixer until blended. Stir in pecans.
Pour mixture into pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: southern style green beans
directions: Cook green beans until barely tender.

title: fruit pizza(the best)
directions: Mix ingredients until crumbly. Pat into 12-inch round pizza pan. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes. Cool.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Melt butter.
Add cocoa and water.
Mix with mixer; add flour, sugar, vanilla, eggs, 1/2 teaspoon salt and baking soda.
Mix in sour cream.
Pour into ungreased baking pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: ritz snacks
directions: Mix bits and pecans in large bowl.
Heat sugar, butter and Karo, bringing to a boil.
Boil 4 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add soda and vanilla.
Pour mixture in bowl and mix well.
Spread in pan and bake in 200° oven for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes. Spread on wax paper.
Separate into small pieces when cooled.

title: fudge
directions: Melt butter and peanut butter on stove, slowly stirring until smooth.
Take off stove and add 1/2 box of 4x sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Mix until creamy and then add 1/2 box more of 4x sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Mix until creamy.
Pour into greased pan and let set until ready to eat.
Put in refrigerator before cutting.

title: st. nicholas punch
directions: Boil 10 minutes and strain.
Let simmer on stove until used. Smells good during the holidays and tastes good.

title: ginger bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add rest of ingredients.
Mix well. Bake at 350° until done.

title: cod bel-a-vista
directions: Bake fillets in a pan (sheet pan) for 12 minutes at 375°. While cod is baking, slice onion, green pepper and tomato into circles.
Melt butter and saute onion
and pepper until done. Add tomato and cook for 3 minutes (saute in frying pan).
When cod is done, remove from oven and add onion, pepper and tomato.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix eggs and sugar well.
Add remaining ingredients (except nuts and cherries).
Blend thoroughly for 2 minutes with mixer or in processor or beat with spoon.
Add nuts and cherries to mixture, blending with spoon.
Bake in greased and floured three 1 pound loaf pans or large Bundt pan.
May be served with whipped cream cheese or whipped cottage cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Cake is done when it springs back from touch or test with toothpick.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Cube eggplant; soak overnight in water with 1 teaspoon soda or salt.
This removes the bitter taste and black.
Next morning, drain and rinse.
Coat eggplant pieces with milk and cracker crumbs.
Cook in hot grease until browned.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Mix bread pieces and meat.
Add milk and mix.
Beat eggs and add to mixture.
Add salt and pepper.
Then dry mustard and mix. Pour into 9 x 11-inch greased pan and bake 35 minutes at 350°. Mixture can be refrigerated overnight and then bake.
The longer it sets, the better it gets.

title: lon's favorite cobbler
directions: Melt oleo in 9 x 9-inch pan and top with fruit.
Mix other ingredients and pour over fruit.
Sprinkle mixture of 1/4 cup sugar and cinnamon over top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: blueberry pound cake
directions: Grease tube pan with 2 tablespoons of butter.
Sprinkle with 1/4 cup sugar.
Set aside.
Cream 1 cup butter.
Gradually add 2 cups sugar, beating well.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla. Combine 2 3/4 cups flour, baking powder and salt.
Add gradually to creamed mixture.
Dredge blueberries with remaining 1/4 cup flour; stir to coat well.
Fold berries into batter and pour batter into prepared pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until done.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Let cool completely.

title: persian chicken breasts
directions: Flour chicken pieces with flour seasoned with salt and pepper. (I salt and pepper it while I'm browning it.) Brown it on all sides in hot fat.
Remove chicken.
Cook onions in hot fat until golden (or translucent).
Drain off excess fat.
Add remaining ingredients to skillet.
Blend.
Cover.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes. Add browned chicken.
Simmer slow until tender, 1 hour or more.

title: potato latke recipe
directions: Grate potatoes and onion on the fine side of grater, or in food processor or through blender with a little water added to it. Add eggs and mix well.
Add matzo meal and sesaoning and mix well. Heat oil in frying pan, then add mixture 1 tablespoon at a time into frying pan.
When golden brown, turn over and brown other side.

title: orange salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Mix in orange jello, then mix in cottage cheese and Cool Whip.
Chill in refrigerator.

title: easy caramel apple pie
directions: Combine caramel pieces and flour in a milium bowl.
Add apples, caramel topping and lemon juice.
Mix well.
Pour into pie crust.
Top with pecans.
Cut the remaining pie crust into strips.
Place strips on top of pie in criss cross fashion.
Use a fork and crimp to filled pie crust.
Bake on a baking sheet at 375 degrees for 40 - 45 minutes or until crust is brown.
Cool and serve.

title: macaroni-chicken-cantaloupe salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, lemon juice, salt and pepper in large bowl until blended.
Add remaining ingredients except cantaloupe; toss. Cover and refrigerate about 2 hours or until chilled.
Spoon salad onto cantaloupe wedges.
Yields 6 servings.

title: taco salad
directions: In 10-inch skillet, over medium heat, cook beef and chili powder until browned and no longer pink, stirring to separate meat.
Spoon off fat.
Stir in soup mix and water.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low.
Cook 10 minutes stirring occasionally.
Arrange lettuce and tortilla chips on plates. Spoon hot meat mixture over chips.
Top with tomatoes and cheese. Makes 6 servings.

title: lemon bars
directions: Blend and press into greased 10 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni until tender.
Place a layer of macaroni noodles on the bottom of casserole dish followed by a layer of cheese. Dot with butter.
Repeat this sequence until you run out of ingredients, adding salt and pepper to taste.
Top the casserole with a layer of crushed saltines.
Combine milk and eggs; pour over casserole.
Bake at 350° until bubbling and golden brown.

title: sausage biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Break sausage into small pieces; mix with Bisquick and cheese (with hands is easiest).
Form into small balls the size of a quarter; flatten slightly.
Bake about 10 minutes.
This can be done ahead and frozen.
No need to thaw before baking.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix cake as directed on box. Bake in tube pan at 350° for 40 minutes or until toothpick is inserted and comes out clean. Remove from pan and cool. Serve with Cool Whip or frosted.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix sugar, peanut butter, butter and vanilla and roll into 1-inch balls.
Place on an aluminum foil-covered cookie sheet. Refrigerate.

title: overnight vegetable beef soup
directions: Put all ingredients in crock-pot.
Turn on low and cook for 10 to 12 hours.
Any extra can be cooked on stovetop until potatoes and carrots are done.
Freeze leftovers to have soup all winter.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix chicken, sour cream, and half of the cheese.
Fill tortillas with chicken mixture and roll up.
Place in a 9 x 13 inch pan in two rows.
Spread a thin layer of butter or margarine on top of the rolled tortillas.
Heat the sauce and soup together and pour over the enchiladas.
Sprinkle the remaining cheese on top.
Bake at 350 degrees until bubbly.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add pumpkin, eggs and vanilla. Beat well; sift together flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt and spices.
Add to creamed mixture.
Stir in raisins and nutmeats.
Drop dough from teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet about 2 inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool. Yield:
7 dozen.

title: puppy chow
directions: Place peanut butter, margarine and chips in 1-quart microwave bowl.
Microwave on High for 1 1/2 minutes or until margarine melts and chips are soft.
Stir until blended.

title: baked potato wedges
directions: Place potatoes and oil in plastic bag; shake until potatoes are coated with oil.
Place wedges on cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with garlic salt and paprika.
Bake at 400° for 1/2 hour.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Saute hamburger, pepperoni and onions lightly. Melt butter and place in 2 1/2-quart baking dish or 11 x 13-inch dish.
Toss cooked spaghetti with butter. Cover with 1 can tomato sauce. Add 1/2 cheese and 1/2 meat. Add all mushrooms.
Sprinkle on oregano and basil. Add rest of cheeses and meat. Top with tomato sauce. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: egg and sausage casserole
directions: Beat eggs eith milk and salt.
Layer bread in bottom of pan (13 x 9-inch).
Pour egg mixture over bread.
Layer sausage on top. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour. Sprinkle cheese on top last 10 minutes.

title: crisscross cookies
directions: Mix together thoroughly the shortening, sugar and egg.
Stir in the milk and lemon or vanilla extract.
Sift together and stir in the flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt.
Stir in the raisins or nuts or both.
Roll into balls the size of small walnuts. Place on ungreased cookie sheet about 3-inches apart.
Flatten with fork dipped in flour, making a crisscross pattern.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 400°.

title: quick dip
directions: Combine ingredients.
Let stand in refrigerator ready to serve. Serve with potato chips.

title: hot sausage balls
directions: Make sausage into 1-inch balls and fry, turning often.
Mix remaining ingredients and bring to a boil. Add sausage balls and stir well. Cool, cover and refrigerate for 24 hours. Reheat and serve with picks.

title: sausage lasagne wraps
directions: Cook and drain the noodles.
Divide the sausage into 6 pieces. Split lengthwise and stuff with 1/2 slice of Mozzarella cheese. Wrap each piece in a lasagne noodle.
Place in baking dish and cover with the Italian sauce.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with grated Parmesan cheese.
Quick and good!

title: key lime pie
directions: Blend lime juice, Eagle Brand and egg yolks together.
Put into crust.
Put in fridge.
Put Cool Whip on top of mixture after it has chilled 1 hour.
Cut up lime in small slices.
Garnish the top.
Pie needs to remain cold.

title: cheese broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Place in a shallow casserole. Melt butter, saute onion in butter;
blend in soup and cheese. Pour over
broccoli.
Cover
with
Ritz crackers (crushed) or croutons. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: garlic bread sticks
directions: Cut bread slices into 1-inch strips. Mix butter and garlic powder in a bowl.
Dip bread in mixture.
Roll in crushed cereal. Place on baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes.

title: fruit delight
directions: Combine fruit and sugar and bring to a boil.
Reserve. Combine dry ingredients and butter.
Blend and add milk.
Mix. Pour into baking dish.
Pour over this batter the fruit or berry mixture.
Bake for 35 minutes or until brown at 350°.
Batter will rise to top.

title: almond roca cracker dessert
directions: Line a cookie sheet with foil and spray well with Pam.
Line pan with 40 single soda crackers.
Boil butter and brown sugar gently for 3 minutes.
Pour over crackers and spread.
Bake in oven at 350° for 5 minutes.
Let cool.
Melt chocolate chips and spread over top.
Put in fridge.

title: heavenly chicken
directions: Cover chicken with water and cook until done.
Pick chicken off the bone and cut.
Mix together until smooth 2 cans chicken noodle soup and 1 can cream of chicken soup.
Add eggs to the soup mixture.
Melt oleo in a small pan and mix with 1 cup chicken broth (from cooked chicken).
Combine stuffing mix cubes and flavor packet, then add 1 cup of dry mix to soup and eggs and fold this into the chicken.
Put into buttered baking dish.
Mix the remaining dry stuffing mix with the oleo and broth mix and put over chicken.
Cover the pan with foil.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Uncover and bake 15 more minutes to brown.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Beat margarine, sugar, egg, milk and vanilla together until light and fluffy.
Stir in flour and baking powder, mixing well. Chill dough thoroughly.
Roll small portions of dough at a time on a lightly floured board.
Using a cookie cutter, cut out shapes, sprinkle with sugar and place on a lightly greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° about 8 minutes.
Cool and store in tightly covered containers.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: scotch eggs
directions: Shape sausage into 8 patties.
Wrap one patty around one cooked egg, covering completely.
Roll each egg in beaten eggs and cracker crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes until meat is no longer pink.
Serve with chili sauce, if desired.

title: italian mushrooms
directions: Wash fresh whole mushrooms.
Drain off water.
Place mushrooms in large bowl. Pour Italian dressing over mushrooms and chill for 2 hours.
Stir and serve.

title: orange or grape sherbet
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into ice cream freezer and crank until frozen.
Makes 1 gallon.
Minute Maid seems to give a better taste than Slice.

title: deluxe chicken breast
directions: Place chicken breasts between pieces of waxed paper. Flatten slightly with palm of your hand. Whisk egg yolks and water. Combine flour, salt, pepper, paprika, bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese. Dip chicken breasts in egg yolk; roll in bread crumb mixture. Brown chicken breasts in butter on both sides. Place in shallow baking dish. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: border buttermilk
directions: Place all ingredients in blender.
Fill with crushed ice, up to 3/4 full.
Blend until mixture is mushy or foamy.
Serve immediately.
Yields 7 to 8 servings.
(This is a regional drink served along the Mexican border.)

title: taco salad
directions: Brown meat, drain fat off, add kidney beans and chili powder, simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.
Cool.
Combine all other ingredients in a large bowl; add meat mixture.
Toss.
May add onions, fresh lemon juice, ripe olives to salad.

title: cherry cake
directions: Cream together sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and beat thoroughly.
Add 1 cup of the flour, salt, soda, baking powder and spices and mix thoroughly.
Add and mix remaining 1 3/4 cups flour, milk and cherry juice.
Fold in drained pitted cherries and the nuts.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
After removing cake from oven, let it stand on cake rack about 5 minutes, then remove from pan.
Let cake cool on cake rack. Serve while it is still a little bit warm with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: creamy lime salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water; cool slightly.
Stir in milk.
Add pineapple and lemon juice.
Stir in cottage cheese, celery, mayonnaise and chopped nuts.
Place in refrigerator to set.

title: wassail
directions: Heat cider and 1 cinnamon stick to boiling.
Decrease heat. Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Uncover and stir in remaining ingredients, except orange slices and cinnamon sticks.
Simmer 5 minutes longer.
Serve in punch bowl.
Float orange slices on top. Use cinnamon sticks as stirrers.

title: hog head cheese
directions: Split hog head and cook in salted water until rags away from the bone (can
be
torn by hand).
Allow to cool.
Remove excess fat.
Use
hand
and
shred
into tiny pieces, removing small bones as you
do
this.
Season to taste using sage, red pepper and salt (Morton sausage seasoning may be substituted). Mix well. Put into
loaf
pan,
drain
off grease and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Continue	to drain off fat as it accumulates. Refrigerate.
Slice and serve.

title: quick and easy fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill until serving time.

title: sweet potato louise
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and add sweet potatoes and orange juice.
Put into large baking dish and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: hot seafood salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Top with buttered bread crumbs and slivered almonds.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: superintendent's cheesecake
directions: Beat all together until smooth and bubbly.
Pour in graham cracker crust.
Bake 20 minutes at 375°.
Cool for 25 minutes. Pour topping and refrigerate for several hours.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar, add bananas and continue creaming until completely smooth.
Add eggs and beat.
Sift flour and soda together, add to banana mixture with buttermilk in four additions, beat after each addition.
Mix in pecans, vanilla and bourbon. Pour batter into 3 greased and floured 9 inch layer pans.
Bake at 350 degree for 45 to 50 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cool on racks.
Ice with Banana Nut Frosting or any caramel frosting.

title: hot vegetable punch for eight
directions: Simmer condensed bouillon, an equal amount of water, tomato juice with celery, onions, bay leaf and black peppers.
Toss in a few carrot slices and any sprigs of parsley you happen to have. When the vegetables have added their flavor to the brew, squeeze 1/4 of lemon into the pot.
Strain hot punch into punch bowl.
Set the garnishes afloat.

title: loaf bread or rolls
directions: Mix together the first 3 ingredients and let set while mixing the other ingredients.
Beat eggs; add oil, water, sugar and salt. Add yeast mixture.
Add 4 cups flour and mix with mixer.
Then add rest by hand.
Let rise; knead down.
Put in pans to rise again. Makes 3 loaves or 2 loaves and 10 to 12 rolls.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes (less for rolls).
Can put in fridge before first rising and use as needed.
Will keep about a week.

title: seaside ambrosia
directions: Mix mayonnaise, juice and sugar.
Combine with shrimp, celery, oranges and onions.
Fill avocados with mixture.
Sprinkle coconut on top.
Can be served as an entree or salad with seafood dinner (fish or shrimp).

title: orange angel food cake dessert
directions: Prepare and bake cake according to package directions, using an ungreased 10-inch tube pan. Immediately invert tube pan. Cool completely.

title: orange pineapple salad
directions: Bring water, jello and pineapple to a boil.
Cool and chill. Mix celery and nuts to partially set gelatin.
Chill.
Mash cream cheese with fork until softened.
Mix Dream Whip according to directions.
Fold in cheese and Dream Whip with first mixture and chill.

title: *reuben meat loaf
directions: Combine tomato sauce and sugar.
Mix together 1/4 cup of sauce, ground beef, corned beef, bread crumbs, onion, garlic and mustard.
Pat meat firmly into a 12 x 5-inch rectangle on a sheet of waxed paper.
Combine sauerkraut, caraway and cheese.
Spread over meat to within 1 inch of edges.
Roll up meat jelly roll fashion, starting at short edge.
Seal seams and ends.
Using the waxed paper to lift the roll, gently ease meat loaf, seam side down, onto a shallow 12 x 18-inch pan.
Spread half of the sauce over loaf.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.
Spread remaining sauce over loaf.
Bake 10 minutes.
Arrange cheese slices over top. Return to oven until cheese melts.

title: rene's famous pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and butter.
Add rest of ingredients.
Bake in moderate oven about 350° to 375° for 45 minutes or until set. Do not bake in too hot an oven or the nuts will burn and center will be runny.

title: yammies
directions: Melt butter; pour over cake mix and add first 1/3 cup milk. Pour 1/2 of cake mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 8 minutes at 350°.
While it is baking, melt caramels with 2nd 1/3 cup milk. Sprinkle chocolate chips and nuts over hot baked cake mix and pour melted caramels over that.
Put remaining half of cake mixture over caramel.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: simple sesame cookies
directions: Beat butter and add sugar.
Gradually stir in remaining ingredients.
Roll into tubes and chill until firm.
Slice and bake at 300° until golden brown.
Yields about 3 dozen.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Mix.
Stuff in cored peppers and wrap in foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Makes approximately 10 large peppers.

title: roberta's fruit salad(makes 6 salads)
directions: Peel and section the oranges.
Cut up the sections.
Add the sugar and the orange juice.
Stir this until the sugar is dissolved.
Peel and cut up the apples. Add them to the orange mixture.
Next peel and cut up the bananas and the kiwis.
Add this to the mixture.

title: strawberry dump cake
directions: Crumble cake into bite size pieces.
Mix Cool Whip, sour cream, milk, and sugar.
Slice strawberries and mix with glaze. Use large bowl.
Layer cake, Cool Whip mixture and strawberries until gone ending with strawberries.

title: sicilian chicken
directions: Heat oil in a large nonstick pan over medium heat.
Add onion, green pepper and mushrooms.
Cook until slightly tender, about 10 minutes.
Cut chicken into 2-inch pieces; add to onion mixture. Cook, turning chicken frequently, until pink is gone.
Add remaining ingredients; simmer for 10 to 15 minutes, until heated through and chicken is cooked.
Serve with rice.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add egg, milk and oil; mix well.
Fold in blueberries.
Spoon into cupcake paper-lined muffin pan.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 8 muffins.

title: refrigerator whole wheat rolls
directions: Scald milk.
Add sugar, salt and shortening.
Cool to lukewarm.
Sprinkle yeast on warm water; stir to dissolve. Combine milk mixture, 1 cup whole wheat flour and 1 cup all-purpose flour.
Beat well with electric mixer at medium speed, scraping the bowl occasionally, about 2 minutes.
Add yeast mixture and eggs and beat well.
Stir in enough remaining flours, a little at a time, to make a soft dough that leaves the sides of the bowl.

title: creamy caramel-pecan rolls
directions: For Topping:
In a small mixing bowl, stir together powdered sugar and whipping cream.
Divide evenly between two 9 x 1 1/2-inch round baking pans.
Sprinkle pecans evenly over sugar mixture.

title: streusel pear pie
directions: Cook pears on low heat until tender or use canned pears.
Add 2 tablespoons flour and 1/3 cup sugar to juice.
Cook until thick. Put pears into pie shell and cover with juice that has been thickened.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.
Top with 1/3 cup sugar, 1/3 cup flour, butter and coconut.
Mix well.
Sprinkle on top of pie.
Bake 10 minutes longer until lightly brown.
Serve warm or cold.

title: italian-style chicken salad
directions: Pour artichoke hearts and marinade into a large serving bowl. Cut artichoke hearts in half.
Add remaining ingredients.
Toss to mix.
Serve with red wine vinegar if you prefer a more acidic dressing.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in frying pan; stir in all of the stuffing mix.
Set aside 1/2 cup buttered stuffing mix. Combine remaining stuffing mix with all other ingredients. Smooth into buttered casserole; top with reserved 1/2 cup stuffing mix.
Bake, uncovered, for 25 minutes, or until browned.
Can be assembled ahead.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: minestrone soup
directions: Brown hamburg and sausage together, then drain off fat.
In large pot, mix all together; bring to a boil.
Turn down heat and simmer 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: tuna burgers
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Divide evenly onto rolls.
Wrap in aluminum foil and place on cookie sheet.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix preceding ingredients and let set in refrigerator.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Mix well the last 6 ingredients.
Spread a thin layer of mixture on each flour tortilla and roll up.
Wrap rolled tortillas in Saran Wrap; freeze.
Slice in pieces.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix by hand.
Add eggs to apples and stir.
Add sugar and cinnamon.
Add oil and nuts; mix well.
Add flour, salt and baking powder.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: key lime pie
directions: In a large heat resistant bowl, dissolve gelatin in boiling water. With wire whisk, stir in yogurt; with wooden spoon, fold in whipped topping.
Transfer mixture to prepared crust; refrigerate overnight or at least 2 hours.

title: quick-and-easy barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in a saucepan and bring to a boil. Lower heat and simmer 2 minutes.
Use on chicken, ribs or frankfurters.
Yields about 2 1/2 cups.

title: carrot cake
directions: Cream together cream cheese and butter in a mixing bowl. Slowly sift in confectioners sugar and continue beating until fully incorporated.
Mixture should be free of lumps.
Stir in vanilla and lemon juice if you use it.
Frosting for a 2-layer cake.

title: slush
directions: Boil water and sugar.
Add Jell-O, almond extract, pineapple juice and 9 cups water.
Freeze! Note:
Two hours before you need it, set it out of the freezer.

title: butterscotch pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Melt morsels in a double boiler or microwave.
Remove from heat and set aside.
In a large bowl combine corn syrup, eggs and salt; beat well.
Gradually blend in melted butterscotch and beat until smooth.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into large unbaked pie shell.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake for 50 minutes.
Cool and garnish with whipped cream.
(This recipe does not need sugar because the butterscotch replaces it.)

title: spanish rice
directions: Combine tomato sauce, water, onion, green pepper, butter, salt, sugar, mustard and pepper in pan.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Stir in rice.
Remove from heat. Cover and let stand for 5 minutes.

title: beef and pinwheel casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion in butter; sprinkle with salt, pepper and flour.
Stir in peas and pour in greased shallow casserole and set aside.
Make biscuit dough and turn out on lightly floured board and knead gently 1/2 minute; roll or pat 1/2 inch thick and spread with melted butter.
Sprinkle with chopped parsley and roll up like a jellyroll.
Cut in 1/2 inch slices and place cut side down on top of meat and vegetable mixture.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: blueberry gems
directions: Combine flour and sugar in a large bowl; set aside.
Combine eggs, vanilla, oil and milk.
Make a well in the center of the dry ingredients.
Pour in the liquid mixture.
Stir until well mixed. Fold in the blueberries and stir 1 minute.
Put batter into muffin tins, filling about half full.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes. Yield:
2 dozen.

title: glen's sour cream pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift flour and soda together.
Add 1/4 teaspoon salt to egg whites and beat until stiff.
Cream the margarine and sugar and add remaining salt, vanilla and almond. Add the egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add the flour mixture alternately with sour cream. Fold in egg whites and pour into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake 1 hour.
Cool on rack.

title: key lime pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour into graham cracker crust. Put into freezer until firm.
You can put a few drops of food color (green).

title: italian beef
directions: Place all ingredients in slow cooker on low for all day.

title: homemade pizza crust
directions: Mix flour and melted shortening together.
Add just enough water to make it doughy.
Spread crust on a large 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and bake for 17 minutes at 350°.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix beef, crumbs, onion, egg, salt, pepper and 1/2 can of the tomato sauce. Form into loaf and put in a shallow 7 x 9-inch pan. Pour remaining 1/2 can tomato sauce over loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: nacho snack
directions: Put in saucepan and stir soup in cheese and milk.
Heat over low heat until cheese is melted and bubbling, stirring constantly. Stir in salsa, pepper and onion; remove from heat.
Serve in a round bowl with chips, bread chunks or fresh vegetables.

title: sweet potatoes a la orange(diabetic recipe)
directions: Arrange sweet potatoes in a shallow baking pan.
Combine oleo and cinnamon.
Pour over potatoes.
Arrange apricot halves on top. Cover dish and bake at 425° for about 15 minutes.
Add orange slices and serve.
Exchanges:
One bread, 1 fruit and 1 fat.

title: curry chicken
directions: Cook chicken and cool.
Cook broccoli until nearly tender. Place well-drained broccoli in buttered baking dish.
Cover with cut-up chicken.
Mix soup, mayonnaise, cheese, evaporated milk, lemon juice and curry powder.
Pour over chicken.
